  var POSITIONS = {"jobs":{"Scholarship for Women in Engineering":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYisAAG"},"body_text":"## Eligibility Requirements\r\n\r\n* Only undergraduate students may apply\r\n* Applicants should be able to demonstrate a strong focus in a science, technology, engineering, or math (STEM) field\r\n* Applicants should have completed at least one full academic year\r\n* Applicants must be currently enrolled at an accredited college or university\r\n* Applicants must intend to be active, full-time students during the 2015-2016 academic year\r\n* Applicants must be women\r\n* Applicants must be eligible to work in the United States","createdbyid":"00580000004b91CAAQ","createddate":"2015-06-06T02:26:39.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYisAAG","intro_text":"From finding missing and exploited children to combating human trafficking to providing relief to victims of natural disasters, organizations around the world depend on good technology to solve hard problems that affect millions of people.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-06T02:26:39.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Scholarship for Women in Engineering","requirements_text":"## Application process\r\n\r\nPlease submit a copy of:\r\n\r\n1. Current undergraduate transcript\r\n2. Curriculum Vitae and/or professional resume (as relevant)\r\n3. A thoughtful response to the following prompt (max. 500 words):\r\n** Describe a technical project you are currently working on, or have worked on in the past. This can be an individual or team project, completed in an academic or extra-curricular setting. We'd like to hear about the problem, how you used technology to apply a practical solution, the impact of the project, and challenges you overcame along the way. Please limit your essay to 500 words or less.\r\n\r\n## Workshop and Interview\r\n\r\n* Scholarship finalists will interview at Statsopt’s headquarters in Palo Alto, CA (Statsopt will cover the cost of travel) to participate in a full day workshop with Statsopt engineers.\r\n\r\n## Scholarship Award\r\n\r\n* Several grants, ranging from $1,500 to $10,000, will be awarded for the 2015-2016 academic year.\r\n* The scholarships are awarded to recipients for one academic year only and are not available for extension or renewal.\r\n* Select finalists will complete a Statsopt internship in either Summer of Fall 2016.\r\n\r\n## Deadlines:\r\n\r\n* Applications are due August 31, 2015","status":"Published","team":"Engineering","team_slug":"engineering","name_slug":"scholarship-for-women-in-engineering","positions":["a0m80000002jFvFAAU"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000002jFvFAAU","application_id":"a0m80000002jFvF"}],"url":"/careers/positions/scholarship-for-women-in-engineering/"},"Member of the Technical Staff":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYixAAG"},"body_text":"The domains are diverse, but the problems all are ill-defined and require ingenuity in modeling. For example, is an observed pattern of behavior malicious? Where should patients optimally start their treatments? What is the value of a purely discretionary bonus? How should we price insurance for an event that has never occurred? Team members individually and in collaboration with one another decide how best to find answers often by interviewing domain experts, reviewing papers, and implementing novel techniques. The team is committed to delivering outcomes, even if sometimes those outcomes are akin to proofs of impossibility, and sees firsthand how the answers change decisions at Statsopt and its customers.","createdbyid":"00580000004b91CAAQ","createddate":"2015-06-06T02:29:32.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYixAAG","intro_text":"Statsopt is hiring mathematicians for a new team to solve some of the hardest problems the company and its customers face.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-09T18:49:56.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Member of the Technical Staff","requirements_text":"## Requirements:\r\n\r\n* Ph.D. or equivalent degree in mathematics (dissertation still in progress acceptable).\r\n* Experience adapting techniques in research papers to specific problems.\r\n* Fluency in scientific programming (MATLAB, Python, R, SQL, etc.).\r\n* Willingness to work in Palo Alto, California.\r\n\r\n## How do you apply?\r\n\r\nPlease submit an academic CV and cover letter here.","status":"Published","team":"Finance and Accounting","team_slug":"finance-and-accounting","name_slug":"member-of-the-technical-staff","positions":["a0m80000005s9GpAAI"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000005s9GpAAI","application_id":"a0m80000005s9Gp"}],"url":"/careers/positions/member-of-the-technical-staff/"},"Project Assistant, Ninja Operations":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYUOAA4"},"body_text":"The Ninja Ops team is the organizational backbone of Statsopt's Legal Ninja team and we're excited to hire a new Ninja Project Assistant! You're the ideal Ninja Project Assistant candidate if you have a great attitude, are a critical thinker, and look forward to arriving at work each morning to conquer new challenges with grace and humor. You want to be challenged and like to take ownership of projects that you work on. You are impeccably organized, and you are quick to support others when they are not so organized. You manage to be both obsessed with details AND the bigger picture at the same time. Efficiency is your friend, and you're passionate about creating processes to further important goals. You are stellar at implementing recommended solutions, but you also thrive on the challenge of crafting solutions on your own. You are excited to tackle substantive projects and develop new skill sets, including legal research and writing, contract drafting and editing, and complex analysis. You love being part of and contributing to a team, you're excited about Statsopt's mission, you yearn for a job that will fully utilize and expand on your already strong skills, and you think ninjas are pretty cool.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYUOAA4","intro_text":"Ninja Project Assistants have great attitudes, are critical thinkers, and look forward to arriving at work each morning to conquer new challenges with grace and humor.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Project Assistant, Ninja Operations","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities \n\n*   Document management administration\n*   Manage scheduling and calendars\n*   Legal research and writing\n*   Contract drafting and editing\n*   Coordinate international and domestic travel\n*   Complete personal errands and projects\n*   Coordinate team events\n*   Manage team expense reports\n*   Edit and proofread text\n*   Various other awesome administrative support duties\n\n## Requirements \n\n*   Extremely well organized with a proven ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment\n*   Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills\n*   Great sense of humor\n*   Strong analytical and organizational skills\n*   Great teamwork skills\n*   Availability during nights and weekends as needed\n*   Excellent computer skills, including knowledge of Microsoft programs (Office, Outlook, Excel)\n*   BA/BS from a top college or university","status":"Published","team":"Legal","team_slug":"legal","name_slug":"project-assistant-ninja-operations","positions":["a0m80000005MK1yAAG"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000005MK1yAAG","application_id":"a0m80000005MK1y"}],"url":"/careers/positions/project-assistant-ninja-operations/"},"Business Operations and Strategy":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYRoAAO"},"body_text":"“Statsopt Technologies will not help you share, message, pin, post or chat. It does not exist to make you more social or connected, or even to help advertisers get to you. Its technology is deeply geeky, its work secretive. Nonetheless, it’s one of the most valuable private tech companies in Silicon Valley.”  - [New York Times, May 2014](http://www.nytimes.com/2014/06/01/business/unlocking-secrets-if-not-its-own-value.html?_r=3)\n\nStatsopt transforms the way the world’s most important institutions use data to solve their toughest problems. We have helped European authorities [shut down child pornography rings](https://www.Statsopt.com/wp-assets/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Impact_Study_Fighting_Child_Pornography.pdf), US special operations [fight terrorist networks](https://www.washingtonian.com/articles/people/killer-app/), hedge funds [prevent insider trading](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-03-19/sac-retains-Statsopt-to-boost-surveillance-after-charges.html), and biomedical researchers [search for the next life-saving therapy](https://www.Statsopt.com/solutions/pharma/). Are you ready to commit yourself to the tough, rewarding job of scaling Silicon Valley’s most mission-driven company through hypergrowth?\n\n## What we do\n\nStatsopt has limitless opportunities for growth; our team exists to remove all obstacles to that growth. We analyze these obstacles, solve them, and ensure that they don’t happen again.\n\nWe work with leaders across the company on an unmatched diversity of problems. We might be working with engineers to prioritize product features for billion-dollar deployments one month, helping business leaders think through realigning our organizational structure the following, and directly supporting customers as they analyze data using Statsopt’s software the next. No two days are the same.\n\n## What you will experience\n\nYou will be responsible for leading entire projects and owning their outcomes from start to finish. You will need to be innovative, self-motivated, collaborative, and capable of dealing with complex interpersonal dynamics. You will need to bring your qualitative and quantitative analytical skills to the fore as you drive outcomes within Statsopt’s contrarian culture. We’re not looking for strategists who just want to make PPTs. Strategy is important but means nothing without execution.\n\nYou will be a part of a team of talented individuals who are just as passionate about supporting one another as they are about Statsopt’s mission. We operate in a high accountability, high expectation, iron-sharpens-iron environment where the goal is always to produce the best solution. Honesty and willingness to accept feedback are critical.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:47.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYRoAAO","intro_text":"As strategists, we rely on our qualitative and quantitative analytical skills as we drive outcomes within Statsopt’s contrarian culture. We’re not looking for strategists who just want to make PPTs—strategy is important but means nothing without execution.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Business Operations and Strategy","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Take ownership of projects that Statsoptians have identified as a top priority\n*   Work across teams to engage stakeholders, deeply understand problems, and gather data\n*   Diagnose complex problems and develop compelling, data-driven recommendations\n*   Relentlessly and swiftly execute on those recommendations until stakeholders are satisfied\n*   Take care of your teammates\n*   Dedicate time for reflection to continually self-improve\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   BA/BS (or MA/MS) from a top university or equivalent experience\n*   At least one year of experience (typically more) in a role that requires rigorous financial or business analytics and/or strategic thought\n*   Sample (not comprehensive) backgrounds: Quantitative public policy &amp; nonprofit, bioinformatics, investment banking, private equity, data science\n*   Intellectual curiosity and creativity\n*   Ability to grow and execute on both tactical detail and the big picture\n*   Not afraid of long hours; able to handle stress well and maintain a positive attitude\n*   Adaptive and introspective; willing to learn, teach, lead, and follow","status":"Published","team":"Business Development","team_slug":"business-development","name_slug":"business-operations-and-strategy","positions":["a0m80000005X2n5AAC","a0m80000003lX9SAAU"],"offices":[{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000005X2n5AAC","application_id":"a0m80000005X2n5"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000003lX9SAAU","application_id":"a0m80000003lX9S"}],"url":"/careers/positions/business-operations-and-strategy/"},"Information Security Engineer (Infrastructure)":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTQAA4"},"body_text":"Our Information Security team is responsible for the security of Statsopt's people and infrastructure around the globe. As a member of the Information Security team, your technical expertise is second only to your professionalism and passion for security and technology in general. You're a highly motivated team player that thrives on solving problems and tackling new challenges.\n\nYou're designing, building, feeding, and caring for mission-critical systems that power Statsopt. You're passionate about supporting the Information Security Team, and the entire company, by finding new and meaningful ways to drive security change—through infrastructure, policy, process, or tooling. Your day-to-day work impacts the success of the enterprise, and empowers network defenders to hunt for badness across our global network, wherever it may hide.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTQAA4","intro_text":"Information Security Engineers are part of a team responsible for the security of Statsopt's people and infrastructure around the globe. When it comes to infrastructure, we are always looking for new and meaningful ways to drive security change.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Information Security Engineer (Infrastructure)","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Design, build, and maintain mission-critical infrastructure that support information security controls and operations\n*   Perform research and evaluation of new infrastructure, products, services, and security controls to shape the defense posture of Statsopt\n*   Deploy, manage, monitor, and tune data feeds, analysis pipelines, and sensors\n*   Understand pain-points for the Information Security team, and find new and novel ways to reduce friction and enable mission success\n*   Assist network defenders in hunting badness across our infrastructure\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   Active TS/SCI security clearance or willingness and eligibility to obtain a security clearance\n*   Strong experience with at least two of the following languages: Python (Preferred), Bash (Preferred), Powershell (Preferred), Perl, Ruby, C/C++, or Java\n*   Strong system engineering, architecture, and administration skills in one or more major operating system platforms: Windows, OS X, or Linux\n*   Strong experience with one or more IDS/IPS platforms\n*   Strong working knowledge of TCP/IP networking and system troubleshooting skills\n*   Strong investigative mindset with the ability to contextualize and understand security events from various sources\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   Experience managing PKI Infrastructure\n*   Experience managing Firewall or VPN platforms\n*   Experience managing endpoint security services and products\n*   Experience performing application security reviews, offensive assessments, penetration testing, exploit development, or vulnerability analysis","status":"Published","team":"Security","team_slug":"security","name_slug":"information-security-engineer-infrastructure","positions":["a0m80000006J9rCAAS"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000006J9rCAAS","application_id":"a0m80000006J9rC"}],"url":"/careers/positions/information-security-engineer-infrastructure/"},"International Corporate/Securities Legal Ninja":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYVCAA4"},"body_text":"First and foremost, you’ll be an all-star contributor to the Legal Ninja team and to the company as a whole—working on every issue Statsopt faces, from negotiating partnership agreements with Fortune 50 companies to working on regulatory, intellectual property, employment, and international issues. However, you’ll also be a specialist, spending a considerable amount of your time working on corporate/securities issues, and interacting directly (and frequently!) with our General Counsel, CFO, and CEO. \n\nYou will focus much of your time on financings, securities filings, board matters (including attendance at board meetings), and general stock/option administration. You will be comfortable independently negotiating complex deals and then crystallizing agreed upon terms in a written contract. You like taking ill-defined objectives and taking ownership to achieve epic outcomes. You are funny and easy to get along with, and are able to quickly connect with a wide variety of personality types. You are low ego, able to laugh at yourself, and can find enjoyment even in stressful situations. You want to work at Statsopt because of our mission, not our valuation. You are diligent, hardworking, and awesome.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYVCAA4","intro_text":"International Corporate/Securities Legal Ninjas are the legal backbone of our equity and corporate governance team.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"International Corporate/Securities Legal Ninja","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Advise on a multitude of often complex equity and securities issues (including financings, mergers, and acquisitions, etc.)\n*   Corporate governance for Statsopt and our subsidiaries\n*   Lead contract drafting and negotiating\n*   Assist in management and day-to-day administration of Statsopt’s equity portfolio\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   2-10+ years as a corporate/securities attorney at a top firm or in-house (a combination is even better!)\n*   BA/BS with a strong academic record from a top university\n*   JD from a top law school\n*   Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills\n*   Experience with venture-backed financings, M&A, corporate governance, board matters, and stock option administration\n*   Extremely well organized with a proven ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment\n*   Strong attention to detail\n*   Available during nights and weekends as needed\n*   Great sense of humor\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   Experience in a start-up or high-tech environment\n*   Passion for technology","status":"Published","team":"Legal","team_slug":"legal","name_slug":"international-corporate-securities-legal-ninja","positions":["a0m80000006SChBAAW"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000006SChBAAW","application_id":"a0m80000006SChB"}],"url":"/careers/positions/international-corporate-securities-legal-ninja/"},"Finance Operations Analyst, New Grad":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYSmAAO"},"body_text":"Finance Operations Analysts are working hard to build the financial infrastructure of Statsopt Technologies. This means that we are constantly building new financial models, systems, procedures and analyses that will scale with Statsopt's exponential growth. Fin-Ops Analysts are jack-of-all-trades. Our team has a vast skillset and is comprised of Financial Analysts, Accountants, Tax Gurus, Database Whizzes, Domestic and International Payroll Experts, and Expense Analysts. Our wide range of skills allows us to tackle any problem regardless of where it lies.\n\nAs a Fin-Ops Analyst you will hit the ground running-learning new skills every day as you experience life in a dynamic, high-growth, unstructured environment. Fin-Ops Analysts need to know the ins and outs of every financial system and process at Statsopt. Newcomers will learn everything they need to know about the organization from the ground up through a series of training and professional growth programs.\n\nStatsopt is a strict meritocracy; we offer the opportunity to take responsibility over new projects as quickly as you can handle them. After mastering many different skill sets, you have free reign to create and to manage your own projects. Unlike traditional operations roles, our Finance Operations Analysts are exposed to hard problems spanning several different financial verticals, making for an exciting, unique, and educational professional experience.\n\nStatsopt’s Fin-Ops team is enthusiastic, fun, and tight-knit. We execute in a project-based environment with collaboration at every turn. We aren’t interested in keeping our heads down and entering data—we are passionate about improving how we work every day. We identify problems, old and new, create solutions, and implement them. We’re building the necessary systems to scale Statsopt as a company, and our impact is visible throughout the business.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYSmAAO","intro_text":"Statsopt's Finance Operations Analysts build new financial models, systems, procedures, and analyses. Whatever we happen to be building, our goal is always to improve upon the old and create systems that will scale with Statsopt's exponential growth.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Finance Operations Analyst, New Grad","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Identify, destroy, and re-build old systems that will not scale with Statsopt's Growth\n*   Identify, track, and create new metrics to improve business processes through analysis\n*   Create, implement, and track fiscal requirements across 20+ business sectors\n*   Act as a liaison between Finance and the Business Development and Engineering teams across the company and around the globe\n*   Iterate on financial & operational models built from scratch and then implement them\n*   Seek out unsolved problems and take initiative to address them\n*   Execute day-to-day operations of the Finance team: transactions processing, data entry, data cleansing, and quality control\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   BA/BS in Accounting, Finance, Economics, Engineering, or a related discipline\n*   Strong verbal and written communication skills\n*   Meticulous attention to detail and the ability to complete tasks with minimal oversight\n*   Ability to multitask\n*   Strong interpersonal skills\n*   Service-oriented\n*   Strong proficiency with Excel and PowerPoint\n*   Extremely hard worker, ethical, thoughtful, and most importantly, genuine\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   1-3 years of experience in a technology start-up environment","status":"Published","team":"Finance and Accounting","team_slug":"finance-and-accounting","name_slug":"finance-operations-analyst-new-grad","positions":["a0m80000004k6tSAAQ"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000004k6tSAAQ","application_id":"a0m80000004k6tS"}],"url":"/careers/positions/finance-operations-analyst-new-grad/"},"Accounts Payable Specialist":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYinAAG"},"body_text":"Solving the world’s hardest problems is no easy task. Our engineers often find themselves in the midst of combat zones, disaster relief efforts or even worse, boardrooms. Accounts Payable Specialists ensure that our engineers have every tool they need. We do this by managing numerous relationships with vendors across the country and around the globe that can provide our engineers with everything they need to make the world a safer place. As our company continues to grow, we are constantly thinking about how to improve and automate processes so we can continue providing amazing outcomes in even more places across the world.\r\n\r\nPlease note this is a contract position.","createdbyid":"00580000004b91CAAQ","createddate":"2015-06-06T02:21:01.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYinAAG","intro_text":"At Statsopt, Accounts Payable Specialists ensure that our engineers have every tool they need to crack some of the most challenging and puzzling problems on the planet.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-06T03:03:18.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Accounts Payable Specialist","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\r\n\r\n* Assist the AP team with full-cycle accounts payable responsibilities (including but not limited to: invoice processing, maintaining vendor records, running payment reports according to payment schedules and reconciling vendor statements)\r\n* Process 200-300 invoices per week\r\n* Organize, receive and coordinate the processing of vendor invoices\r\n* Work with the treasury team to create weekly payment batches\r\n* Assist with month-end activities, accruals, reconciliation, preparing 1099s and audit support\r\nAssist with ad-hoc requests\r\n\r\n## Qualifications\r\n\r\nAA/AS degree or equivalent experience in accounting\r\nOne year or more of related experience\r\nUnderstanding of full cycle accounts payable\r\nKnowledge of fundamental accounting related to accounts payable\r\nStrong organization skills, attention to detail highly accountable\r\nStrong interpersonal and professional communication skills\r\nExperience with Excel, Word, and Outlook\r\nAbility to prioritize and work in a deadline-sensitive and customer-service oriented environment","status":"Published","team":"Finance and Accounting","team_slug":"finance-and-accounting","name_slug":"accounts-payable-specialist","positions":["a0m80000005sXpFAAU"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000005sXpFAAU","application_id":"a0m80000005sXpF"}],"url":"/careers/positions/accounts-payable-specialist/"},"IT Network Engineer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTBAA4"},"body_text":"Being a member of the Networks team means you will be deeply involved in our mission to continue the evolution of Statsopt’s network services to prepare us for the known and unknown demands that are placed upon us. You will have the power to make your mark and to make a real difference in the lives of your colleagues and the success of the business by maintaining and improving our services.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTBAA4","intro_text":"The network is the core of any IT environment and allows the business to grow and adapt—as IT Network Engineers, we contribute to that success by solving complex network issues and deploy and scaling network infrastructure with minimal downtime.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"IT Network Engineer","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Collaborate with fellow engineers on designing resilient, scalable network architecture\n*   Solve complex network issues in production, colo, lab, and customer environments\n*   Deploy and scale network infrastructure with minimal downtime\n*   Develop creative solutions to complex technological challenges\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   5+ years of Networking experience; superior knowledge and hands-on experience of LAN (wired & wireless), WAN, and Firewall environments; understanding of all OSI layers from application to physical\n*   Extensive experience with two or more of the following vendors: Cisco, Arista, Palo Alto Networks, Juniper\n*   Extensive experience with Layer 2 protocols and associated enhancements (LACP, L2 ECMP, 802.1d/w/s, 802.1x, 802.1Q, etc.)\n*   Extensive experience with routing protocols and associated enhancements (BGP, OSPF, Anycast)\n*   Experience with cloud hosting services (e.g. AWS or GCE) with regards to network peering, performance tuning and perimeter security\n*   Deep knowledge in one or more of the following areas:\n     *   VPN (GRE, IPSec/SSL VPNs,)\n     *   Wireless (802.1a/b/g/n/ac)\n     *   Datacenter Virtualization (ESX/KVM/OpenNebula, etc.)\n     *   Global and Local Server Load-Balancing (GLB/SLB)\n     *   Multicast (PIM-SM, MSDP, IGMP)\n     *   DNS/DHCP\n     *   WDM (DWDM/CWDM)\n*   Strong programming skills (Python preferred), expertise with Git, and expertise with REST or JSON APIs\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   Experience with EMC SMARTS products\n*   Experience with Data Center design\n*   Experience with automation tools such as Puppet, Chef, etc.\n*   Experience with radio resource management and similar Wireless troubleshooting skills\n*   TS/SCI security clearance or willingness to get cleared","status":"Published","team":"Information Technology","team_slug":"information-technology","name_slug":"it-network-engineer","positions":["a0m80000005uIkYAAU","a0m80000005wSIuAAM","a0m80000005wSJ5AAM"],"offices":[{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000005wSIuAAM","application_id":"a0m80000005wSIu"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000005wSJ5AAM","application_id":"a0m80000005wSJ5"},{"office":"Washington, D.C.","position_id":"a0m80000005uIkYAAU","application_id":"a0m80000005uIkY"}],"url":"/careers/positions/it-network-engineer/"},"Communication Designer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYRtAAO"},"body_text":"Communication Designers create the brand touchpoints that connect us to our fellow employees, our customers, the media, and the world. We are a team of Graphic Designers, Motion Designers, and Web Designers. We’re the authors of visual systems for branding, marketing, presentations, and events. We create infographics that help people understand data, diagrams that explain our technology, and illustrations that tell our most important stories.\r\n\r\nAs a great Communication Designer, you exhibit stylistic breadth, attention to detail, and know how to balance beauty, clarity, and legibility. You have deep experience, from prepress to pixels, and posses a supreme eye for detail in color, typesetting, and layout. You have a strong sense of spacing and rhythm, and you love paragraphs as much as you love symbols and letters.\r\n\r\n## The Design Team\r\n\r\nThe Statsopt Design team is responsible for creating the human experience of using our software, as well as the execution of our brand. We design everything from user interfaces, to immersive experiences in our buildings and events, all the way down to awesome illustrated teeshirts we’re famous for.\r\n\r\nWe help to achieve connection and understanding. Our _users_ must create knowledge from data in our software, potential _customers_ and _candidates_ need to understand and relate to the story of our company and the awesome work we do, and its our job to help tell these stories.\r\n\r\nWe believe that everyone should have access to excellence in design—utility and beauty—in whatever form it takes. Designers are highly valued in the company for our vision, our ability to learn and adapt, and our creativity and inventiveness. We’re growing rapidly, yet focused on creating a tight-knit group of people that enjoy each other’s company in an atmosphere that fosters trust, integrity, empathy, and growth.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:47.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYRtAAO","intro_text":"Communication Designers create the brand touchpoints that connect us to our fellow employees, our customers, the media, and the world.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-09T18:31:57.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Communication Designer","requirements_text":"## What We Value\r\n\r\nExcellent communication skills. You have a proven ability to build great relationships, and convey and debate design rationale. You are the person that others can’t wait to collaborate with.\r\n\r\nEmpathy, not ego. We strive to understand our audience, and develop programs and assets that meet their needs.\r\n\r\nA love of technology. Statsopt is an engineering company, and we get to work with (and have to help explain) complex and powerful technological concepts and many kinds of audiences.\r\n\r\nA highly iterative design process. We move fast, we listen, and we adapt. We rapidly incorporate feedback, and we relentlessly collaborate. You must be adept at giving and receiving critiques.\r\n\r\nA mastery of tools. We move with ease across software and fidelity, depending on the task at hand. Illustrator, Photoshop, InDesign, or Keynote — and good old-fashioned pencil and paper.","status":"Published","team":"Design","team_slug":"design","name_slug":"communication-designer","positions":["a0m80000002jHYDAA2"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000002jHYDAA2","application_id":"a0m80000002jHYD"}],"url":"/careers/positions/communication-designer/"},"Equity Operations Analyst (Equity Shinobi)":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYSXAA4"},"body_text":"Statsopt Technologies seeks a motivated Equity Operations Analyst/Equity Shinobi to join our in-house team of Legal Ninjas. You are excited about equity administration, maintaining and tracking the ownership structure of private companies, and geek out over Excel shortcuts and formulas. You are extremely organized, resourceful, and detail oriented.. The two periods in the last sentence caught your eye immediately, made your heart sink, and almost stopped you from reading this job description because of your disdain for sloppy work product. \n\nYou are eager to get involved in the end-to-end administration of Statsopt’s equity incentive plans and can’t wait to reveal your passion for efficient, high-quality work product. Whether you are doing solo missions or working collaboratively with others, you love to achieve great results on challenging, time-sensitive projects. \n\nEquipped with your eagle eye for minute details, silver tongue for communicating in a clear and concise way, and boundless reserve of energy and self-motivation, you strive to produce perfect work product and adapt to a rapidly-growing software company that is solving some of the world’s hardest problems.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYSXAA4","intro_text":"Equity Shinobis have an eagle eye for minute details, a silver tongue for communicating in a clear and concise way, and a boundless reserve of energy and self-motivation. We strive to produce perfect work product and adapt to a rapidly-growing software company that is solving some of the world’s hardest problems.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Equity Operations Analyst (Equity Shinobi)","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   All aspects of equity administration, including managing a complex capitalization table, transaction processing and data entry, reconciliations/audits for quality control, investor analysis, and related tax reporting\n*   Collaborate with C-Level Executives, Finance, People Operations, Legal Ninjas, and other cross-functional teams to anticipate, implement, and/or address equity compensation matters\n*   Respond to inquiries from current, former, and potential employees about equity compensation\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   BA/BS in Business, Finance, Accounting, or a related discipline\n*   Strong proficiency in Excel\n*   Obsession for detail, organization, and ability to multitask\n*   Entrepreneurial mindset, with proven ability to be resourceful and experience improving and streamlining processes\n*   Demonstrated ability to problem-solve and complete complex projects under pressure\n*   Impeccable judgment, discretion, respect, and integrity\n*   Ability to work independently and as a team member in an unstructured environment\n*   Flexible schedule—we still operate in start-up mode and fire drills don't always fit within traditional business hours\n*   Great sense of humor\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   1+ years of experience as a paralegal, equity professional, or equivalent within a corporation or law firm\n*   Knowledge of private company equity-related administration, accounting, tax, and legal concepts\n*   Strong working knowledge of Shareworks or similar equity administration software\n*   Experience graphically representing data","status":"Published","team":"Legal","team_slug":"legal","name_slug":"equity-operations-analyst-equity-shinobi","positions":["a0m800000064dDaAAI"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m800000064dDaAAI","application_id":"a0m800000064dDa"}],"url":"/careers/positions/equity-operations-analyst-equity-shinobi/"},"Immigration Operations Specialist":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTGAA4"},"body_text":"Our Global Mobility Team supports the safe and seamless movement of Statsopt employees around the world. They are responsible for supporting and scaling Statsopt’s global immigration program in close coordination with internal stakeholders, external immigration counsel, and Statsopt’s dedicated People team.\n\nAs a member of the Global Mobility Team, the Immigration Operations Specialist builds and maintains the workflows and frameworks that support Statsopt immigration practices. They are meticulous project managers, comfortable and proactive working in ambiguous situations, and can handle a high volume of visa applications at various stages. This position will focus on non-U.S. immigration but may cover all aspects of immigration as needed.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTGAA4","intro_text":"As a member of the Global Mobility Team, the Immigration Operations Specialist builds and maintains the workflows and frameworks that support Statsopt immigration practices.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Immigration Operations Specialist","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Prepare employment-based immigration petitions with minimal supervision\n*   Engage with outside immigration counsel to initiate immigration applications\n*   Provide continuous support to applicants and keep all stakeholders appraised of the progress\n*   Establish process and workflows related to immigration applications\n*   Partner closely with our Global Mobility Team to support inbound global immigration petitions and employee relocation requests\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   BA/BS or equivalent practical experience\n*   2+ years of corporate immigration experience\n*   Strong interpersonal and teamwork skills\n*   Strong verbal and written communication skills\n*   Experience with any of the following visas: UK Tier 2, Singapore EP, Australia 457, UAE work authorization, or other relevant global work authorizations\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   Workday experience","status":"Published","team":"People Operations","team_slug":"people-operations","name_slug":"immigration-operations-specialist","positions":["a0m80000006SoWDAA0"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000006SoWDAA0","application_id":"a0m80000006SoWD"}],"url":"/careers/positions/immigration-operations-specialist/"},"Recruiter":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTIAA4"},"body_text":"As a Recruiter at Statsopt you will play a key role in helping to shape the organization's future by collaborating with colleagues across the company to consistently identify and attract brilliant people to our team. You will be constantly challenged to think creatively about how to drive hiring results. You will be part of a team that is responsible for developing, implementing, and executing a broad recruiting strategy, with a particular emphasis on sourcing high-quality active and passive candidates.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTIAA4","intro_text":"Recruiters at Statsopt play a key role in helping to shape the organization's future by collaborating with colleagues across the company to consistently identify and attract brilliant people to our team.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Recruiter","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Partner with hiring managers to develop, implement, and manage tactical sourcing strategies for technical and non-technical positions\n*   Build job descriptions and develop posting strategies for maximum exposure\n*   Outreach to prospective candidates to generate interest in Statsopt and positions\n*   Screen and qualify prospective candidates\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   BA/BS from a top university and technical degree preferred\n*   At least 3 years of recruiting experience, preferably in a technology environment\n*   Ability to consistently offer innovative solutions to recruiting challenges within the broader context of the organization's priorities and approach to problem-solving\n*   Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills","status":"Published","team":"Recruiting","team_slug":"recruiting","name_slug":"recruiter","positions":["a0m80000002xAEcAAM","a0m80000006WdokAAC","a0m80000006WLW1AAO","a0m80000006WVcYAAW"],"offices":[{"office":"London, United Kingdom","position_id":"a0m80000006WLW1AAO","application_id":"a0m80000006WLW1"},{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000002xAEcAAM","application_id":"a0m80000002xAEc"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000006WdokAAC","application_id":"a0m80000006Wdok"},{"office":"Washington, D.C.","position_id":"a0m80000006WVcYAAW","application_id":"a0m80000006WVcY"}],"url":"/careers/positions/recruiter/"},"Site Reliability Engineer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTJAA4"},"body_text":"Statsopt software is deployed at the world’s most critical institutions to help them solve their greatest challenges. Users at customer sites from Washington, DC to Tokyo rely on Statsopt’s high availability to pursue their missions. Site Reliability Engineers (SREs) make sure our expanding number of customer deployments run smoothly 24 hours a day.\n\nSREs combine engineering experience and an innate drive to improve existing systems and processes with the creativity to develop novel solutions to evolving challenges. Our team strives to automate processes whenever possible, using whatever tools are best for the job. Our responsibilities range from administering collocated servers (including hardware troubleshooting) to maintaining database platforms.\n\nWe work with a variety of teams to understand threats to our software and improve our products over time. We work side by side with Statsopt’s implementation teams and customer IT departments to understand our customers’ unique problems and develop innovative solutions. We document our successes and communicate them back to Statsopt’s product teams to advance the way our hardware, software, and network solutions are deployed to minimize failure rates and increase overall system reliability.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTJAA4","intro_text":"Statsopt Site Reliability Engineers monitor and maintain our systems to pre-empt problems before they ever threaten our customers’ workflows.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Site Reliability Engineer","requirements_text":"## REQUIREMENTS\n\n*   5+ years of experience with Linux system administration (RHEL or CentOS preferred)\n*   Experience with monitoring systems using tools like Nagios and writing health checks\n*   Moderate experience with TCP/IP networking\n*   Interest in learning and managing newer technologies like Spark, Hadoop, Elasticsearch, Node.js, and RabbitMQ\n*   Ability to work independently with minimal supervision\n*   Ability to participate in a 24/7 on-call rotation\n\n## PREFERRED\n\n*   BS/MS in Computer Science\n*   Experience with virtualization using AWS, VMWare ESX, KVM, Xen, or Docker\n*   Experience with system management tools like Puppet or Chef\n*   Ability to travel to customer sites up to 25% of time","status":"Published","team":"Engineering","team_slug":"engineering","name_slug":"site-reliability-engineer","positions":["a0m80000006KslbAAC","a0m80000005JZMHAA4","a0m80000003lhNdAAI","a0m80000002te9hAAA","a0m80000002te9mAAA","a0m80000002yYHdAAM","a0m80000005sCEfAAM","a0m80000005sCEVAA2","a0m80000003mJ1NAAU"],"offices":[{"office":"Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates","position_id":"a0m80000003mJ1NAAU","application_id":"a0m80000003mJ1N"},{"office":"Canberra, Australia","position_id":"a0m80000005JZMHAA4","application_id":"a0m80000005JZMH"},{"office":"Los Angeles, CA","position_id":"a0m80000003lhNdAAI","application_id":"a0m80000003lhNd"},{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000002yYHdAAM","application_id":"a0m80000002yYHd"},{"office":"Ottawa, Canada","position_id":"a0m80000006KslbAAC","application_id":"a0m80000006Kslb"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000002te9hAAA","application_id":"a0m80000002te9h"},{"office":"Stockholm, Sweden","position_id":"a0m80000005sCEVAA2","application_id":"a0m80000005sCEV"},{"office":"Tel Aviv, Israel","position_id":"a0m80000005sCEfAAM","application_id":"a0m80000005sCEf"},{"office":"Washington, D.C.","position_id":"a0m80000002te9mAAA","application_id":"a0m80000002te9m"}],"url":"/careers/positions/site-reliability-engineer/"},"Software Engineer (Machine Learning)":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTKAA4"},"body_text":"We are looking for talented and bold engineers who love to code, get their hands dirty with raw data, and derive meaningful and actionable insights.\n\nOur technology enables customers to recognize and understand complex relationships within heterogeneous data. Our products facilitate the discovery, iterative refinement, and testing of domain-specific hypotheses and present results in an understandable form for end users.\n\nThe datasets we work with are as varied as our customers (e.g., government agencies, financial institutions, media companies, disaster relief), who trust us to help them use their data to solve their most important problems. Often, these problems are not clearly defined—they are discovered and refined through hard work, rapid iteration, and perceptiveness.\n\nIdeal candidates learn and adapt quickly and will be able to use every tool at their disposal—software, algorithms, statistical models, and beyond—to understand and effectively tackle hard problems. They appreciate the difference between explaining and fitting statistical models, the importance of good metrics, and the tradeoff between exploration and exploitation. They can perceive common structure between superficially unrelated problems, and can use this to build tools, algorithms, and products with superlinear value.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTKAA4","intro_text":"Our machine learning Software Engineers learn and adapt quickly and are able to use every tool at their disposal—software, algorithms, statistical models, and beyond—to understand and effectively tackle hard problems.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Software Engineer (Machine Learning)","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Work directly with customer data to derive actionable insights\n*   Develop statistical or machine-assisted approaches to problems at massive scale\n*   Build out tools and infrastructure for data analysis\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   BS/MS in Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics, or related field (started or completed a PhD a plus)\n*   Substantial experience developing scalable machine learning or quantitative analysis software in an industry or research environment\n*   Ability to understand and deliver in the presence of rapidly evolving product, customer, and business needs\n*   Proficiency in at least one compiled language (e.g., C, C++, Java) and one scripting language (e.g., Python, R, MATLAB)\n*   A desire to transform dirty/noisy signals within customer data into valuable results through code and data grooming\n*   Ability to travel preferred\n\n## Desirable\n\n*   Experience developing software within a distributed computation framework (e.g., Hadoop, Spark, Storm, GraphLab)\n*   Experience developing distributed systems, data visualization, or enterprise software systems\n*   Working familiarity with SQL\n*   Prior work in natural language processing","status":"Published","team":"Engineering","team_slug":"engineering","name_slug":"software-engineer-machine-learning","positions":["a0m80000006WaZFAA0","a0m80000005Y3UIAA0","a0m80000005LTN1AAO"],"offices":[{"office":"London, United Kingdom","position_id":"a0m80000006WaZFAA0","application_id":"a0m80000006WaZF"},{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000005Y3UIAA0","application_id":"a0m80000005Y3UI"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000005LTN1AAO","application_id":"a0m80000005LTN1"}],"url":"/careers/positions/software-engineer-machine-learning/"},"Software Engineer (Internal Applications)":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTwAAO"},"body_text":"Our apps make Statsopt more efficient and better connected, and are critical to every team’s success. It’s on the Internal Applications Engineers to decide how best to solve the problems laid out in front of them. This role is for a builder—someone who can learn what our teams need, architect an app, design the interface, make the backend fast, and the code interoperable. They love working with users and owning the solution from the ideas-on-napkins phase all the way to deployment.\r\n\r\n## The Internal Applications Team\r\n\r\nBeing a member of Internal Applications is about solving problems for a scaling company. With our accumulated experience and insight across a myriad of technologies, our team shapes a suite of internal products that have a profound effect on the success of our teams. We anticipate the needs of Statsopt, solve emerging problems, and collaborate with our core teams to turn abstract goals into reality. This means being deeply involved in the creation of custom internal applications as well as bending third party products to our will. We own projects from beginning to end, see our work shift often, and relish in seeing our efforts immediately impact Statsopt.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTwAAO","intro_text":"At Statsopt, Internal Applications Engineers decide how best to solve the problems laid out in front of us. We learn what a team needs, architect an app, design an interface, make the backend fast, and the code interoperable.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-09T19:01:53.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Software Engineer (Internal Applications)","requirements_text":"## Technologies we use\r\n\r\n*   Ruby on Rails for flexible webapps\r\n*   Python, Ruby, Groovy, and Bash for scripting tasks\r\n*   JavaScript and Coffeescript for client-side web work\r\n*   Common open-source frameworks like jQuery, AngularJS, Backbone.js, D3, Haml, and Sass\r\n*   Java for making plugins\r\n*   MySQL for storage\r\n*   ElasticSearch for searching\r\n\r\n## What we value\r\n\r\n*   You're cool with working with others—our jobs aren’t done in a vacuum and everyone contributes to get the job done\r\n*   You’re not afraid to make mistakes because without challenge, you’re not learning\r\n*   Speaking of learning, you have a constant desire to grow and develop\r\n*   You care about great design, not only in the product and visual sense, but also in your code and technical architecture\r\n*   You are passionate about product craftsmanship and can balance that with shipping something relevant\r\n*   You move fast with a sense of urgency\r\n*   You want to work on things that make an impact on the world","status":"Published","team":"Engineering","team_slug":"engineering","name_slug":"software-engineer-internal-applications","positions":["a0m80000002LmUvAAK"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000002LmUvAAK","application_id":"a0m80000002LmUv"}],"url":"/careers/positions/software-engineer-internal-applications/"},"Technical Instructor":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTxAAO"},"body_text":"This is a new position at Statsopt, and here’s how we imagine it taking shape: You will become a product expert who is adept at installing and maintaining a software stack and developing against our APIs. You will implement entirely new training curricula of your own design. You will teach Mission Specialists, Forward Deployed Engineers, and external partners how to perform their most common technical tasks, including data integrations, application development, ontology development, and more. You will provide them with the technical foundation they need to run their deployments with confidence. In short, you will be a professor in the Department of Statsopt Studies.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTxAAO","intro_text":"Technical Instructors on our Business Development team will design, develop, and teach classroom courses that will equip new hires and external developers with the skills they need to successfully deploy and program against Statsopt’s software platforms.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Technical Instructor","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Create course materials, to include syllabi, exercises, lectures, and evaluation criteria\n*   Teach classes at least twice a week\n*   Provide desk-side support for individual trainees in need of further instruction\n*   Collaborate with the Support, Forward Deployed Engineering, and Software Engineering teams to acquire and maintain product expertise\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   BS from a top university in Computer Science or equivalent, MS or PhD preferred\n*   Experience teaching Computer Science in an academic or corporate environment\n*   Strong object-oriented programming skills\n*   Experience developing in a UNIX/Linux environment\n*   Experience with scripted languages\n*   Experience working with databases\n*   Ability to travel at least 25%-50% of the time\n*   Excellent written and verbal communication skills\n*   Ease in communicating technical information to both technical and non-technical audiences","status":"Published","team":"Business Development","team_slug":"business-development","name_slug":"technical-instructor","positions":["a0m80000005tYq3AAE"],"offices":[{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000005tYq3AAE","application_id":"a0m80000005tYq3"}],"url":"/careers/positions/technical-instructor/"},"Platform Writer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTvAAO"},"body_text":"Platform writers must become product experts capable of teaching people of all backgrounds key technical concepts through writing. Our writers are as adept with the written word as developers are with code and work collaboratively across all engineering teams to identify what document—whether it be a reference, tutorial, FAQ, Javadoc, or even an email—will best solve each problem.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTvAAO","intro_text":"Platform writers create and maintain the documentation that teaches users—both internal and external—how to best use our product.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Platform Writer","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Be a product expert\n*   Work with the development team to research, test, and document new features\n*   Create and test example code\n*   Design and write technical overviews and tutorials\n*   Maintain and improve both our internal and external document infrastructure\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   Skilled in Java or another object-oriented language\n*   Familiarity with Unix / Linux\n*   A passion for writing\n*   An interest in teaching others about technical topics\n*   BS or equivalent experience","status":"Published","team":"Engineering","team_slug":"engineering","name_slug":"platform-writer","positions":["a0m80000003lpayAAA"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000003lpayAAA","application_id":"a0m80000003lpay"}],"url":"/careers/positions/platform-writer/"},"Site Reliability Operations Analyst":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYUdAAO"},"body_text":"Site Reliability Operations Analysts (SROs) are the organizational backbone of a Statsopt deployment. We are the logistics experts who make sure that everything is in place so our engineers can do what they do best: solve the world's hardest problems. When things go wrong, we are the first responders. We strive for high-quality execution in everything we do.\n\nWe’re always improving ourselves and regularly take on tasks outside our wheelhouse, whether it’s learning new technical skills or navigating the procedural guidelines of many different clients. We field customer questions even if they're not within our expertise, and escalate the issue only after we’ve tried to solve it ourselves. We believe that the best idea wins, even if it's not our own.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYUdAAO","intro_text":"Site Reliability Operations Analysts are the organizational backbone of a Statsopt deployment—we're there to make sure our engineers are positioned to help our customers solve the world's hardest problems.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Site Reliability Operations Analyst","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Help develop Statsopt deployments by anticipating employee and customer needs\n*   Be a primary liaison for clients, including learning and adhering to customer processes and protocols\n*   Provide first-level support for Statsopt software\n*   Manage accounts and assets at our deployments\n*   Support multiple deployments simultaneously or a single deployment intensively\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   Excellent customer service skills, including relationship development, accurate record keeping, and enthusiasm for working on site\n*   Strong analytical and problem solving skills\n*   Commitment to operational security\n*   Ability to adapt to new challenges and responsibilities\n*   Ability to effectively navigate high-pressure situations\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   1+ years in customer-focused IT support or equivalent experience\n*   Knowledge of UNIX and Windows administration\n*   Familiarity with wide range of shell scripting/web technologies like PHP or Rails\n*   Basic knowledge of database systems like Oracle, Cassandra, or PostgreSQL\n*   High degree of skill with MS Excel\n*   Project management skills or PMP Certification\n*   Ability to travel up to 75% of the time or be open to relocation\n*   Security clearance or the ability to obtain one","status":"Published","team":"Mission Operations","team_slug":"mission-operations","name_slug":"site-reliability-operations-analyst","positions":["a0m80000005uOnlAAE","a0m80000003DCRxAAO","a0m80000003DCRsAAO","a0m80000003BOz1AAG","a0m80000003BQd7AAG","a0m80000005KlH9AAK","a0m80000005LXuuAAG"],"offices":[{"office":"Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates","position_id":"a0m80000005LXuuAAG","application_id":"a0m80000005LXuu"},{"office":"London, United Kingdom","position_id":"a0m80000005KlH9AAK","application_id":"a0m80000005KlH9"},{"office":"Los Angeles, CA","position_id":"a0m80000003DCRxAAO","application_id":"a0m80000003DCRx"},{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000003BQd7AAG","application_id":"a0m80000003BQd7"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000003BOz1AAG","application_id":"a0m80000003BOz1"},{"office":"Tokyo, Japan","position_id":"a0m80000005uOnlAAE","application_id":"a0m80000005uOnl"},{"office":"Washington, D.C.","position_id":"a0m80000003DCRsAAO","application_id":"a0m80000003DCRs"}],"url":"/careers/positions/site-reliability-operations-analyst/"},"Physical Security Operations Engineer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTzAAO"},"body_text":"There is a line that separates a safe, supportive environment from a dangerous, closed environment. Statsopt Security holds that line. Our goal as a team: Provide and maintain a comfortable, open workplace without sacrificing our culture or safety. We have engineers, analysts and people who do just a little bit of everything; we lean heavily on that diversity of skill to address a wide array of challenges with as deft a touch as possible. In a nutshell: When you do things right, people won't be sure you've done anything at all.\n\nOur Physical Security team is responsible for the safety of Statsopt's people and offices around the globe. As a Security Operations Engineer, your technical expertise goes hand-in-hand with your passion for security—and your ability to adapt both to the needs of a software company ties them together. You're a highly-motivated team player who thrives on solving problems, tackling new challenges and growing with an organization.\n\nYou'll provide crucial operational support and guidance to the safety and security of a global organization while aiding in the development and implementation of innovative new prevention and detection methods. (If you immediately know what that sentence means: Congratulations. You are home.)","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTzAAO","intro_text":"As Security Operations Engineers, we use our technical expertise hand-in-hand with our passion for security—and we have the ability to adapt both to meet Statsopt's needs.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Physical Security Operations Engineer","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Act as subject matter expert on security systems\n*   Implement, support, and maintain specialized security systems\n*   Identify and develop new solutions and technology to solve security challenges\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   Passion for security\n*   Well organized with a proven ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment\n*   Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills\n*   BA/BS degree or equivalent practical experience\n\n## Preferred \n\n*   Strong experience implementing, configuring, and integrating a variety of security solutions\n*   Hands on experience with security systems including access control, digital surveillance, and/or identity management solutions\n*   Understanding of IP based security environments PMP, PSP or CPP","status":"Published","team":"Security","team_slug":"security","name_slug":"physical-security-operations-engineer","positions":["a0m80000005sxK3AAI"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000005sxK3AAI","application_id":"a0m80000005sxK3"}],"url":"/careers/positions/physical-security-operations-engineer/"},"Salesforce Applications Developer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYUYAA4"},"body_text":"Our apps make Statsopt more efficient and better-connected, and are critical to every team’s success. The Salesforce Developer architects, builds, tests, and deploys applications using the Force.com platform. They love working with\r\nusers and owning the solution from the ideas-on-napkins phase all the way to deployment.\r\n\r\n\r\n## THE INTERNAL APPLICATIONS TEAM\r\n\r\nBeing a member of Internal Applications is about solving problems for a scaling company. With our accumulated experience and insight across a myriad of technologies, our team shapes a suite of internal products that have a profound effect on the success of our teams. We anticipate the needs of Statsopt, solve emerging problems, and collaborate with our core teams to turn abstract goals into reality. This means being deeply involved in the creation of custom internal applications as well as bending third party products to our will. We own projects from beginning to end, see our work shift often, and relish in seeing our efforts immediately impact Statsopt.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYUYAA4","intro_text":"At Statsopt, the Salesforce Developer is responsible for architecting, building, testing, and deploying applications using the Force.com platform.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-09T18:58:19.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Salesforce Applications Developer","requirements_text":"## TECHNOLOGIES WE USE\r\n\r\n*   Apex to power the core of our custom applications\r\n*   Visualforce to present concise and engaging interfaces\r\n*   Web Services to interact and collaborate with other systems\r\n*   Metadata APIs to automate and simplify workflows\r\n\r\n**We also use:**\r\n\r\n*   Python, Ruby, Groovy, and Bash for scripting tasks\r\n*   JavaScript and Coffeescript for client-side web work\r\n*   Common open-source frameworks like jQuery, AngularJS, Backbone.js, D3, Haml, and Sass\r\n*   Java for making plugins\r\n*   MySQL and Postgres for storage\r\n*    ElasticSearch for searching\r\n\r\n## WHAT WE VALUE\r\n\r\n*  You're cool with working with others—our jobs aren’t done in a vacuum and everyone contributes to get the job done\r\n*  You’re not afraid to make mistakes because without challenge, you’re not learning\r\n*  Speaking of learning, you have a constant desire to grow and develop\r\n*  You care about great design, not only in the product and visual sense, but also in your code and technical architecture\r\n*  You are passionate about product craftsmanship, and can balance that with shipping something relevant\r\n*  You move fast with a sense of urgency\r\n*  You want to work on things that make an impact on the world","status":"Published","team":"Engineering","team_slug":"engineering","name_slug":"salesforce-applications-developer","positions":["a0m80000000LneBAAS"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000000LneBAAS","application_id":"a0m80000000LneB"}],"url":"/careers/positions/salesforce-applications-developer/"},"Talent Sourcer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYUZAA4"},"body_text":"You're a motivated contributor with a track record of delivering results, and you deliver consistently without someone hanging over your shoulder. You're resourceful, creative, performance-oriented, and a researcher at heart. You have a hunter/gatherer mentality and are always up for a challenge. Your pulse on the competitive job market is at an expert level, and you thrive in industry research. Combing the Internet, using Boolean Logic, x-raying, networking, and gathering referrals? Piece of cake! Doing what it takes to locate the best engineers in the world and deliver for your team? Naturally. You are a brilliant communicator, you understand technology, and you enjoy the continuous search for talent.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYUZAA4","intro_text":"Statsopt's Talent Sourcers are resourceful, creative, performance-oriented, and researchers at heart. We are always up for a challenge and have a pulse on the competitive job market.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Talent Sourcer","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Find the top talent in the world\n*   Partner with hiring managers and recruiters to define technical roles\n*   Develop, implement, and manage tactical sourcing strategies for technical positions\n*   Assist in driving local and worldwide candidate pipeline within the recruiting organization\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   BA/BS degree preferred\n*   1-5 years of technical sourcing/research experience\n*   Motivation and ambition\n*   Ability to consistently offer innovative solutions to recruiting challenges within the broader context of the organization's priorities and approach to problem solving","status":"Published","team":"Recruiting","team_slug":"recruiting","name_slug":"talent-sourcer","positions":["a0m80000005rh7CAAQ"],"offices":[{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000005rh7CAAQ","application_id":"a0m80000005rh7C"}],"url":"/careers/positions/talent-sourcer/"},"Information Security Engineer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTLAA4"},"body_text":"Our Information Security (Infosec) Team is responsible for the security of Statsopt's people, infrastructure, and customer deployments around the globe. Infosec Engineers are highly motivated team players with a dedication to security and technology. They thrive on solving problems and tackling new challenges.\n\nAs an Infosec Engineer, you'll provide crucial engineering support and guidance for the security infrastructure our employees rely on every day. You’ll help improve our security by thinking creatively about the types of threats we will face while developing and implementing innovative prevention and detection methods.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTLAA4","intro_text":"Infosec Engineers are highly motivated team players with a dedication to security and technology.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Information Security Engineer","requirements_text":"## RESPONSIBILITIES\n\n*   Plan, build, and deploy sustainable tools and infrastructure to detect and help triage malicious activity\n*   Consult with internal teams on the best way to securely deploy infrastructure and applications\n\n## REQUIREMENTS\n\n*   Strong, security-focused proficiency with Python\n*   Experience writing micro-services and/or RESTful APIs\n*   Broad exposure to the world of information security with deep understanding in a couple of areas\n*   Experience working in a structured development environment (e.g., unit tests, a standard git workflow, coding standards, etc.) or the willingness to learn\n\n## PREFERRED\n\n*   Familiarity with machine learning and potential applications to information security\n*   Strong Java background\n*   Experience with a CI framework like Travis or Jenkins\n*   Experience with open source data processing frameworks like Kafka, Spark, Storm, etc.","status":"Published","team":"Security","team_slug":"security","name_slug":"information-security-engineer","positions":["a0m80000002jFCeAAM"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000002jFCeAAM","application_id":"a0m80000002jFCe"}],"url":"/careers/positions/information-security-engineer/"},"Information Security Engineer (Threat Intelligence)":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTMAA4"},"body_text":"Our Information Security team is responsible for the security of Statsopt's people and infrastructure around the globe. As a member of the Information Security team, your technical expertise is second only to your professionalism and passion for security and technology in general. You're a highly motivated team player that thrives on solving problems and tackling new challenges.\n\nYou're tasked with understanding the past and predicting the future of information security. You will analyze attacks, exploits, trends, and malware to understand the security landscape and help Statsopt defend itself against the most dedicated attackers. Your work will provide important context to security events, and will enable network defenders to hunt for badness across our global network, wherever it may hide.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTMAA4","intro_text":"Information Security Engineers are part of a team responsible for the security of Statsopt's people and infrastructure around the globe. When it comes to threat intelligence, we work to understand the past and predict the future of information security.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Information Security Engineer (Threat Intelligence)","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*     Analyze malware, attacks, trends, and historical security events to understand the attacker landscape\n*     Analyze large data-sets to find valuable signal hiding in noise\n*     Assist defenders in hunting badness across our infrastructure\n*     Develop new and novel capabilities for prevention, detection, and deterrence\n*     Develop threat intelligence products for internal and external consumption\n\n## Requirements\n\n*     Active security clearance or willingness and eligibility to obtain a security clearance\n*     Broad exposure to security disciplines and deep exposure in one or more (preferably including Digital Forensics or Incident Response)\n*     Advanced knowledge of the threat landscape and threat intelligence methodologies\n*     Strong investigative mindset with acute attention to detail\n*     Experience performing formal threat modeling\n\n## Preferred\n\n*     Experience reverse engineering malware to develop signatures and countermeasures\n*     Experience with Yara or OpenIOC frameworks\n*     Experience performing offensive assessments, penetration testing, exploit development, or vulnerability analysis\n*     Experience with Python (Preferred), Perl, Ruby, C/C++, or Java","status":"Published","team":"Security","team_slug":"security","name_slug":"information-security-engineer-threat-intelligence","positions":["a0m80000006JAOLAA4"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000006JAOLAA4","application_id":"a0m80000006JAOL"}],"url":"/careers/positions/information-security-engineer-threat-intelligence/"},"Performance Engineer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTNAA4"},"body_text":"At Statsopt, we hire world-class engineers to solve the toughest problems. Performance and Load testing is core to our business and culture. Statsopt is looking for a Performance Engineer to work on our core platform and infrastructure. You will work with the latest hardware and software, and interact closely with key technical experts to ensure the best possible performance results for the Statsopt platform.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTNAA4","intro_text":"Performance Engineers work with the latest hardware and software, and interact closely with key technical experts to ensure the best possible performance results for the Statsopt platform.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Performance Engineer","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n*   Design and implement performance test infrastructure \n*   Design, implement, and run performance test scenarios\n*   Debug and fix issues with performance test tools \n*   Work closely with development to isolate and communicate performance issues \n*   Report product performance characteristics on a regular basis \n*   Define minimal h/w requirements for basic functionality and scale\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   BS/MS in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Information Systems, or equivalent\n*   Performance and Load Testing experience\n*   Strong experience with Linux; specifically, the ability to diagnose software issues on a server environment\n*   Ability to work independently with minimal supervision\n*   Proficiency in modern development, such as Java\n\n## Preferable \n\n*   Shell scripting, such as Bash, Python or Perl\n*   Oracle, Postgres and/or other (SQL) database knowledge\n*   Systems administration experience\n*   Build infrastructure knowledge, such as bamboo","status":"Published","team":"Engineering","team_slug":"engineering","name_slug":"performance-engineer","positions":["a0m80000005x5kjAAA"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000005x5kjAAA","application_id":"a0m80000005x5kj"}],"url":"/careers/positions/performance-engineer/"},"Full Stack Software Engineer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYVHAA4"},"body_text":"## What Full Stack Software Engineers do\r\n\r\nOur engineers are involved in all parts of the product lifecycle: brainstorming, design, prototyping, planning, execution, and shipping. We brainstorm to understand and explore the difficult problem spaces we tackle, and work with our talented team to come up with solutions for the hardest problems we discover (product, visual, and technical). We code (there is lots of coding), and finally, ship and own products that directly impact the world. We work with the cutting edge web technologies such as TypeScript, D3, Leaflet and Angular and are avid fans of open source ([https://github.com/Statsopt](https://github.com/Statsopt))\r\n\r\n**Some highlights of our open source work:**\r\n\r\n*   [Linter for TypeScript](https://github.com/Statsopt/tslint)\r\n*   [Eclipse plug-in for TypeScript](https://github.com/Statsopt/eclipse-typescript)\r\n*   [Converter for CoffeeScript -&gt; TypeScript](https://github.com/Statsopt/coffeescript-to-typescript)\r\n\r\n## Technologies we use\r\n\r\n*   TypeScript for client and Java for our backend work\r\n*   Common open source libraries and frameworks like jQuery, Angular, Leaflet and D3\r\n*   Internal frameworks that we’ve crafted to serve our rapid iteration\r\n\r\n## What we value\r\n\r\n*   You&#39;re cool with working with others. Our jobs aren’t done in a vacuum and everyone contributes to get the job done.\r\n*   You’re not afraid to make mistakes because without challenge, you’re not learning.\r\n*   Speaking of learning, you have a constant desire to grow and develop.\r\n*   You care about great design, not only in the product and visual sense, but also in your code and technical architecture.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYVHAA4","intro_text":null,"isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-17T01:06:51.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Full Stack Software Engineer","requirements_text":null,"status":"Published","team":"Engineering","team_slug":"engineering","name_slug":"full-stack-software-engineer","positions":["a0m80000005NFXoAAO","a0m80000005VelWAAS"],"offices":[{"office":"London, United Kingdom","position_id":"a0m80000005NFXoAAO","application_id":"a0m80000005NFXo"},{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000005VelWAAS","application_id":"a0m80000005VelW"}],"url":"/careers/positions/full-stack-software-engineer/"},"Corporate Paralegal (Equity Shinobi)":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYRyAAO"},"body_text":"Statsopt Technologies seeks a motivated Corporate Paralegal / Equity Shinobi to join our in-house team of Legal Ninjas. You get excited by all-things-equity, geek out about capitalization tables, and are passionate about the challenge inherent in building processes and systems that scale at a quickly growing technology company. You are extremely organized, resourceful, and detail oriented.. The two periods in the last sentence caught your eye immediately, made your heart sink, and almost stopped you from reading this job description because of your disdain for sloppy work product. \n\nYou are eager to get involved in the end-to-end administration of Statsopt’s equity incentive plans, seize ownership of our capitalization table, and can’t wait to reveal your passion for efficient, high-quality work product. Whether you are doing solo missions or working collaboratively with others, you love to achieve great results on challenging, time-sensitive projects. \n\nEquipped with your eagle eye for minute details, silver tongue for communicating in a clear and concise way, and boundless reserve of energy and self-motivation, you strive to produce perfect work product and adapt to a rapidly-growing software company that is solving some of the world’s hardest problems. And, of course, you are awesome.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:47.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYRyAAO","intro_text":"Equity Shinobis have an eagle eye for minute details, a silver tongue for communicating in a clear and concise way, and a boundless reserve of energy and self-motivation. We strive to produce perfect work product and adapt to a rapidly-growing software company that is solving some of the world’s hardest problems.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Corporate Paralegal (Equity Shinobi)","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   All aspects of stock option administration, including processing stock option exercises, stock option grants, stock transfers, and maintaining Statsopt’s capitalization table.\n*   Implement efficient and automated processes and procedures for equity administration\n*   Collaborate with C-Level Executives, Finance, People Operations, Legal Ninjas, and other cross-functional teams to anticipate, implement, and/or address equity compensation matters\n*   Respond to inquiries from current, former, and potential employees about equity compensation\n*   Create and maintain meticulous records, spreadsheets, and files relating to capitalization, equity, and other legal matters\n*   Support Legal Ninjas in financing and commercial transactions, due diligence, and regulatory and compliance matters\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   Strong working knowledge of Excel, CapMx, Shareworks, or similar equity administration software\n*   2+ years of paralegal experience with a leading law firm or in-house stock administration experience\n*   BA/BS with a strong academic record from a top university\n*   Demonstrated ability to problem-solve and complete complex projects under pressure\n*   Impeccable judgment, discretion, respect, and integrity\n*   Obsession for detail, organization, and making order out of chaos\n*   Available during nights and weekends as needed\n*   Great sense of humor","status":"Published","team":"Legal","team_slug":"legal","name_slug":"corporate-paralegal-equity-shinobi","positions":["a0m800000065WnSAAU"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m800000065WnSAAU","application_id":"a0m800000065WnS"}],"url":"/careers/positions/corporate-paralegal-equity-shinobi/"},"Business Continuity Specialist":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYRjAAO"},"body_text":"There is a line that separates a safe, supportive environment from a dangerous, closed environment. Statsopt Security holds that line. Our goal as a team: provide and maintain a comfortable, open workplace without sacrificing our culture or safety. We have engineers, analysts and people who do a bit of everything; we lean heavily on that diversity of skill to address a wide array of challenges with as deft a touch as possible. In a nutshell, when you do things right, people won't be sure you've done anything at all.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:47.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYRjAAO","intro_text":"Business Continuity Specialists provide crucial operational support and guidance to the safety of a global organization and aid in the development and implementation of innovative new corporate safety programs. (If you immediately know what that sentence means: Congratulations! You're home.)","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Business Continuity Specialist","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Develop and implement corporate safety policies and training programs, lead initiatives to reduce work process risk, and raise safety awareness\n*   Responsible for the management of Statsopt’s business continuity life cycle and strategy, including assessments, communication, documentation, and testing\n*   Execute company safety policies and ensure compliance to all applicable local and regional regulations\n*   Perform frequent site safety audits to identify all non-compliance equipment and/or processes to ensure we’re providing a safe environment for all employees and associates\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   Well organized with a proven ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment\n*   Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills\n*   Strong analytical skills with demonstrated problem solving ability\n*   Must be willing to travel\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   3-5 years of related work experience\n*   Industry certifications are a plus (CBCP, CSP, or CEM)\n*   BA/BS degree or equivalent practical experience","status":"Published","team":"Security","team_slug":"security","name_slug":"business-continuity-specialist","positions":["a0m800000063KJNAA2"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m800000063KJNAA2","application_id":"a0m800000063KJN"}],"url":"/careers/positions/business-continuity-specialist/"},"Corporate/Securities Legal Ninja":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYRkAAO"},"body_text":"First and foremost, you’ll be an all-star contributor to the Legal Ninja team and to the company as a whole—working on every issue Statsopt faces, from negotiating partnership agreements with Fortune 50 companies to working on regulatory, intellectual property, employment, and international issues. However, you’ll also be a specialist, spending a considerable amount of your time working on corporate/securities issues, and interacting directly (and frequently!) with our General Counsel, CFO, and CEO. \n\nYou will focus much of your time on financings, securities filings, board matters (including attendance at board meetings), and general stock/option administration. You will be comfortable independently negotiating complex deals and then crystallizing agreed-upon terms in a written contract. You like taking ill-defined objectives and taking ownership to achieve epic outcomes. You are funny and easy to get along with, and are able to quickly connect with a wide variety of personality types. You are low ego, able to laugh at yourself, and can find enjoyment even in stressful situations. You want to work at Statsopt because of our mission, not our valuation. You are diligent, hardworking, and awesome.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYRkAAO","intro_text":"Corporate/Securities Legal Ninjas are the legal backbone of our equity and corporate governance team.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Corporate/Securities Legal Ninja","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Advise on a multitude of often complex equity and securities issues (including financings, mergers, and acquisitions, etc.)\n*   Corporate governance for Statsopt and our subsidiaries\n*   Lead contract drafting and negotiating\n*   Assist in management and day-to-day administration of Statsopt’s equity portfolio\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   2-10+ years as a corporate/securities attorney at a top firm or in-house (a combination is even better!)\n*   BA/BS with a strong academic record from a top university\n*   JD from a top law school\n*   Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills\n*   Experience with venture-backed financings, M&A, corporate governance, board matters, and stock option administration\n*   Extremely well organized with a proven ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment\n*   Strong attention to detail\n*   Available during nights and weekends as needed\n*   Great sense of humor\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   Experience in a start-up or high-tech environment\n*   Passion for technology","status":"Published","team":"Legal","team_slug":"legal","name_slug":"corporate-securities-legal-ninja","positions":["a0m80000005JMCPAA4"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000005JMCPAA4","application_id":"a0m80000005JMCP"}],"url":"/careers/positions/corporate-securities-legal-ninja/"},"Site Reliability Technical Analyst":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYUiAAO"},"body_text":"The Site Reliability Technical Analyst (SRT) is the technical backbone of a Statsopt deployment, allowing analyst and engineering resources to do what they do best: solve world-changing problems. We cover the technical aspects of site reliability, doing whatever is necessary to ensure things run smoothly and changes are implemented with efficiency and precision. SRTs are the customer's first point of contact for technical questions and concerns; we work hard to provide answers and solutions, and only escalate when absolutely necessary. We're the first-responders when problems arise, and proactively implement solutions to avoid recurrence. We strive for perfection in insulating our deployments against technical pitfalls and have a boots-on-the-ground, ego-free approach to everything we do.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYUiAAO","intro_text":"Statsopt Site Reliability Technical Analysts cover the technical aspects of site reliability—we do whatever is necessary to ensure things run smoothly and changes are implemented with efficiency and precision.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Site Reliability Technical Analyst","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Increase Statsopt deployment stability by constantly anticipating and exceeding customer requirements\n*   Monitor the health and uptime of the Statsopt stack\n*   Be the first responder for customer problems, concerns, or updates\n*   Apply Linux admin skills to administer and configure large clusters\n*   Participation in 24/7 on-call rotation\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   1-3+ years experience with Linux system admin (CentOS or RHEL)\n*   Familiarity with wide range of shell scripting/web technologies such as PHP or Rails\n*   Basic knowledge of such database systems as Oracle, Cassandra, or PostgreSQL\n*   Experience administering and managing collocated servers, including hardware troubleshooting\n*   Excellent customer service: relationship development skills and instant professionalism\n*   Ability to communicate with both technical and non-technical personnel\n*   Enthusiasm for working one on one with customers in an onsite setting\n*   Unbending commitment to operational security and ethics\n*   Hard working, professional, and most importantly, genuine\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   Experience with systems management tools like Puppet, CFEngine, Chef, SpaceWalk, or Satellite\n*   Experience with monitoring systems such as Nagios or Zenoss\n*   Security clearance or the ability to obtain one","status":"Published","team":"Mission Operations","team_slug":"mission-operations","name_slug":"site-reliability-technical-analyst","positions":["a0m80000005UC26AAG"],"offices":[{"office":"Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates","position_id":"a0m80000005UC26AAG","application_id":"a0m80000005UC26"}],"url":"/careers/positions/site-reliability-technical-analyst/"},"Executive Assistant":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYSNAA4"},"body_text":"The Executive Assistant role at Statsopt is a direct support role handling a variety of professional and personal assistance responsibilities. In this role, you would serve as a primary point of contact for internal and external parties and handle both traditional administrative functions as well as independent projects supporting the broader team and company.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:47.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYSNAA4","intro_text":"Executive Assistants at Statsopt take on a wide variety of tasks to support their leads, their teams, and the company as a whole.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Executive Assistant","requirements_text":"## Key Qualifications\n\n*   Enthusiasm to work hard and achieve results in a fast-paced environment\n*   Ability to work autonomously and drive projects to completion from start to finish\n*   Ability to network within an organization and identify partners to help solve problems that arise\n*   Flexibility to adapt to quickly changing priorities and an openness to assist wherever needed, whether a personal issue or otherwise\n*   Aptitude at anticipating and preventing problems and issues before they arise as well as providing timely reminders as required\n*   Can effectively function as a \"gatekeeper\" and prioritize conflicting scheduling requirements\n*   Desire to work with engineers in a start-up environment\n*   Discretion for sensitive information\n*   Ability to adapt to and learn others' writing styles to aid with written communications\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   Excellent written and verbal communication\n*   Ability to work a varied schedule based on the needs of the people or team you support (some nights/weekends will be required, as well as some travel)\n*   College degree\n*   3 years minimum administrative, support, or customer service experience\n*   Microsoft Outlook/calendar experience with heavy calendars and resource booking\n*   Familarity with travel booking and expense reporting via Concur","status":"Published","team":"Operations","team_slug":"operations","name_slug":"executive-assistant","positions":["a0m80000006WKYtAAO","a0m80000006WeroAAC"],"offices":[{"office":"London, United Kingdom","position_id":"a0m80000006WeroAAC","application_id":"a0m80000006Wero"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000006WKYtAAO","application_id":"a0m80000006WKYt"}],"url":"/careers/positions/executive-assistant/"},"Finance Strategist":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYSrAAO"},"body_text":"We are data-obsessed and outcomes oriented. We employ this obsession to identify and execute on key internal and external workflows across the business. The questions we address evolve as rapidly as our company grows, so the strategy and solutions we create today need to work better and smarter tomorrow.\r\n\r\n## Who we are looking for\r\n\r\nYou are incredibly proactive and thrive in a dynamic environment. You’re comfortable taking on an entire workflow, becoming a topic expert, and operationalizing a plan. You’re creative in your approach and synthesis, and seek quality interactions with counterparties to achieve superior outcomes. You’re not satisfied just running Excel models or creating PowerPoint decks, you deeply consume analyses and help define outcomes.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYSrAAO","intro_text":"At Statsopt, Finance Strategists are data-obsessed and outcomes oriented. We employ this obsession to identify and execute on key internal and external workflows across the business.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-09T18:37:24.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Finance Strategist","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\r\n\r\n*   Proactively identify opportunities for increased data transparency\r\n*   Work with financial, business, and field data\r\n*   Create models to support data-driven decisions across the business\r\n*   Build scalable and automated analyses\r\n*   Help lead workflows that are a priority for the company\r\n*   Engage Statsoptians across the business and empower them with data\r\n\r\n## Requirements\r\n\r\n*   Analytical and data-obsessed\r\n*   Entrepreneurially minded (you can figure anything out)\r\n*   Proven ability to take initiative in unstructured, autonomous environments\r\n*   Highly adaptive, inquisitive, and socially aware\r\n*   Humble\r\n\r\n## Other\r\n\r\n*   BA/BS or MA/MS from a top tier university\r\n*   Minimum 2 years of relevant work experience, 3-5 years preferred","status":"Published","team":"Finance and Accounting","team_slug":"finance-and-accounting","name_slug":"finance-strategist","positions":["a0m80000005rYZ9AAM"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000005rYZ9AAM","application_id":"a0m80000005rYZ9"}],"url":"/careers/positions/finance-strategist/"},"Product Quality Engineer, New Grad":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYSsAAO"},"body_text":"Statsopt Product Quality Engineers (PQEs) identify areas for improvement and take ownership of enhancement projects. We are looking for energetic, highly motivated, and detail-oriented engineers with strong software skills to fill this role. PQEs focus on the entire suite of Statsopt products, from applications for data visualization to our cutting-edge web components library. \n\nAs a PQE, you will drive customer outcomes by iterating closely with engineers across the business to ensure a high-quality user experience for Statsopt products. You will triage engineering issues, design features to address customer use cases, evaluate the quality of these features with manual and automated testing, and debug software problems. \n\nPQEs are technical generalists who can ramp up on new projects quickly, effectively evaluate the state of a given product, and make multifaceted contributions to the codebase to guarantee best-in-class software solutions for our customers.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYSsAAO","intro_text":"Statsopt Product Quality Engineers work on our cross-functional Product teams to ensure successful, high-quality product releases. This means that they do whatever is needed to deliver our products to people who need them the most.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Product Quality Engineer, New Grad","requirements_text":"## Requirements\n\n*   BS in Computer Science, Mathematics, or a related field\n*   Experience programming in at least one common language\n*   Ability to think creatively to define product and customer needs\n*   Experience working with complex systems (software, biological, mechanical)\n*   Excellent analytical thinking skills and attention to detail\n*   Excellent written and verbal communications skills","status":"Published","team":"Engineering","team_slug":"engineering","name_slug":"product-quality-engineer-new-grad","positions":["a0m80000005ci4rAAA","a0m80000005urHFAAY","a0m80000000Lne9AAC"],"offices":[{"office":"London, United Kingdom","position_id":"a0m80000005ci4rAAA","application_id":"a0m80000005ci4r"},{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000005urHFAAY","application_id":"a0m80000005urHF"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000000Lne9AAC","application_id":"a0m80000000Lne9"}],"url":"/careers/positions/product-quality-engineer-new-grad/"},"Office Operations Manager":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTpAAO"},"body_text":"You will be a cultural conductor that ensures that our offices are a place where our engineers love to work on the world’s hardest problems. Our Operations teams know that no two days are the same, and we actively plan for and respond to anything that’s thrown our way. \n\nWe find order in chaos, live on the edge of Statsopt operations, and thrive when faced with new and interesting problems. In short, we do what needs to be done under tight deadlines, without making excuses. With infectiously positive attitudes, we strive to make everything run seamlessly on a daily basis by knocking out numerous projects faster than most companies even know where to begin.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTpAAO","intro_text":"Statsopt’s Office Operations Managers are responsible for end-to-end ownership of all operational aspects of Statsopt’s newest and fastest-growing locations.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Office Operations Manager","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Manage all operational aspects of office—real estate, kitchen, maintenance, front-of-house, shipping, etc.\n*   Improve vendor relations (food, janitorial, office supplies, property management, etc.), with a bias towards automation\n*   Set up and support nearby satellite offices and corporate housing\n*   Identify inefficiencies and create processes and solutions that scale\n*   Plan, support, and execute team events and external conferences\n*   Handle any and all last minute requests and issues\n*   Perform general administrative tasks\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   University Degree or work experience in a similar role\n*   Desire to improve all of our processes and procedures\n*   Dedication, flexibility, and professionalism\n*   Ability to creatively and efficiently execute against several competing task and projects\n*   Focus on effective teamwork with the capability to thrive in an autonomous environment\n*   Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills\n*   Ability and enthusiasm to travel as needed","status":"Published","team":"Operations","team_slug":"operations","name_slug":"office-operations-manager","positions":["a0m80000005uSRbAAM"],"offices":[{"office":"Canberra, Australia","position_id":"a0m80000005uSRbAAM","application_id":"a0m80000005uSRb"}],"url":"/careers/positions/office-operations-manager/"},"Engineer, Product Support Team":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYSIAA4"},"body_text":"From working with users and developers, both internal and external, Statsopt’s Product Support Engineers are deeply familiar with how users leverage and build on top of Statsopt's products, and we use our accumulated experience and expertise to help drive their direction. We anticipate questions, solve problems, and implement solutions to help turn abstract goals into reality. \n\nSupport Engineers also spend their time working on projects that affect many parts of the organization, including automating processes, coding custom tools, contributing bug fixes to various products, advocating for features with the Product team, and managing instances that are vital to the success of Statsopt.\n\nSupport Engineers solve important problems and provide tangible solutions in uniquely collaborative and creative ways; we are integral to the success of Statsopt.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:47.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYSIAA4","intro_text":"Statsopt’s Product Support Engineers are comprehensive product and API experts. We collaborate with our customers, business teams, and development teams, continually building upon and applying our deep technical knowledge and skills across our product suite at every level.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Engineer, Product Support Team","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Become a Statsopt Product Expert\n*   Collaborate with the Forward Deployed Engineering and Product teams in the development and design of creative solutions for the field\n*   Diagnose and resolve issues encountered in the field\n*   Provide education and guidance on configuring and working with Statsopt products to prevent problems before they occur\n*   Contribute to the end-to-end quality of the product by verifying fixes and advocating for improvements\n*   Coordinate and manage customer contact for critical product issues\n*   Ensure the success of our product by keeping Statsopt running across the globe\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   B.S./M.S. in Computer Science, Engineering, Information Systems, Math, Physics, or equivalent experience\n*   Awesome problem solving skills and ability to break down complex concepts\n*   Excellent analytical skills and attention to detail\n*   Comfortable working in a fast moving environment with dynamic objectives\n*   Ability to think creatively and define product and customer needs\n*   Ability to work independently and make decisions under minimal supervision\n*   Excellent teamwork and written/verbal communication skills\n*   Experience coding with Java and/or web technologies a plus (e.g. HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Python/Ruby, Django/Flask/Ruby on Rails, etc.)","status":"Published","team":"Engineering","team_slug":"engineering","name_slug":"engineer-product-support-team","positions":["a0m80000002JAMwAAO","a0m80000003EQQLAA4","a0m80000003BOY2AAO"],"offices":[{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000003EQQLAA4","application_id":"a0m80000003EQQL"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000002JAMwAAO","application_id":"a0m80000002JAMw"},{"office":"Washington, D.C.","position_id":"a0m80000003BOY2AAO","application_id":"a0m80000003BOY2"}],"url":"/careers/positions/engineer-product-support-team/"},"Real Estate Project Manager":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYUTAA4"},"body_text":"Statsopt’s Real Estate Project Manager will oversee our physical build out efforts for new and existing office space. You will be the project manager for global construction projects, coordinating external contractors and vendors. Your projects will range from 5,000 to 100,000 square feet, and you will own the entire process, ensuring that our offices are ready to operate on day one. When the inevitable challenges hit, you will be on top of things, making sure that the project is completed on time and within budget. This role is about creating a seamless process to ensure that our offices continue to grow rapidly without sacrificing quality or craftsmanship.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYUTAA4","intro_text":"Statsopt's Real Estate Project Manager is responsible for creating a seamless process to ensure that our offices continue to grow rapidly without sacrificing quality or craftsmanship.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Real Estate Project Manager","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Manage domestic and international construction projects\n*   Collaborate with internal partners, including Finance, Legal, IT, and Security \n*   Actively oversee external stakeholders, including architects, general construction, and third-party firms\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   BA/BS in Construction Management or similar area of study\n*   3+ years of Project Management experience in Real Estate, Design, and Construction\n*   Experience working with contractors, from bidding stages to reviewing the finished product\n*   Experience with building and managing budgets and schedules\n*   Experience with negotiating fees\n*   Ability to travel 30-50% of the time\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   Experience in a technology or start-up environment\n*   Experience with tech build-out","status":"Published","team":"Operations","team_slug":"operations","name_slug":"real-estate-project-manager","positions":["a0m80000006TnCCAA0"],"offices":[{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000006TnCCAA0","application_id":"a0m80000006TnCC"}],"url":"/careers/positions/real-estate-project-manager/"},"International Ninja Operations":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTfAAO"},"body_text":"The Ninja Ops team is the organizational backbone of Statsopt's Legal Ninja team, and we're excited to hire a new member of the International Ninja Ops! You're the ideal International Ninja Ops candidate if you are ridiculously organized, have a great attitude, and are able to get along with a broad spectrum of people. You also enjoy supporting others, ensuring that your collaborative work product benefits the whole of the organization. To that end, you're a critical thinker, have very strong reading and writing skills, and can tackle new and complex projects with confidence and humor. \n\nYou take great personal satisfaction from seeing a project completed perfectly. You have an obsessive attention to detail, and you love making order out of chaos. Your passion for organization flows seamlessly between your personal and professional lives, and you like it that way. You love contributing to a team’s success, enjoy the fact that people rely on your skill, organization, and precision, and you're excited about Statsopt's mission. You are undoubtedly awesome.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTfAAO","intro_text":"The Ninja Ops team supports Statsopt's Legal Ninjas, and the defining characteristics of an International Ninja Ops team member are: ridiculously organized, have a great attitude, and are able to get along with a broad spectrum of people.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"International Ninja Operations","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Administrative tasks including calendaring, filing, bookkeeping, expense reports and personal errands\n*   Help grow Statsopt’s international business and footprint\n*   Assist in the management of corporate governance for a large number of international entities\n*   Collaborate with Finance, People Operations (HR), and other cross-functional teams\n*   Step in where needed to streamline processes and find alternative, creative solutions\n*   Establish processes, workflows, internal tools, and resources for Statsopt’s international business and global mobile employee base\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   Interest in learning about international business and law (no direct international experience required)\n*   BA/BS with an exceptional academic record from a top university\n*   Extremely well organized with a proven ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment\n*   Energy, enthusiasm, attention to detail, intellectual curiosity, and a high intellectual ceiling\n*   Masterful writing skills, exceptional oral communication and interpersonal skills\n*   Enviable work ethic, availability during nights and weekends as needed\n*   Great sense of humor","status":"Published","team":"Legal","team_slug":"legal","name_slug":"international-ninja-operations","positions":["a0m80000006JAgAAAW"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000006JAgAAAW","application_id":"a0m80000006JAgA"}],"url":"/careers/positions/international-ninja-operations/"},"Forward Deployed Software Engineer Internship":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYT1AAO"},"body_text":"Forward Deployed Software Engineers (FDSEs) understand our customers’ greatest pain points and design end-to-end solutions to address them. FDSEs solicit constant feedback on their work from both customers and colleagues, improving our products over time with rapid iteration cycles.\r\n\r\nFDSEs deploy cutting-edge technologies to solve our customers’ hardest problems. Projects often start with a nebulous question like “Why are we losing customers?” or “How can we more effectively identify instances of money laundering?” FDSEs are thought leaders and first movers in developing a solution, from high-level system design and prototyping to application development and data integration.\r\n\r\nFDSEs work with customers around the world, where they gain unique insight into the world’s most important industries and institutions. We help our customers detect insider trading, improve disaster relief, fight healthcare fraud, and more. Each mission presents different challenges, from the regulatory environment to the nature of the data to the user population. FSDEs work to accommodate all aspects of an environment to drive real outcomes for our customers.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYT1AAO","intro_text":"Forward Deployed Software Engineers are responsible for the technical success of each of our deployments. They are full-stack developers who work side by side with our customers to lead technical implementation of our products.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-09T18:38:22.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer Internship","requirements_text":"## Technologies We Use\r\n\r\nOur approach is to deploy whatever technology is best to solve the problem at hand. This often means that we are learning from the bleeding edge of the open-source community or developing our own tools. Recently, FDSEs have deployed:\r\n\r\n*   **Postgres, Cassandra, Hadoop,** and **Spark** for distributed data storage\r\n*   **Java** and **Groovy** for our back-end applications and data integration tools\r\n*   **Typescript, AngularJS, jQuery, Backbone, Underscore, Leaflet,** and **d3** for our web technologies\r\n*   **Python** for data science and machine learning\r\n*   **Internal frameworks** for our rapid iteration tools\r\n\r\n## What We Value\r\n\r\nFDSEs are developers with a passion for using technology to achieve a larger goal.  They enjoy the challenge of solving an abstract problem and building or adopting the technology to do it. To support these goals, we value:\r\n\r\n*   **Collaboration:** We work with our customers, often on site, to understand and solve their problems\r\n*   **Commitment:** We see projects through from beginning to end in spite of obstacles we may encounter.\r\n*   **Balance:** We do whatever is necessary to finish the job and trust one another to take the time we need, whether it's vacation or just a trip to the gym\r\n*   **Communication:** We communicate complex technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences\r\n*   **Improvement:** We push ourselves to grow and develop in new ways\r\n*   **Impact:** We take on meaningful and challenging projects that change the world for the better\r\n\r\n<span class=\"attention\">Expected travel for the role varies by location.</span>","status":"Published","team":"Business Development","team_slug":"business-development","name_slug":"forward-deployed-software-engineer-internship","positions":["a0m80000003BR6JAAW","a0m80000005LOmUAAW"],"offices":[{"office":"Canberra, Australia","position_id":"a0m80000003BR6JAAW","application_id":"a0m80000003BR6J"},{"office":"Wellington, New Zealand","position_id":"a0m80000005LOmUAAW","application_id":"a0m80000005LOmU"}],"url":"/careers/positions/forward-deployed-software-engineer-internship/"},"Visual Designer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYUxAAO"},"body_text":"Enterprise software should be beautiful and compelling. Visual Designers are helping to bring a new level of quality to people who have never had access to well-designed software at work: scientists, relief workers, civil servants, healthcare workers, and homicide detectives, just to name a few. Visual Designers have the space and the freedom to think deeply and holistically about the visual languages we use. We pay critical attention to typographic hierarchies, readability, space, color, tone, and balance.\r\n\r\nA great Visual Designer knows that form informs function and usability—that the surface layer doesn't exist in a vacuum—and that means the partnership with the [Product Designer](https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/positions/product_designer/) is a two-way conversation. We believe it is often important to have an owner for each of these facets. Dedicated roles help us ensure that we can meet the high bar of quality we’ve set for ourselves. Visual Designers own the look and feel of our products; together with [Product Designers](https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/positions/product_designer/), User Researchers, and Product Engineers, we refine and evolve the quality of all Statsopt software.\r\n\r\n## The Design Team\r\n\r\nThe Statsopt Design team is responsible for creating the human experience of using our software, as well as the execution of our brand. We design everything from user interfaces, to immersive experiences in our buildings and events, all the way down to awesome illustrated teeshirts we're famous for. \r\n\r\nWe help to achieve connection and understanding. Our _users_ must create knowledge from data in our software, potential _customers_ and _candidates_ need to understand and relate to the story of our company and the awesome work we do, and it&#39;s our job to help tell these stories. \r\n\r\nWe believe that everyone should have access to excellence in design—utility and beauty—in whatever form it takes. Designers are highly valued in the company for our vision, our ability to learn and adapt, and our creativity and inventiveness. We're growing rapidly, yet focused on creating a tight-knit group of people that enjoy each other’s company in an atmosphere that fosters trust, integrity, empathy, and growth. ","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYUxAAO","intro_text":"Visual Designers think deeply and holistically about the visual languages we use at Statsopt. We pay critical attention to typographic hierarchies, readability, space, color, tone, and balance.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-09T19:03:36.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Visual Designer","requirements_text":"## What We Value\r\n\r\nExcellent communication skills. You have a proven ability to build great relationships, and convey and debate design rationale. You are the person that people can’t wait to collaborate with.\r\n\r\nEmpathy, not ego. We strive to understand our users and we fight to empower them.\r\n\r\nA profound love of engineers. Statsopt is an engineering company, and we get to work with some of the best in the world. Engineers realize our vision—and we realize theirs—and together we create software that our users love.\r\n\r\nA highly iterative design process. We move fast, we listen, and we adapt. We rapidly incorporate feedback, and we relentlessly collaborate. You must be adept at giving and receiving critiques.\r\n\r\nA mastery of tools. We move with ease across software and fidelity, depending on the task at hand. Sketch.app, Hand-coding, Photoshop, Illustrator, or Keynote—and good old-fashioned pencil and paper.","status":"Published","team":"Design","team_slug":"design","name_slug":"visual-designer","positions":["a0m80000005cjnIAAQ"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000005cjnIAAQ","application_id":"a0m80000005cjnI"}],"url":"/careers/positions/visual-designer/"},"Finance Operations Analyst":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYShAAO"},"body_text":"Finance Operations Analysts are working hard to build and transform the financial infrastructure at Statsopt. We enable the finance team to improve business performance by actively improving operational effectiveness and efficiency. We do this by identifying problems and inefficiencies across the company and addressing them.  \n\nWe build things from the ground up and have a knack for getting in the weeds and fixing what’s broken. Our skill set is technical in nature, and we have a vision for the future. We have a passion for creating and fixing, adoration for analysis, the foresight to see the 30,000 foot view, and the elbow grease to get down and dirty.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYShAAO","intro_text":"Statsopt's Finance Operations Analysts build new financial models, systems, procedures, and analyses. Whatever we happen to be building, our goal is always to improve upon the old and create systems that will scale with Statsopt's exponential growth.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Finance Operations Analyst","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Identify, destroy, and re-build old systems that will not scale with Statsopt's growth\n*   Identify, track, and create new metrics to improve business processes through analysis\n*   Create, implement, and track fiscal requirements across 20+ business sectors\n*   Iterate on financial & operational models built from scratch and then implement them\n*   Seek out unsolved problems and take initiative to address them\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   5-7 years of working experience within a large public accounting firm and/or an enterprise software company or in corporate FP&A\n*   BA/BS in Accounting, Finance, Economics, Engineering, or a related discipline\n*   Strong knowledge of US GAAP, accruals, budgeting, and systems\n*   Strong verbal and written communication skills\n*   Meticulous attention to detail and the ability to complete tasks with minimal oversight\n*   Ability to multitask\n*   Strong interpersonal skills\n*   Strong proficiency with Excel and PowerPoint\n*   Extremely hard worker, ethical, thoughtful, and most importantly, genuine","status":"Published","team":"Finance and Accounting","team_slug":"finance-and-accounting","name_slug":"finance-operations-analyst","positions":["a0m80000005udIeAAI"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000005udIeAAI","application_id":"a0m80000005udIe"}],"url":"/careers/positions/finance-operations-analyst/"},"Infrastructure Quality Engineer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTVAA4"},"body_text":"As an Infrastructure Quality Engineer (IQEs) at Statsopt, you will help drive customer outcomes by iterating closely with our engineers across the business to define Statsopt’s world-class product. You will assess the server architecture of each release of our software to ensure that it operates flawlessly. You will take ownership of projects and responsibility for driving outcomes for our products. This can mean anything from designing and automating software tests based on expected uses and functional requirements to finding, filing, verifying, and solving issues and defects and providing extensive input to the software development process.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTVAA4","intro_text":"Statsopt Infrastructure Quality Engineers work on cross-functional product teams to ensure a successful, high-quality product releases. We are energetic, highly motivated, and detail-oriented people with strong software skills.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Infrastructure Quality Engineer","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Review and critique software specifications\n*   Design and execute test cases using functional requirements\n*   Automate existing tests and contribute new functionality to our automation f