015-06-04T04:06:50.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTXAA4","intro_text":null,"isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-18T19:38:54.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Full Stack Software Engineer, New Grad","requirements_text":null,"status":"Published","team":"Engineering","team_slug":"engineering","name_slug":"full-stack-software-engineer-new-grad","positions":["a0m80000005WIhEAAW"],"offices":[{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000005WIhEAAW","application_id":"a0m80000005WIhE"}],"url":"/careers/positions/full-stack-software-engineer-new-grad/"},"Global Security Lead":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYT6AAO"},"body_text":"There is a line that separates a safe, supportive environment from a dangerous, closed environment. Statsopt Security holds that line. Our goal as a team: Provide and maintain a comfortable, open workplace without sacrificing our culture or safety. We have engineers, analysts, and people who do just a little bit of everything; we lean heavily on that diversity of skill to address a wide array of challenges with as deft a touch as possible. Understanding and complementing that diversity is the key to success.\n\nAs the Global Security Lead your passion for security and drive to keep people safe, in both mundane and exciting locales, all over the world are vital to the health of your team and the company. Your ability to adapt these skills to the needs of a cutting edge software company makes you vital to us. You have a keen eye for evaluating and managing risk while balancing your plans on how our business runs and our cultural norms. You're a highly-motivated team player that thrives on solving problems, tackling new challenges, growing an organization and guiding the people within it.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYT6AAO","intro_text":"Our Physical Security team is responsible for the safety of Statsopt's people and offices around the globe.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Global Security Lead","requirements_text":"## RESPONSIBILITIES\n\n*   Provide guidance and expertise regarding best-practice business security standards and solutions to maintain a secure environment for the protection of personnel, property and information\n*   Analyze business and global trends to determine and plan for both short-term and long-term security operation goals\n*   Provide leadership, organization and mentorship to the program leads of various security and life safety efforts: risk management, business continuity, intelligence, security systems, and operations\n*   Establish and maintain effective relationships as a liaison with Federal, State, and local law enforcement and regulatory agencies that affect security operations\n\n## REQUIREMENTS\n\n*   Passion for security\n*   Creative problem solver\n*   Well organized with a proven ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment\n*   Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills\n*   BA/BS degree or equivalent practical experience\n\n## PREFERRED\n\n*   Strong experience developing safety and security programs internationally\n*   Hands on experience leading, growing, and developing teams\n*   Ability to adapt to a fast paced and changing landscape","status":"Published","team":"Security","team_slug":"security","name_slug":"global-security-lead","positions":["a0m80000006KKzZAAW"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000006KKzZAAW","application_id":"a0m80000006KKzZ"}],"url":"/careers/positions/global-security-lead/"},"International Specialist":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYT7AAO"},"body_text":"The International Ninja team helps keep the rapidly-moving ship that is Statsopt’s international business afloat and on course, and we’re excited to hire another hand on deck to help us navigate harsh international waters and maintain our ship’s momentum! You're the ideal International Ninja candidate if you are obsessively organized, nimble and adaptive, interested in developing project management skills, have a great attitude, and are able to get along with a broad spectrum of people. You must also be a critical thinker, have strong reading and writing skills, and can tackle new and complex projects with confidence and humor. You're also the kind of person who takes pleasure in making order out of chaos.  \n\nYou love facing, and then outright owning, any and all unique challenges that are thrown your way (and in the international arena, there are many!). Your passion for organization flows seamlessly between your personal and professional lives, and you like it that way. You are the type of person who, once entrusted with a task, will do absolutely anything to accomplish your objective. You do not need detailed instructions to get something across the finish line, though you do enjoy collaborating with your peers. You love contributing to a team’s success, enjoy the fact that people rely on your skill, organization, and precision, and you're excited about Statsopt's mission. You are undoubtedly awesome.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYT7AAO","intro_text":"International Specialists are obsessively organized Ninjas; we are nimble and adaptive, interested in developing project management skills, and are able to get along with a broad spectrum of people.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"International Specialist","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Help grow Statsopt’s international business and footprint\n*   Research international law surrounding international expansion\n*   Learn to manage international corporate governance for a large number of international entities\n*   Collaborate with Finance, People Operations (HR), and other cross-functional teams\n*   Step in where needed to streamline processes and find alternative, creative solutions\n*   Establish processes, workflows, internal tools, and resources for Statsopt’s international business and global mobile employee base\n*   Impeccable bookkeeping, project status tracking, filing, calendaring, administrative work, and task management\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   Interest in learning about international business and law (no direct international experience required)\n*   BA/BS with an exceptional academic record from a top university\n*   Extremely well organized with a proven ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment\n*   Energy, enthusiasm, attention to detail, intellectual curiosity, and a high intellectual ceiling\n*   Masterful writing skills, exceptional oral communication and interpersonal skills\n*   Enviable work ethic, availability during nights and weekends as needed\n*   Great sense of humor","status":"Published","team":"Legal","team_slug":"legal","name_slug":"international-specialist","positions":["a0m80000006JAg5AAG"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000006JAg5AAG","application_id":"a0m80000006JAg5"}],"url":"/careers/positions/international-specialist/"},"Engineering Team Lead":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYSSAA4"},"body_text":"We need world-class Engineering Leads to develop our information exploration technologies and grow our engineering teams. The problem space includes everything from exploring huge information sets to presenting complex information in an easily digestible form for end-users.\n\nWe are looking for talented and passionate leads who love to code but understand the importance of helping individuals grow and who aren't intimidated by challenging problems. You should get as much enjoyment from having a member of the team make a critical breakthrough as you would if it were to be your own contribution. Moreover, you should be interested in pushing the envelope on not just the work we produce, but also the _way in which_ we produce this work—_meta_ should be your middle name.\n\nYou will be responsible for more than just people. The product will also be a core part of your duties and you will need to help the team make tradeoffs between functionality, time, and complexity. Having a keen product sense is important; being able to really get to know your audience and customers is critical. Finally, decentralized decision making must be something you encourage and foster in our culture.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYSSAA4","intro_text":"At Statsopt, Engineering Team Leads love to code but understand the importance of helping individuals grow. We aren't intimidated by challenging problems, and we take pleasure in supporting members of our teams as they make critical breakthroughs.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Engineering Team Lead","requirements_text":"## Requirements\n\n*  BS/MS in Computer Science or equivalent (started or completed PhD a plus)\n*  Previous engineering leadership responsibilities a plus, but advanced contributors are required\n*  Enthusiasm for solving interesting problems and a willingness to take on new product features\n*  Background in distributed systems, machine learning, information retrieval, data visualization, and/or developing enterprise software systems a plus\n*  Interest in working on a rapidly changing, ever-evolving system","status":"Published","team":"Engineering","team_slug":"engineering","name_slug":"engineering-team-lead","positions":["a0m80000005X4QLAA0","a0m80000003lcGcAAI"],"offices":[{"office":"London, United Kingdom","position_id":"a0m80000005X4QLAA0","application_id":"a0m80000005X4QL"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000003lcGcAAI","application_id":"a0m80000003lcGc"}],"url":"/careers/positions/engineering-team-lead/"},"Software Engineer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYSTAA4"},"body_text":"Our engineers are involved in all parts of the product lifecycle: idea generation, design, prototyping, planning, execution, and shipping. Our work starts with brainstorming to discover, explore, and understand our customer’s greatest challenges in the visual and technical spaces. Then we code. A lot. Finally, we ship and continuously iterate on products that have a direct impact on the world’s hardest problems.\r\n\r\n## OUR WORK\r\n\r\nStatsopt makes products for human-driven analysis of real-world data. These products must handle messy data at enormous scales, all while maintaining an intuitive user experience and a wide range of analytic capabilities. Our software engineers push the boundaries of what’s possible. We have:\r\n\r\n*   Built a web-based mapping interface that handles millions of data points dynamically displayed at once.\r\n*   Constructed an analysis platform on top of a columnar database and custom infrastructure that allows complex numerical analysis at the petabyte scale.\r\n*   Created AtlasDB, which provides high-scale, reliable data storage for Statsopt products. This NoSQL distributed data store adds a transactional layer that gives the whole system ACID properties.\r\n*   Developed a WYSIWYG web app for quickly creating interactive, data-driven web sites.\r\n*   And much, much more: mobile, infrastructure, search, client facing, etc.\r\n\r\nWe work with the cutting edge web technologies such as TypeScript, D3, Leaflet and Angular and are avid fans of open source (https://github.com/Statsopt).\r\n\r\nSome highlights of our open source work:\r\n\r\n*   [Linter for TypeScript](https://github.com/Statsopt/tslint)\r\n*   [Eclipse plug-in for TypeScript](https://github.com/Statsopt/eclipse-typescript)\r\n*   [Converter for CoffeeScript -> TypeScript](https://github.com/Statsopt/coffeescript-to-typescript)","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYSTAA4","intro_text":"Statsopt Software Engineers push the boundaries of what’s possible. We are involved at every stage of the product lifecycle from idea generation to shipping the product.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-09T19:01:28.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Software Engineer","requirements_text":"## TECHNOLOGIES WE USE\r\n\r\n*   Java for back-end work\r\n*   JavaScript, CoffeeScript, and TypeScript for client and server web work (link all three of these)\r\n*   Open source technologies such as Cassandra, Spark, ElasticSearch, etc.\r\n*   The latest web technologies\r\n*   Internal frameworks for our rapid iteration tools\r\n\r\n## WHAT WE LOOK FOR\r\n\r\n*   You’re a strong coder; regardless of which language you use or how you learned it, we’re looking for people who can write clean, effective code\r\n*   You enjoy collaboration with others—our work isn’t carried out in a vacuum, and everyone contributes to get the job done\r\n*   You understand that making mistakes means you’re learning\r\n*   You have a constant desire to grow and develop\r\n*   You are passionate about product craftsmanship and care about great design, not only in products and their visual presentation but in your code and technical architecture as well\r\n*   You are comfortable in a high-paced environment, and can respond to urgent requests\r\n*   You want to work on things that make an impact on the world","status":"Published","team":"Engineering","team_slug":"engineering","name_slug":"software-engineer","positions":["a0m8000000557A8AAI","a0m80000004kyQhAAI","a0m80000000LkdwAAC"],"offices":[{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m8000000557A8AAI","application_id":"a0m8000000557A8"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000000LkdwAAC","application_id":"a0m80000000Lkdw"},{"office":"Washington, D.C.","position_id":"a0m80000004kyQhAAI","application_id":"a0m80000004kyQh"}],"url":"/careers/positions/software-engineer/"},"Financial Analyst":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYSwAAO"},"body_text":"On the Financial Analytics team, the questions we ask evolve as quickly as our company grows, so what works today always needs to work better and smarter tomorrow. Our small team is full of creative self-starters, and we tackle unstructured problems every day with a lot of independence. \n\nOur roles are flexible and tailored to our superpowers; we analyze data using whatever program and method will generate the best results. Everything in our workplace is designed to let us rock a project from start to finish with no red tape to hold us back. This team resembles the rest of Statsopt, not anything you’ll find in traditional corporate finance.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYSwAAO","intro_text":"Financial Analysts at Statsopt are engineers, entrepreneurs, and finance geeks, brought together by our passion for solving complex problems, building innovative models, and supporting data-driven transparency.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Financial Analyst","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Seeking out unsolved problems and taking initiative to address them\n*   Constantly iterating on projects to ensure they will scale with Statsopt's growth\n*   Building models, dashboards, and systems from scratch\n*   Collaborating with other Statsoptians, across the company and around the globe\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   BA/BS or MA/MS in Engineering, Finance, Economics, Math, or another analytical field\n*   Entrepreneurial mindset, with proven ability to be resourceful, and experience improving and streamlining processes\n*   Strong experience with complex data modeling in at least one of the following: Excel, VBA, SQL, or MATLAB; familiarity with additional modeling platforms is always a plus\n*   Demonstrated ability and desire to learn quickly, and make an impact\n*   Ability to work independently and as a team member in an unstructured environment\n*   Flexible schedule—we still operate in start-up mode and fire drills don't always fit within traditional business hours\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   Startup experience / work in a low-structure, high-autonomy environment\n*   Experience graphically representing data\n*   Programming experience","status":"Published","team":"Finance and Accounting","team_slug":"finance-and-accounting","name_slug":"financial-analyst","positions":["a0m80000002jHYNAA2"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000002jHYNAA2","application_id":"a0m80000002jHYN"}],"url":"/careers/positions/financial-analyst/"},"Administrative Assistant":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYRPAA4"},"body_text":"Our day-to-day is a fast-paced landscape of new challenges, creative problem solving, and goal setting. Every “To Do” we complete brings us one step closer to our mission. Our positive spirit and can-do attitude transforms chaos into order, paving the way for Statsopt’s success. Our willingness to experiment with new processes helps us boldly step forward one Post-it at a time.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:47.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYRPAA4","intro_text":"Statsopt Administrative Professionals are the behind-the-scenes, multitasking powerhouses that ensure the people, teams, and projects we support run smoothly.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Administrative Assistant","requirements_text":"## Key Qualifications\n\n*   Enthusiasm to work hard and achieve results in a fast-paced environment\n*   Ability to work both autonomously and in constant collaboration with teammates, colleagues, and external contacts\n*   Determination to find the answers to open-ended questions\n*   Desire to delve into details to understand how they fit into the big picture\n*   Capacity to learn quickly and apply knowledge on the fly\n*   Flexibility to adapt to rapidly changing priorities and an openness to assist wherever needed\n*   Aptitude at anticipating and preventing problems, issues, and roadblocks before they materialize while strategizing for when things go wrong\n*   Motivation to help our teams succeed\n*   Desire to partner with the people and teams we support as we gather context and tailor solutions\n*   Desire to work with engineers in a start-up environment\n*   Discretion for sensitive information\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   Excellent written and verbal communication\n*   Ability to work a varied schedule based on the needs of the people or team you support (Note: some nights and weekends required)\n*   Some college or equivalent relevant work experience\n*   1 year minimum administrative, support, or customer service experience (more experience required for some roles)\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   Microsoft Outlook/calendar experience with heavy calendars and resource booking\n*   Familiarity with travel booking and expense reporting via Concur\n\n## Roles\n\nWe are hiring for a range of administrative roles. Through the interview process we will help you connect with the role(s) that best suit your experience, abilities, and goals. Potential roles include: Front Desk Administrator, Generalist Admin, Team Admin, and Executive Admin.","status":"Published","team":"Operations","team_slug":"operations","name_slug":"administrative-assistant","positions":["a0m80000006LUWwAAO","a0m80000006LUWmAAO","a0m80000006LUWSAA4","a0m80000006LUWXAA4"],"offices":[{"office":"London, United Kingdom","position_id":"a0m80000006LUWwAAO","application_id":"a0m80000006LUWw"},{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000006LUWXAA4","application_id":"a0m80000006LUWX"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000006LUWSAA4","application_id":"a0m80000006LUWS"},{"office":"Washington, D.C.","position_id":"a0m80000006LUWmAAO","application_id":"a0m80000006LUWm"}],"url":"/careers/positions/administrative-assistant/"},"Product Designer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYU4AAO"},"body_text":"Product Designers are generalists who span many design disciplines: user research, information architecture, prototyping, ideation, interaction design, and sometimes visual design. Our artifacts come in many different forms and fidelities. We draw a lot, and we write a lot. We prototype with paper and Sharpies, JavaScript, After Effects, and Keynote. We visit our users, listen, investigate, learn, and ideate. We rigorously share and promote our ideas and constantly incorporate feedback and critique.\r\n\r\nSometimes we’re out in front, exploring brand-new problem spaces, figuring out _what_ to build. And sometimes we’re deep in the details of micro-interactions, figuring out _how_ to build it. We lead feature teams in design exercises ranging from day-long design studios to week-long design sprints.\r\n\r\nA great Product Designer knows that form informs function and usability—that the surface layer doesn't exist in a vacuum—and that means the partnership with the [Visual Designer](https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/positions/visual_designer/) is a two-way conversation. We believe it is often important to have an owner for each of these facets. Dedicated roles help us ensure that we can meet the high bar of quality we’ve set for ourselves. Product Designers own the user experience of our products along with [Visual Designers](https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/positions/visual_designer/), User Researchers, and Product Engineers. Together, we refine and evolve the quality of all Statsopt software. \r\n\r\n<span class=\"attention\"><strong>Please note</strong>: this is not an industrial design role.</span>\r\n\r\n## The Design Team\r\n\r\nThe Statsopt Design team is responsible for creating the human experience of using our software, as well as the execution of our brand. We design everything from user interfaces, to immersive experiences in our buildings and events, all the way down to awesome illustrated teeshirts we're famous for. \r\n\r\nWe help to achieve connection and understanding. Our _users_ must create knowledge from data in our software, potential _customers_ and _candidates_ need to understand and relate to the story of our company and the awesome work we do, and it's our job to help tell these stories. \r\n\r\nWe believe that everyone should have access to excellence in design—utility and beauty—in whatever form it takes. Designers are highly valued in the company for our vision, our ability to learn and adapt, and our creativity and inventiveness. We're growing rapidly, yet focused on creating a tight-knit group of people that enjoy each other’s company in an atmosphere that fosters trust, integrity, empathy, and growth. ","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYU4AAO","intro_text":"We are generalists who span many design disciplines: user research, information architecture, prototyping, ideation, interaction design, and sometimes visual design.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-09T18:56:07.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Product Designer","requirements_text":"## What We Value\r\n\r\nExcellent communication skills. You have a proven ability to build great relationships, and convey and debate design rationale. You are the person that people can’t wait to collaborate with.\r\n\r\nEmpathy, not ego. We strive to understand our users and we fight to empower them.\r\n\r\nA profound love of engineers. Statsopt is an engineering company, and we get to work with some of the best in the world. Engineers realize our vision—and we realize theirs—and together we create software that our users love.\r\n\r\nA highly iterative design process. We move fast, we listen, and we adapt. We rapidly incorporate feedback, and we relentlessly collaborate. You must be adept at giving and receiving critiques.\r\n\r\nA mastery of tools. We move with ease across software and fidelity, depending on the task at hand. Sketch.app, hand-coding, Photoshop, Illustrator, or Keynote—and good old-fashioned pencil and paper.","status":"Published","team":"Design","team_slug":"design","name_slug":"product-designer","positions":["a0m80000000iQpMAAU","a0m80000005KmMhAAK","a0m80000005KmMmAAK","a0m80000005KmMcAAK"],"offices":[{"office":"London, United Kingdom","position_id":"a0m80000005KmMmAAK","application_id":"a0m80000005KmMm"},{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000005KmMhAAK","application_id":"a0m80000005KmMh"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000000iQpMAAU","application_id":"a0m80000000iQpM"},{"office":"Washington, D.C.","position_id":"a0m80000005KmMcAAK","application_id":"a0m80000005KmMc"}],"url":"/careers/positions/product-designer/"},"Product Designer, Internship":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYU9AAO"},"body_text":"We are generalists who span many design disciplines: user research, information