in applications and related infrastructure\n*   Build and support enterprise-worthy operations, monitoring, and configuration management tools\n*   Monitor the health and uptime of the Statsopt stack and its dependencies\n*   Be the face of technical operations for a deployment, both internally and for our clients\n*   Constantly document technical implementation and configuration, and set an example for deployment resources to follow your lead\n*   Be the first responder for customer problems, concerns, or updates\n*   Be independently responsible for a single deployment, but able to share best practices among the greater team\n*   Apply Linux admin skills to administer and configure large distributed applications and clusters\n*   Participation in 24/7 on-call rotation\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   Expert-level Linux system admin abilities (CentOS or RHEL preferred—and no GUIs!)\n*   Experience administering and managing distributed server environments, including hardware troubleshooting\n*   Intermediate knowledge of database systems including Oracle, PostgreSQL, and NoSQL technologies like Cassandra\n*   Familiarity with a wide range of scripting languages such as Bash, Python, or PHP\n*   Familiarity with Linux system security best practices\n*   Demonstrable knowledge of TCP/IP networking, routing, and firewalls\n*   Experience and interest in working in a highly-collaborative setting - sharing best practices, lessons learned, and assisting where gaps exist\n*   Interest in developing skills and tools that can be leveraged across the company\n*   Ability to manage multiple, high-priority demands from separate sources at high quality with zero loss\n*   Ability to communicate with both technical and non-technical personnel\n*   Enthusiasm for working one-on-one with customers in an onsite or remote setting\n*   Unbending commitment to operational security and ethics\n*   Hard working and professional\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   Experience with systems management tools like Puppet, CFEngine, Chef, SpaceWalk, or Satellite\n*   Experience with monitoring systems such as Nagios or Zenoss\n*   Experience with common developer and code management tools like git, Stash, Jenkins, and Eclipse\n*   Experience with virtualization platforms such as VMware ESX or RHEV\n*   Experience with cloud-based hosting platforms like AWS or Rackspace/OpenStack\n*   Deep knowledge of TCP/IP networking, routing and firewalls\n*   Security clearance or the ability to obtain one","status":"Published","team":"Engineering","team_slug":"engineering","name_slug":"linux-site-engineer","positions":["a0m80000005qIwOAAU","a0m80000006JKPxAAO","a0m80000003kov0AAA","a0m80000003DCQNAA4","a0m80000003DCQDAA4","a0m80000003DCQIAA4","a0m80000005Ie2hAAC"],"offices":[{"office":"Canberra, Australia","position_id":"a0m80000006JKPxAAO","application_id":"a0m80000006JKPx"},{"office":"London, United Kingdom","position_id":"a0m80000005Ie2hAAC","application_id":"a0m80000005Ie2h"},{"office":"Los Angeles, CA","position_id":"a0m80000003DCQNAA4","application_id":"a0m80000003DCQN"},{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000003DCQDAA4","application_id":"a0m80000003DCQD"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000003DCQIAA4","application_id":"a0m80000003DCQI"},{"office":"Singapore City, Singapore","position_id":"a0m80000005qIwOAAU","application_id":"a0m80000005qIwO"},{"office":"Washington, D.C.","position_id":"a0m80000003kov0AAA","application_id":"a0m80000003kov0"}],"url":"/careers/positions/linux-site-engineer/"},"Product Expert":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYUEAA4"},"body_text":"Product Experts at Statsopt own every layer of our deployment: working with software, wrangling data, managing relationships, and most importantly solving whatever problem is put in front of us. Our role adapts to meet the needs of the moment.  We collaborate with our engineering team on the future of the platform while relaying concrete product timelines to our customers. We are the Swiss Army knives of Statsopt deployments who manipulate data with code to impact business outcomes for our customers. We’re motivated by the scope and impact of the problems we solve; our work has a direct effect on the world and the success of Statsopt. We run with projects without needing to be managed, and we love that the success of our deployment rests on our shoulders.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYUEAA4","intro_text":"Product Experts at Statsopt are the technical wizards who empower our customers to solve their most difficult analytical problems.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Product Expert","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Conduct analysis and solve problems with customer data onsite\n*   Deliver quantitative analysis based on modeling from first-principles\n*   Translate business questions into data questions—ask: what are we doing to provide value? What are the causes and what does it mean for the business?\n*   Implement technical solutions at customer sites\n*   Build a roadmap for the future of the product in conjunction with the Engineering team\n*   Manage relationships with customer stakeholders\n*   Help build customer workflows and train users through these workflows; gather feature feedback and requirements for features under development\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   BA/BS in Engineering, Computer Science, Sciences, Statistics, or Mathematics (or equivalent work experience)\n*   Familiarity with quantitative data analysis methods\n*   Object-oriented programming skills\n*   Ease in communicating with technical and non-technical personnel\n*   Travel 50% of the time\n*   Ability to work in teams while still leading projects solo\n\nCover letter strongly preferred; please include examples of your technical aptitude, interesting projects you have managed or worked on in the past, and your analysis experience.","status":"Published","team":"Business Development","team_slug":"business-development","name_slug":"product-expert","positions":["a0m80000005daWcAAI","a0m80000006Wdk4AAC","a0m80000000gguhAAA"],"offices":[{"office":"London, United Kingdom","position_id":"a0m80000006Wdk4AAC","application_id":"a0m80000006Wdk4"},{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000000gguhAAA","application_id":"a0m80000000gguh"},{"office":"Sydney, Australia","position_id":"a0m80000005daWcAAI","application_id":"a0m80000005daWc"}],"url":"/careers/positions/product-expert/"},"Project Manager":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYRaAAO"},"body_text":"Our Information Security team is responsible for the security of Statsopt's people, data, and infrastructure around the globe. We strive to establish ourselves as thought leaders in the InfoSec community through innovative ideas and ruthless execution. As the business and organization continues to grow, the Project Manager becomes even more critical to the success of the InfoSec team.\n\nThis high-impact role requires a high level of organization to track active key projects. Through careful planning you'll help ensure that engineers are successful in meeting the objectives of their projects in a timely manner. Your technical background will enable you to understand technical hurdles that the engineering team is facing. Ultimately, your success results in the mission's success.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYRaAAO","intro_text":"The Project Manager role on the InfoSec team is fast paced and high impact—it demands a high level of organization to track active key projects.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Project Manager","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Partner closely with business and IT leads to develop a deep understanding of Statsopt's business goals, processes, and technology limitations\n*   Design and run a machine to ensure that the InfoSec engineering team achieves their quarterly objectives for the organization\n*   Drive success of high impact projects by:\n    *   Developing roadmaps with detailed milestones and potential risks. Breaking down the milestones into sprint sized efforts\n    *   Holding engineers accountable and focused on their commitments stated in their roadmaps\n    *   Unblocking engineers when necessary\n   *   Communicating with internal customers on a regular basis to manage expectations\n*   Capture signal on project progress and relevant metrics that measure impact and team efficiency; report interesting trends to leadership and use data to improve the team\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   Experience developing project roadmaps based on customer requirements\n*   Strong organization skills and attention to detail\n*   Excellent end-user/customer/stakeholder facing and communication skills\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   Technical Engineering background and strong analytical skills evidenced by an engineering or a math degree\n*   Experience in change management\n*   Experience in JIRA\n*   Excellent prior success running projects and keeping things organized and chaos at bay","status":"Published","team":"Security","team_slug":"security","name_slug":"project-manager","positions":["a0m80000006SC1dAAG"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000006SC1dAAG","application_id":"a0m80000006SC1d"}],"url":"/careers/positions/project-manager/"},"Deployment Strategist":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYS3AAO"},"body_text":"Deployment Strategists at Statsopt own the outcomes of all the work we do in Business Development. We begin with a vision: a vision of how software can transform people's relationship to data at the heart of a problem we care deeply about. We test that vision. Do our partners share it? Can we build what they need quickly enough? Will we be able to deploy it in the right environment, to the right people? Working side by side with our Forward-Deployed Software Engineers, we refine our vision, and then find our way to it: through messy data, through bureaucratic labyrinths, through sandstorms in \"data centers\" made of tents and suitcases. Whatever it takes, we figure out how to do it.\n\nA team of analysts at a customer site might want training for a tool we've built. One of our customers' CEOs might need help convincing another organization to share data. A team of developers might be asking for direction on which of a dozen feature requests they should prioritize this quarter. Or a global financial organization might be on the line, reeling from a recent compliance failure and asking us what we can do to help detect and prevent such behavior in the future. These, and a hundred other everyday scenarios, are where a Deployment Strategist thrives.\n\nThis role doesn't come neatly packaged or defined. You should expect it to change during your time at Statsopt, to evolve as our organization evolves and as you do. When we interview Deployment Strategists, we aren't looking for people with a specific background. We're looking for people with exceptional analytic ability, creative brilliance, technical aptitude, and a gift for finding the details that matter. Most of all, we're looking for people who combine a calling to leave the world better than they found it with the resourcefulness necessary to realize that calling, no matter the circumstances.\n\nIf that sounds like you, then we're interested.\n\nWe look forward to hearing from you. You can scroll down for more specific examples of roles Deployment Strategists might take on.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:47.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYS3AAO","intro_text":"Deployment Strategists at Statsopt have exceptional analytic ability, creative brilliance, technical aptitude, and a gift for finding the details that matter. We combine a calling to leave the world better than we found it with the resourcefulness necessary to realize that calling, no matter the circumstances.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Deployment Strategist","requirements_text":"## PRODUCT OWNER\n\nWe're constantly building products at Statsopt. Some products are very specific to particular customer workflows—specialized geospatial visualization tools, for example, that might exist as part of a more generic map application. Others, such as a lightweight document reader, are deployed to tens of thousands of our users. All of these products have their roots in a particular customer's needs, where a team of Deployment Strategists and Forward-Deployed Software Engineers sat down together with our core developers and started work.\n\nDeployment Strategists who gravitate towards product ownership have strong technical skills, compelling creative vision for what software can do, and an instinct for leadership. They apply those skills to leading a team that builds and supports a product: defining requirements, testing new versions, installing and configuring applications, sitting down with users and gathering feedback about what's working well and what isn't. They work across organizations and across internal teams, ensuring that we are all aligned on what we are building and why. Ultimately, they are responsible for ensuring that we deliver a product that truly transforms our customers'; ability to work with data.\n\n## PROJECT OWNER\n\nOur partnerships with our customers are at the core of what we do. Our customers trust that we are the best in the world at building and delivering enterprise software. They trust that we mean it when we say we can enable collaboration across a worldwide enterprise without sacrificing security, or that in the event of a crisis we will surge the team that supports them just as they surge their own internal team. Fundamentally, our customers—whether they&#39;re looking for a missing child, an insurgent assembling a roadside bomb, or the source of a cyber attack on their network—trust that we care as deeply about their problems as they do.\n\nDeployment Strategists who gravitate towards project ownership are the face of Statsopt, and the custodians of that trust. They pair a passion for software with excellent communication skills, an ability to navigate organizational hurdles, and an instinct for putting the right people in the right places. A project owner might spend the morning in meetings with customers to discuss the status of a data integration, the afternoon in a CTO's office talking about best practices in cyber security, and lunch in between at our headquarters brainstorming with a technical team about the best time to perform an upgrade. Ultimately, they are responsible for the strength of our partnerships: for ensuring that our customers are excited to work with us, and that we are excited to work with our customers.\n\n## PROCESS OWNER\n\nThe common thread across all of our work is data—lots of data. Organizations come to us when they no longer know how to make sense of the data they wish to inform their decisions, and while there are always differences, large and small, between different customers'; workflows in our software, there are also many areas of overlap.\n\nDeployment Strategists who gravitate towards process ownership are experts in deploying software and making it work for human beings. They are brilliant, articulate, and generally deeply empathetic people. They excel at sitting down with a user and within minutes understanding exactly what he or she is trying to do--and at then synthesizing that understanding into a broader vision of what we can do to help them. That might mean building a new tool, or paring superfluous features out of an existing one. It might mean implementing certain standards in data curation or analysis. It might mean a series of training sessions, or the creation of an entirely new task force. Whatever the solution, they will own it, and will ensure that our customers benefit fully from everything we've learned over the last decade of helping humans to navigate data.","status":"Published","team":"Business Development","team_slug":"business-development","name_slug":"deployment-strategist","positions":["a0m80000005LnB5AAK","a0m80000005XWU7AAO","a0m80000005XWTsAAO","a0m80000003RDCvAAO","a0m80000002MjHuAAK","a0m80000006Wdp4AAC","a0m80000006WerPAAS","a0m80000006WdozAAC","a0m80000003lpb2AAA","a0m80000003mUYHAA2","a0m800000055wVDAAY","a0m800000055wVIAAY","a0m80000005XvuZAAS","a0m80000005UAxlAAG","a0m80000005Vge2AAC"],"offices":[{"office":"Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates","position_id":"a0m80000003RDCvAAO","application_id":"a0m80000003RDCv"},{"office":"Canberra, Australia","position_id":"a0m80000002MjHuAAK","application_id":"a0m80000002MjHu"},{"office":"Copenhagen, Denmark","position_id":"a0m80000005LnB5AAK","application_id":"a0m80000005LnB5"},{"office":"Helsinki, Finland","position_id":"a0m80000005Vge2AAC","application_id":"a0m80000005Vge2"},{"office":"London, United Kingdom","position_id":"a0m80000005XvuZAAS","application_id":"a0m80000005XvuZ"},{"office":"Melbourne, Australia","position_id":"a0m80000006WdozAAC","application_id":"a0m80000006Wdoz"},{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000005XWU7AAO","application_id":"a0m80000005XWU7"},{"office":"Oslo, Norway","position_id":"a0m80000005UAxlAAG","application_id":"a0m80000005UAxl"},{"office":"Ottawa, Canada","position_id":"a0m80000003lpb2AAA","application_id":"a0m80000003lpb2"},{"office":"Stockholm, Sweden","position_id":"a0m800000055wVDAAY","application_id":"a0m800000055wVD"},{"office":"Sydney, Australia","position_id":"a0m80000006Wdp4AAC","application_id":"a0m80000006Wdp4"},{"office":"Tel Aviv, Israel","position_id":"a0m800000055wVIAAY","application_id":"a0m800000055wVI"},{"office":"Toronto, Canada","position_id":"a0m80000006WerPAAS","application_id":"a0m80000006WerP"},{"office":"Washington, D.C.","position_id":"a0m80000005XWTsAAO","application_id":"a0m80000005XWTs"},{"office":"Wellington, New Zealand","position_id":"a0m80000003mUYHAA2","application_id":"a0m80000003mUYH"}],"url":"/careers/positions/deployment-strategist/"},"Systems Analyst":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYS4AAO"},"body_text":"As Systems Analysts, our duties range across the IT spectrum, from systems administration and hardware-building to trade shows and help desk support. Adaptability is key for us—we need to be able to talk fluently to both people and machines while working in any of several IT specialties; we’re the interdisciplinary team that gets called on to solve the hardest problems with solutions that attack the root cause. \n\nWe fix whatever issues the rest of Business Development throws our way, and more importantly we do all we can to prevent problems from occurring to begin with. Our varied expertise is called upon daily in consultations across teams across the organization. We’re the technical arm of Statsopt’s logistical team, known for our excellence in execution, and we approach every day with the proactive attitude that allows us to consistently exceed expectations.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYS4AAO","intro_text":"Statsopt’s Mission Operations Systems Analysts are the first responders for our Business Development team on tough technical issues.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Systems Analyst","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Proactively support the Business Development team with an emphasis on adaptability\n*   Create and maintain demo/training computers and their support infrastructure\n*   Provide troubleshooting service at all levels\n*   Simultaneously work on time-dependent projects in an extremely fast-paced environment\n*   Support the rest of the Mission Ops & Site Reliability teams as necessary\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   2+ years experience in IT support or equivalent\n*   Basic understanding of UNIX/Linux server management\n*   Strong analytical and problem-solving skills\n*   Eagerness to take ownership\n*   Ability to perform at a high level in high-pressure situations\n*   Extreme attention to detail\n*   Ability to clearly articulate problems and proposed solutions to varied audiences\n*   Skepticism of inertia and the status quo\n*   10-15% travel with optional potential for up to 75%\n\n## Optional\n\n*   Previous or current security clearance\n*   Solid knowledge of UNIX/Linux server administration and configuration","status":"Published","team":"Mission Operations","team_slug":"mission-operations","name_slug":"systems-analyst","positions":["a0m80000004k8e6AAA","a0m80000005wmtlAAA"],"offices":[{"office":"Canberra, Australia","position_id":"a0m80000004k8e6AAA","application_id":"a0m80000004k8e6"},{"office":"Washington, D.C.","position_id":"a0m80000005wmtlAAA","application_id":"a0m80000005wmtl"}],"url":"/careers/positions/systems-analyst/"},"AV Operations":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYRFAA4"},"body_text":"Statsopt was built to solve the world’s hardest problems, and our Operations (Ops) team ensures that every aspect of internal operations runs smoothly. The Ops team takes both a high-level and granular view of what needs to be done, and easily manages competing priorities to deliver an excellent product or process.\n\nOur A/V team members bring their vision and passion to their work, making it the best it can be. We are ambitious, going above and beyond to create outstanding audio and visual experiences for internal and external company events. Above all, we are team players who believe that no job is too big or small.\n\nWe’re looking for an experienced team member who understands A/V production and logistics. At Statsopt, you’ll work with stakeholders across the business to manage the A/V process from equipment procurement to show wrap and adapt on the fly to changing priorities and issues. You will be a key contributor and help maintain the excellent performance of our Ops team.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:47.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYRFAA4","intro_text":"A/V Operations Specialists excel at all aspects of the craft, from high-level problem solving in conference and event production to on-the-spot troubleshooting with A/V equipment.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"AV Operations","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Provide A/V oversight for internal and external company events, including equipment purchase and maintenance, infrastructure advice, and vendor management\n*   Run light and sound boards, cameras, and other equipment for events\n*   Call the run of a show based off of pre-curated flows\n*   Troubleshoot problems with audio equipment, conferencing software, and content\n*   Process audio and video capture files and turn them into polished end products\n*   Build out event spaces in multiple office locations, including setting up video conferencing systems\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   Ability to skillfully operate A/V equipment, including broadcast-quality HD cameras and digital and analog audio and lighting consoles\n*   Experience with live sound mixing and adapting to a broad range of environments\n*   Comfort with rapid audio/video editing and transcoding\n*   Record of setting up A/V systems from start to finish, including design and cosmetic details\n*   Experience planning and producing large events with heavy technical and A/V components\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   Formal education in A/V production\n*   Professional proficiency with Adobe Premiere and Final Cut Pro\n*   Familiarity with Polycom conferencing systems\n*   Knowledge of Webex and similar applications\n*   Troubleshooting skills on Windows and Mac OS systems","status":"Published","team":"Operations","team_slug":"operations","name_slug":"av-operations","positions":["a0m80000006KskZAAS"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000006KskZAAS","application_id":"a0m80000006KskZ"}],"url":"/careers/positions/av-operations/"},"Business Development Operations Analyst":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYReAAO"},"body_text":"Statsopt's Business Development Operations Analysts are experts in implementation and execution. We own projects end-to-end and are willing to do whatever it takes to achieve the objective at hand. Timelines are tight, but we thrive under pressure. We're capable of running the entire spectrum of a project, from the small details to the long-term goals. We work hard, we have fun, and most importantly—we get it done.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:47.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYReAAO","intro_text":"Business Development Operations Analysts are specialists in high-level logistics: from event management to vendor relationships, from budgets to basic technical support, we do it all and we do it well.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Business Development Operations Analyst","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Proactively support the Business Development team with an emphasis on adaptability\n*   Willingness to be on-call 24/7\n*   Adapt to new challenges and responsibilities\n*   Break down complex problems into actionable tasks\n*   Own several projects simultaneously under extremely tight deadlines\n*   Balance daily responsibilities with time-dependent, high-priority tasks\n*   Anticipate problems before they happen and create contingency plans\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   BA/BS\n*   Ability to travel at least 50% of the time\n*   Hard working, professional, and most importantly, genuine\n*   Skepticism of inertia and the status quo\n*   Ability to perform at a high level in high-pressure situations\n*   Willingness to learn new technical skills\n*   Extreme attention to detail\n\nPrevious experience in several of the following:\n\n*   Event management\n*   Vendor relations\n*   Project management\n*   Budgeting/forecasting\n*   Logistical planning and execution","status":"Published","team":"Mission Operations","team_slug":"mission-operations","name_slug":"business-development-operations-analyst","positions":["a0m80000006WQBMAA4","a0m80000006WQBRAA4","a0m80000006WQB2AAO"],"offices":[{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000006WQBMAA4","application_id":"a0m80000006WQBM"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000006WQBRAA4","application_id":"a0m80000006WQBR"},{"office":"Washington, D.C.","position_id":"a0m80000006WQB2AAO","application_id":"a0m80000006WQB2"}],"url":"/careers/positions/business-development-operations-analyst/"},"Recruiting Coordinator":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTcAAO"},"body_text":"As a Recruiting Coordinator at Statsopt, you will work closely with our Hiring Managers and Recruiters to ensure a positive interview experience for all candidates. We’re looking for someone who is smart, resourceful, and who thrives under intense pressure. This position will rely heavily on your superb ability to manage multiple and competing priorities in a hectic environment. You will be part of a team that is responsible for developing, implementing, and executing on a broad recruiting strategy, with an emphasis on efficiency and overall value generation (i.e., hiring awesome people!).","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTcAAO","intro_text":"At Statsopt, Recruiting Coordinators work closely with our Hiring Managers and Recruiters to ensure a positive interview experience for all candidates at every step in the process.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Recruiting Coordinator","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Schedule multiple interviews with candidates; coordinate all details of interviews, including travel arrangements\n*   Manage written and verbal communication with candidates and hiring managers throughout the interview process\n*   Manage Applicant Tracking System (ATS) candidate records; create and run weekly tracking reports\n*   Take on an array of special projects that advance the mission of our recruiting team\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   Impeccable organizational skills and attention to detail\n*   Superior time management and multi-tasking ability\n*   Poise, superior professionalism, and discretion\n*   Strong analytical ability\n*   Strong verbal and written communication skills\n*   Excellent team player\n*   Proactive approach to problem solving\n*   Strong work ethic and willingness to take ownership for wide-ranging responsibilities\n*   BA/BS required\n*   At least 1 year of relevant experience, preferably in a technology environment","status":"Published","team":"Recruiting","team_slug":"recruiting","name_slug":"recruiting-coordinator","positions":["a0m80000005wRCzAAM","a0m80000002iHWvAAM"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000002iHWvAAM","application_id":"a0m80000002iHWv"},{"office":"Washington, D.C.","position_id":"a0m80000005wRCzAAM","application_id":"a0m80000005wRCz"}],"url":"/careers/positions/recruiting-coordinator/"},"Infrastructure Quality Engineer, New Grad":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTaAAO"},"body_text":"As an Infrastructure Quality Engineer (IQEs) at Statsopt, you will help drive customer outcomes by iterating closely with our engineers across the business to define Statsopt’s world-class product. You will assess the server architecture of each release of our software to ensure that it operates flawlessly. You will take ownership of projects and responsibility for driving outcomes for our products. This can mean anything from designing and automating software tests based on expected uses and functional requirements to finding, filing, verifying, and solving issues and defects and providing extensive input to the software development process.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTaAAO","intro_text":"Statsopt Infrastructure Quality Engineers (I work on cross-functional product teams to ensure a successful, high-quality product releases. We are energetic, highly motivated, and detail-oriented people with strong software skills.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Infrastructure Quality Engineer, New Grad","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Review and critique software specifications\n*   Design and execute test cases using functional requirements\n*   Automate existing tests and contribute new functionality to our automation framework\n*   Find and file defects and verify fixed deficiencies\n*   Maintain and administer robust enterprise software deployments\n*   Work with developers to ensure successful, high-quality releases\n*   Debug software and server issues\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   Experience working with complex systems and the desire to understand them in detail (software, biological, mechanical)\n*   Ability to thrive in a fast-moving environment with ad hoc objectives\n*   Excellent teamwork, independent decision making, and communication skills\n*   Analytical thinking, creative problem-solving, and troubleshooting skills with great attention to detail\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   BS in Engineering, Computer Science, or a related field\n*   Experience coding in a major language such as Java or C\n*   Firm grasp of testing methodologies, preferably backend and scale testing\n*   Basic knowledge of version control systems such as git or Subversion\n*   Linux systems administration experience\n*   Strong scripting abilities","status":"Published","team":"Engineering","team_slug":"engineering","name_slug":"infrastructure-quality-engineer-new-grad","positions":["a0m80000005urHAAAY","a0m80000005tM8RAAU","a0m80000000jNlvAAE"],"offices":[{"office":"London, United Kingdom","position_id":"a0m80000005tM8RAAU","application_id":"a0m80000005tM8R"},{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000005urHAAAY","application_id":"a0m80000005urHA"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000000jNlvAAE","application_id":"a0m80000000jNlv"}],"url":"/careers/positions/infrastructure-quality-engineer-new-grad/"},"People Partner":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYTbAAO"},"body_text":"The People Team at Statsopt works to ensure that all Statsoptians have the resources they need to be as effective as possible. We identify potential points of failure for our people and build the programs, policies, and processes to mitigate them. We create sustainable frameworks that scale with Statsopt as it expands to solve even more of the world’s hardest problems.\n\nOur People Partners wear a variety of hats to support operations across the People Team. This means that they own complicated projects from start to finish, with a focus on delivering the most impactful outcomes for life at Statsopt. People Partners easily move from articulating the broader context of a project—goals, tradeoffs, and outcomes—to collaborating with coworkers on sensitive issues with empathy and discretion.\n\nGenerally, People Partners have a core area of expertise, either professionally or experientially, and are excited to bring their unique perspective to Statsopt. They thrive on designing new, scalable processes and procedures and are excited to teach us something new and help us develop new ways to deal with existing issues.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYTbAAO","intro_text":"Our People Partners wear a variety of hats to support operations across the People Team. This means owning complicated projects from start to finish, with a focus on delivering the most impactful outcomes for life at Statsopt.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"People Partner","requirements_text":"## What We Do\n\nThe People Partner will be responsible for:\n\n*   Programs and projects, including autonomous execution, evaluation, and reporting of program statuses to key stakeholders\n*   Performance, including the creation of proactive, repeatable, and scalable solutions\n*   People and community, including providing guidance and advice on a variety of people management issues\n*   Metrics, including the generation and analysis of people data\n\n## What We Value\n\n*   Collaboration: We build relationships and partnerships with all people and areas of the business to better understand and meet their needs\n*   Action: We proactively develop plans to achieve our desired outcomes, even in novel situations\n*   Organization: We assist hundreds of people and coordinate our workload so that no issues fall through the cracks\n*   Individuality: We each leverage our individual perspectives and areas of expertise to improve our team and Statsopt as a whole\n*   Iteration: We constantly give and receive feedback to ensure we’re always improving\n*   Standardization: We build processes and procedures that scale across the business to ensure that all Statsoptians enjoy a uniformly positive work experience","status":"Published","team":"People Operations","team_slug":"people-operations","name_slug":"people-partner","positions":["a0m800000036HFdAAM"],"offices":[{"office":"Washington, D.C.","position_id":"a0m800000036HFdAAM","application_id":"a0m800000036HFd"}],"url":"/careers/positions/people-partner/"},"Events Coordinator":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYScAAO"},"body_text":"At Statsopt, we love events of all shapes and sizes. Success in this position relies heavily on the ability to take ownership and manage multiple large projects, each with several moving parts and in multiple geographic locations. You must be able to adapt when sudden changes arise, take initiative in solving problems, and demonstrate impeccable organizational skills to ensure flawless execution.\n\nOn the Events team, we have a broad mandate. This can span from helping our Recruiting team attract new talent and designing internal events for fostering connection to putting on conferences that boost our brand. As individuals, we execute; as a team, we ideate and position our events to help represent and enrich Statsopt. We want unconventional thinkers who value getting things done. If this is you, welcome.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYScAAO","intro_text":"Events Coordinators bring mission-critical events within Statsopt to life. We play a crucial role in shaping externally facing events as well as the internal events that make Statsopt a fun and welcoming place for all of our employees to connect throughout the year.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Events Coordinator","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities \n\n*   Schedule, execute, and coordinate all logistics for college, internal and industry-related events such as company info sessions, career fairs, holiday parties, tech talks, and conferences\n*   Multi-plan high-level events simultaneously\n*   Troubleshoot level-one technical problems\n*   Operate independently and as a part of a team\n*   Calculate and forecast event budgets\n*   Anticipate problems and create contingency plans\n*   Execute consistently under extremely tight deadlines\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   BA/BS\n*   Excellent interpersonal skills both in person and by phone\n*   Previous event coordination/support experience (please list in cover letter)\n*   Experience with audio, sound, and technical AV\n*   Must be able to work events from start to finish throughout the year, which will include nights and weekends\n*   Experience and willingness to do manual work for setup and teardown of events\n*   Extremely well organized with a proven ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment\n*   Ability to simultaneously be on track for events of varying scales and different timelines: daily, weekly, monthly, and annual projects\n*   Willingness to travel up to 25% of time\n*   Strong work ethic and ability to take on multiple projects at once\n*   Ability to adapt quickly to new challenges and projects that may or may not be familiar\n*   Skepticism of inertia and the status quo\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   2-5 years events industry experience","status":"Published","team":"Operations","team_slug":"operations","name_slug":"events-coordinator","positions":["a0m80000005uIk9AAE"],"offices":[{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000005uIk9AAE","application_id":"a0m80000005uIk9"}],"url":"/careers/positions/events-coordinator/"},"Information Security Engineer (CIRT)":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYSdAAO"},"body_text":"Our Information Security team is responsible for the security of Statsopt's people and infrastructure around the globe. As a member of the Information Security team, your technical expertise is second only to your professionalism and passion for security and technology in general. You're a highly motivated team player that thrives on solving problems and tackling new challenges.\n\nYou're the first line of defense for protecting Statsopt. You are part of an elite team responsible for 24/7 protection, detection, and investigation of security events and active attacks. Your work directly impacts the success of the mission, as you hunt for badness across our global network – wherever it may hide.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYSdAAO","intro_text":"Our Information Security Engineers (CIRT) are the first line of defense for protecting Statsopt.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Information Security Engineer (CIRT)","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*    Actively detect, respond to, and remediate security events across our global infrastructure\n*    Perform proactive enterprise-wide operations to hunt for sophisticated and previously unknown malware\n*    Develop new and novel capabilities for uncovering, detecting, and disabling malware\n*    Dissect network, host, memory, and other artifacts originating from multiple operating systems and applications\n*    Work closely with other members of the Information Security team to drive changes in the network defense posture of Statsopt\n\n## Requirements\n\n*    Active TS/SCI security clearance or willingness and eligibility to obtain a security clearance\n*    Broad exposure to security disciplines and deep exposure in one or more (preferably including Digital Forensics or Incident Response)\n*    Deep forensic experience in one or more major operating system platforms (preferably including Windows, OS X, or Linux)\n*    Strong investigative mindset with acute attention to detail\n*    Strong working knowledge of TCP/IP networking and common protocols\n\n## Preferred\n\n*    Experience reverse engineering malware to develop signatures and countermeasures\n*    Experience with Yara or OpenIOC frameworks\n*    Experience performing offensive assessments, penetration testing, exploit development, or vulnerability analysis\n*    Experience with Python (Preferred), Perl, Ruby, C/C++, or Java\n*    Experience with investigating intrusion sets or performing exploit analysis","status":"Published","team":"Security","team_slug":"security","name_slug":"information-security-engineer-cirt","positions":["a0m80000006JAg0AAG"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000006JAg0AAG","application_id":"a0m80000006JAg0"}],"url":"/careers/positions/information-security-engineer-cirt/"},"Ops Curator":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYSeAAO"},"body_text":"Ops Curators overhaul existing programs and traditional services, finding ways to improve their quality, streamline their delivery, and allow their outcomes to be provided at a massive scale. We constantly monitor the experience of Statsopt, prioritizing our workflow to ensure that problems never arise, but, when pain points surface, we mobilize our resources and attention rapidly to save the day. We actively search for best-in-class partners, cultivate multiple options for every service required by Statsopt, and monitor vendor performance rigorously throughout the lifecycle of our partnerships. \n\nLateral-thinking, active listening, and amazing customer service are attributes that are highly prized on our team. Each decision we make is data-driven and carefully documented, so Statsopt gets smarter as an organization. We excel in written communication, and our input enables any stakeholders involved to clearly perceive the crucial aspects of their decisions. On this team, we won't leave the office until we have ensured life at Statsopt is more excellent each successive day.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYSeAAO","intro_text":"Ops Curators are the catalysts of improvement in everyday life at Statsopt. Our mission is to find the best vendors, tools, and processes to make Statsopt an amazing place to work as we continue to grow at a rapid pace.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Ops Curator","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Project management\n*   Independent management and selection of vendors\n*   Budgeting/forecasting\n*   Simultaneously execute daily responsibilities and time-dependent high-priority tasks in an extremely fast-paced environment\n*   Anticipate problems and create contingency plans\n*   Execute under extremely tight deadlines\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   BA/BS\n*   Excellent written communication\n*   Ability to provide quantitative analysis\n*   Creative thinking/problem solving\n*   Ability to travel at least a few weeks of the year\n*   Experience with, and up-to-date knowledge of, technologies and business partners that can improve work life\n*   Ability to break down complex problems into actionable tasks\n*   An above average sense of professional integrity and discretion\n*   Willingness to be on-call 24/7\n*   Ability to adapt to new challenges and responsibilities\n*   Extreme attention to detail\n*   Skepticism of inertia and the status quo","status":"Published","team":"Operations","team_slug":"operations","name_slug":"ops-curator","positions":["a0m80000005vsUiAAI"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000005vsUiAAI","application_id":"a0m80000005vsUi"}],"url":"/careers/positions/ops-curator/"},"Product Quality Engineer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYUJAA4"},"body_text":"Statsopt Product Quality Engineers (PQEs) identify areas for improvement and take ownership of enhancement projects. We are looking for energetic, highly motivated, and detail-oriented engineers with strong software skills to fill this role. PQEs focus on the entire suite of Statsopt products, from applications for data visualization to our cutting-edge web components library. \n\nAs a PQE, you will drive customer outcomes by iterating closely with engineers across the business to ensure a high-quality user experience for Statsopt products. You will triage engineering issues, design features to address customer use cases, evaluate the quality of these features with manual and automated testing, and debug software problems. \n\nPQEs are technical generalists who can ramp up on new projects quickly, effectively evaluate the state of a given product, and make multifaceted contributions to the codebase to guarantee best-in-class software solutions for our customers.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYUJAA4","intro_text":"Statsopt Product Quality Engineers work on our cross-functional Product teams to ensure successful, high-quality product releases. This means that they do whatever is needed to deliver our products to people who need them the most.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Product Quality Engineer","requirements_text":"## Requirements\n\n*   BS in Computer Science, Mathematics, or a related field\n*   Experience programming in at least one common language\n*   Ability to think creatively to define product and customer needs\n*   Experience working with complex systems (software, biological, mechanical)\n*   Excellent analytical thinking skills and attention to detail\n*   Excellent written and verbal communications skills","status":"Published","team":"Engineering","team_slug":"engineering","name_slug":"product-quality-engineer","positions":["a0m80000005x5kUAAQ","a0m80000005x5kPAAQ","a0m80000005x5kAAAQ"],"offices":[{"office":"London, United Kingdom","position_id":"a0m80000005x5kAAAQ","application_id":"a0m80000005x5kA"},{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000005x5kPAAQ","application_id":"a0m80000005x5kP"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000005x5kUAAQ","application_id":"a0m80000005x5kU"}],"url":"/careers/positions/product-quality-engineer/"},"Application Security Engineer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYRKAA4"},"body_text":"Our Information Security (Infosec) Team is responsible for the security of Statsopt's people, infrastructure, and customer deployments around the globe. Infosec Engineers are highly motivated team players with a dedication to security and technology. They thrive on solving problems and tackling new challenges.\n\nAs an Application Security Engineer, you will act as both a builder, creating tools to help our engineers write more secure code, and a breaker, performing penetration tests of internally developed applications.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:47.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYRKAA4","intro_text":"Application Security Engineers work with engineering teams across Statsopt to establish and improve the security of Statsopt’s entire suite of products at every step of the development lifecycle.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Application Security Engineer","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Consult with internal teams to assist in design, threat modeling, and reviewing security-critical code\n*   Conduct periodic penetration tests of internal applications with up to several million lines of code\n*   Plan, build, and deploy infrastructure to help our engineers detect and remediate vulnerabilities automatically\n*   Work with external vendors to support 3rd party security reviews\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   Expert-level knowledge in Python, Java, or Ruby\n*   Strong familiarity with OWASP top 10 web vulnerabilities and the ability to explain them\n*   Expert with ZAP, Burp, or another intercepting proxy\n*   Knowledge of the role of static and dynamic analysis in a robust security testing suite\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   Experience in evaluating the choice and implementation of cryptography\n*   Experience evaluating the security of mobile applications on iOS and Android\n*   Experience evaluating the security of applications written in Node.js or Go\n*   Experience integrating WAFs as part of a defensible application stack\n*   Experience with fuzzing\n*   Experience with threat modeling, especially STRIDE","status":"Published","team":"Security","team_slug":"security","name_slug":"application-security-engineer","positions":["a0m80000003mQFSAA2"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000003mQFSAA2","application_id":"a0m80000003mQFS"}],"url":"/careers/positions/application-security-engineer/"},"Build Systems Engineer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYRUAA4"},"body_text":"The Internal Tools team is comprised of the experts that spend their time building, maintaining, and improving the glue that holds our development process together.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:47.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYRUAA4","intro_text":"In this highly cross-functional role, Build Systems Engineers develop innovative solutions that facilitate developer productivity.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Build Systems Engineer","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\nOur Build Systems Engineers are responsible for building and maintaining:\n\n*   Modules and configurations\n*   Scripts and plugins for our Source Control Management and Continuous Integration services\n*   Additional tooling to make testing against complex systems easier\n\nProjects that our Internal Tools team has tackled include:\n\n*   Creating simple service that makes it easy to use a shared, extremely fast Oracle server across multiple tests simultaneously\n*   Building and maintaining bleeding edge build system architectural components\n*   Building a web service for knowing how all of our internal packages depend on each other, allowing for chained upstream/downstream builds when dependencies change\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   B.S./M.S. in Computer Science or equivalent experience in one or more of the following: Ruby, Java, SQL, scripting\n*   A deep understanding of Unix, Linux, or Windows internals\n*   Strong communication skills\n*   Experience with Git, Jenkins, Gerrit, Gradle, Ivy, Oracle, Postgres, Eclipse or other open source code recommended\n*   Previous experience with Jira, Confluence, Bamboo, Stash also a plus","status":"Published","team":"Engineering","team_slug":"engineering","name_slug":"build-systems-engineer","positions":["a0m80000002LiKaAAK"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000002LiKaAAK","application_id":"a0m80000002LiKa"}],"url":"/careers/positions/build-systems-engineer/"},"Tax and International Accountant":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYUsAAO"},"body_text":"Statsopt is looking for an energetic, highly skilled individual who will thrive in this entrepreneurial environment to manage our tax accounting and international accounting. This successful candidate will manage all tax operations, assist with international accounting and provide guidance on technical tax and foreign accounting issues that are relevant to our ordinary course of business.  This role will work directly with our Finance, PeopleOps and Legal teams to expand Statsopt’s global operations.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYUsAAO","intro_text":"The Tax and International Accountant manages all tax operations, assists with international accounting and provides guidance on technical tax and foreign accounting issues that are relevant to our ordinary course of business.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Tax and International Accountant","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Manage all aspects of tax accounting; including information gathering and analysis for all Federal, State and Local tax issues (e.g., property tax, sales tax, use tax, franchise tax, oversight of unclaimed property reports/filings, preparing quarterly estimated corporate tax payments, and researching and responding to various state and local inquiries/notices)\n*   Help manage the general ledger for all international subsidiaries and assist with monthly consolidation in accordance with intercompany agreements\n*   Maintain high level of confidentiality and integrity of tax data\n*   Become the central point of contact for all tax and international accounting issues\n*   Coordinate with our external accountants on tax filings and footnotes for our audited financial statements\n*   Provide technical guidance, training, and support to the Finance, PeopleOps and Legal teams\n*   Work actively with external auditors to ensure compliance with all IRS and GAAP guidelines\n*   Build cross-functional working relationships within the company \n*   Identify and implement continuous improvement initiatives related to tax, including reporting, data gathering, value added analysis and enhancement of existing processes for efficiency and effectiveness\n*   Participate/lead various special ad hoc projects\n\n## Critical Success Factors \n\n*   High degree of forward thinking, partnering skills, personal integrity, and motivation for results\n*   Effective communication & interpersonal skills and the ability to interact effectively and professionally with cross-functional teams\n*   Strong interest in technology, innovation, civil liberties, and national security\n*   Entrepreneurial spirit and desire to meet deadlines in a rapidly growing environment\n*   Strong analytical and problem solving skills \n*   Attention to detail and organization skills \n*   Ability to multi-task in a dynamic environment\n*   Eligible to obtain clearance from the US Government\n\n## Qualifications\n\n*   Bachelor's Degree or equivalent experience in Business Administration, Economics, Finance, Accounting, or related field\n*   5+ years of working experience within a large public accounting firm and/or a small to mid-size enterprise software company with a strong concentration in tax \n*   Extensive experience in application of US GAAP\n*   Foreign subsidiary and consolidations accounting experience\n*   Highly skilled in the interpretation of tax accounting pronouncements as well as applicability to specific technical accounting transactions \n*   Strong communication, analytical, and writing skills, including the ability to summarize key accounting and operational issues to management\n*   Complex analytic problem solving and project management skills\n*   Proficiency with Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, and PowerPoint)\n*   Proficiency with NetSuite and/or other accounting systems\n*   CPA is a plus, but is not required","status":"Published","team":"Finance and Accounting","team_slug":"finance-and-accounting","name_slug":"tax-and-international-accountant","positions":["a0m80000002LgTSAA0"],"offices":[{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000002LgTSAA0","application_id":"a0m80000002LgTS"}],"url":"/careers/positions/tax-and-international-accountant/"},"Wordsmith":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYV2AAO"},"body_text":"Wordsmiths are a central part of Business Development at Statsopt. We collaborate with teams across the company to communicate our philosophy, mission, products, and impact to external audiences. On any given day, we’re writing a proposal to win a new contract, a presentation deck describing our impact at a customer, or a web-based description of a new product that our engineers have made possible.\n\nWordsmiths handle language the way our developers handle code, meaning we’re the best at what we do and perform with agility under pressure. We work alongside our engineers and developers to translate highly-technical and complex concepts into clear, concise, and powerful written products. Time is usually of the essence, so we’re always ready to craft documents and support projects on short notice.\n\nWe are prose experts, but our work extends beyond writing itself to researching potential customers and understanding how they think about their problems. Our role also demands a deep understanding of our constantly evolving product and deployment landscape. Because we work with so many groups, Wordsmiths must be highly collaborative and willing to hold ideas loosely. We are constantly improving our internal processes and communication vehicles to ensure that our work reflects the broader mission.\n\nOur backgrounds are diverse, but we all have a passion for the written word, drive for perfection, and commitment to execution.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:49.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYV2AAO","intro_text":"Wordsmiths handle language the way our developers handle code, meaning we’re the best at what we do and perform with agility under pressure.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Wordsmith","requirements_text":"## Responsibilities\n\n*   Communicate the core concepts of our business philosophy, mission, impact, and products to multiple audiences, including executives, policymakers, contracting officers, and the public\n*   Write responses, solo or collaboratively, to proposals and other solicitations from potential customers\n*   Write concept papers, presentation decks, and marketing documents to support customer outreach\n*   Identify new customers and opportunities in collaboration with the broader business development team\n*   Gain deep knowledge of our products and their applications to a variety of use cases\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   BA/BS (or MA/MS/JD/MBA/PhD) from a top university or equivalent experience\n*   Exceptional writing and editing ability\n*   Demonstrated communication and interpersonal skills\n*   Superior attention to detail\n\n## Preferred\n\n*   Background in a technical field \n*   Ability to travel on short notice","status":"Published","team":"Business Development","team_slug":"business-development","name_slug":"wordsmith","positions":["a0m80000002LdDNAA0","a0m80000002wl3rAAA","a0m80000002wl3wAAA","a0m80000005rFRwAAM","a0m80000005rFRrAAM","a0m80000003jZb8AAE"],"offices":[{"office":"Canberra, Australia","position_id":"a0m80000005rFRwAAM","application_id":"a0m80000005rFRw"},{"office":"London, United Kingdom","position_id":"a0m80000005rFRrAAM","application_id":"a0m80000005rFRr"},{"office":"Los Angeles, CA","position_id":"a0m80000003jZb8AAE","application_id":"a0m80000003jZb8"},{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000002wl3rAAA","application_id":"a0m80000002wl3r"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000002LdDNAA0","application_id":"a0m80000002LdDN"},{"office":"Washington, D.C.","position_id":"a0m80000002wl3wAAA","application_id":"a0m80000002wl3w"}],"url":"/careers/positions/wordsmith/"},"Communications Strategist":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYRBAA4"},"body_text":"Statsopt enables the world’s most important institutions to solve their hardest problems, but we can only scale our impact at these institutions if they understand our software, our people, and what we’re capable of accomplishing together. Communications Strategists play a critical role in enabling our Business Development team to deliver clear and compelling narratives about what we do.\n\nCommunications Strategists own how Statsopt’s software, impact, and mission are communicated to external audiences. We collaborate with teams across the company to gain an in-depth understanding our products, triage new business opportunities, and determine what message and what vehicle will resonate most strongly with a given audience. We work within Business Development to help customers understand the value Statsopt is creating for them and ways our software can be applied to new use cases and business units. We design new modes of communication when existing ones are insufficient. We develop content for proposals, marketing documents, and presentations. We manage highly-complex communications projects involving both internal and external counterparties. And we implement processes and structures that empower everyone on the Business Development team to deliver persuasive content quickly and effectively.\n\nThis role is neither static nor easily defined. It changes as quickly as our company and our products. We are looking for people who will shape Statsopt’s Business Development communications, whether it’s figuring out the best way to describe our search technology on our website, designing a more efficient method to share communications products across Statsopt’s teams, or managing the development of a critical proposal for a federal agency. If you identify with any of these kinds of challenges, we’d love to talk to you.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:47.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYRBAA4","intro_text":"Communications Strategists own how Statsopt’s software, impact, and mission are communicated to external audiences.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-04T23:34:55.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Communications Strategist","requirements_text":"Here are a few “versions” of Communications Strategists that have worked well for us.\n\n### Content Expert\n\n*   Research, write, and edit a wide range of Business Development communications products\n*   Define how Statsopt’s software, impact, and mission are communicated to broad audiences and specific customers\n*   Document new offerings and technologies through proposals, presentations, and marketing materials\n\n### Communications Manager\n\n*   Design and execute communication plans for our most important deployments\n*   Manage complex government proposals or product documentation projects involving multiple teams across Statsopt\n*   Capture, document, and disseminate customer success metrics\n*   Draft prose for targeted communications products in collaboration with other teams across Business Development\n\n### Communications Designer\n\n*   Design new communications vehicles and products for customer or public consumption\n*   Develop new templates in HTML, InDesign, and PowerPoint\n*   Construct graphics and visuals for a range of communications products\n\n## Requirements\n\n*   Exceptional communication skills\n*   BA/BS (or MA/MS/JD/MBA/PhD) from a top university or equivalent experience\n*   At least two years of experience (typically more) in a role that requires significant writing, communications design, communications strategy, and/or management of complex projects\n*   Sample (not comprehensive) backgrounds: management consulting, public policy, law, government, technology, digital marketing, finance, data science\n*   Ability to quickly grok technical concepts and thrive in a highly technical environment","status":"Published","team":"Business Development","team_slug":"business-development","name_slug":"communications-strategist","positions":["a0m80000006UCSKAA4","a0m80000006UCS5AAO","a0m80000006UCS0AAO","a0m80000006UCSFAA4","a0m80000006UCRlAAO","a0m80000006UCSAAA4"],"offices":[{"office":"Canberra, Australia","position_id":"a0m80000006UCSAAA4","application_id":"a0m80000006UCSA"},{"office":"London, United Kingdom","position_id":"a0m80000006UCSFAA4","application_id":"a0m80000006UCSF"},{"office":"Los Angeles, CA","position_id":"a0m80000006UCSKAA4","application_id":"a0m80000006UCSK"},{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000006UCS0AAO","application_id":"a0m80000006UCS0"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000006UCRlAAO","application_id":"a0m80000006UCRl"},{"office":"Washington, D.C.","position_id":"a0m80000006UCS5AAO","application_id":"a0m80000006UCS5"}],"url":"/careers/positions/communications-strategist/"},"Forward Deployed Software Engineer":{"attributes":{"type":"Website_Job__c","url":"/services/data/v33.0/sobjects/Website_Job__c/a2a80000000PYRCAA4"},"body_text":"Forward Deployed Software Engineers (FDSEs) understand our customers’ greatest pain points and design end-to-end solutions to address them. FDSEs solicit constant feedback on their work from both customers and colleagues, improving our products over time with rapid iteration cycles.\r\n\r\nFDSEs deploy cutting-edge technologies to solve our customers’ hardest problems. Projects often start with a nebulous question like “Why are we losing customers?” or “How can we more effectively identify instances of money laundering?” FDSEs are thought leaders and first movers in developing a solution, from high-level system design and prototyping to application development and data integration.\r\n\r\nFDSEs work with customers around the world, where they gain unique insight into the world’s most important industries and institutions. We help our customers detect insider trading, improve disaster relief, fight healthcare fraud, and more. Each mission presents different challenges, from the regulatory environment to the nature of the data to the user population. FSDEs work to accommodate all aspects of an environment to drive real outcomes for our customers.","createdbyid":"00580000008cD3fAAE","createddate":"2015-06-04T04:06:48.000+0000","custom_sidebar_body":null,"custom_sidebar_title":null,"id":"a2a80000000PYRCAA4","intro_text":"Forward Deployed Software Engineers are responsible for the technical success of each of our deployments. They are full-stack developers who work side by side with our customers to lead technical implementation of our products.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-09T18:38:06.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer","requirements_text":"## Technologies We Use  \r\n\r\nOur approach is to deploy whatever technology is best to solve the problem at hand. This often means that we are learning from the bleeding edge of the open-source community or developing our own tools. Recently, FDSEs have deployed:\r\n\r\n*   **Postgres, Cassandra, Hadoop,** and **Spark** for distributed data storage\r\n*   **Java** and **Groovy** for our back-end applications and data integration tools\r\n*   **Typescript, AngularJS, jQuery, Backbone, Underscore, Leaflet,** and **d3** for our web technologies\r\n*   **Python** for data science and machine learning\r\n*   **Internal frameworks** for our rapid iteration tools\r\n\r\n## What We Value\r\n\r\nFDSEs are developers with a passion for using technology to achieve a larger goal.  They enjoy the challenge of solving an abstract problem and building or adopting the technology to do it. To support these goals, we value:\r\n\r\n*   **Collaboration:** We work with our customers, often on site, to understand and solve their problems\r\n*   **Commitment:** We see projects through from beginning to end in spite of obstacles we may encounter.\r\n*   **Balance:** We do whatever is necessary to finish the job and trust one another to take the time we need, whether it's vacation or just a trip to the gym\r\n*   **Communication:** We communicate complex technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences\r\n*   **Improvement:** We push ourselves to grow and develop in new ways\r\n*   **Impact:** We take on meaningful and challenging projects that change the world for the better\r\n\r\n<span class=\"attention\">Expected travel for the role varies by location.</span>","status":"Published","team":"Business Development","team_slug":"business-development","name_slug":"forward-deployed-software-engineer","positions":["a0m80000000M1DSAA0","a0m80000005XWTnAAO","a0m80000005XWUCAA4","a0m80000005XWUDAA4","a0m80000005JZNPAA4","a0m80000002yG8TAAU","a0m80000006WcmpAAC","a0m80000006WdopAAC","a0m80000005t3BsAAI","a0m80000006WerUAAS","a0m80000003lpY2AAI","a0m80000002IiWkAAK","a0m80000002LaXRAA0","a0m80000005U0ulAAC","a0m80000003mUYCAA2","a0m800000055wUKAAY","a0m800000055wUPAAY"],"offices":[{"office":"Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates","position_id":"a0m80000003lpY2AAI","application_id":"a0m80000003lpY2"},{"office":"Canberra, Australia","position_id":"a0m80000002IiWkAAK","application_id":"a0m80000002IiWk"},{"office":"Copenhagen, Denmark","position_id":"a0m80000005JZNPAA4","application_id":"