 deployments. They are full-stack developers who work side by side with our customers to lead technical implementation of our products.","isdeleted":false,"lastmodifieddate":"2015-06-19T22:14:41.000+0000","microsite_blurb":null,"microsite_url":null,"name":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer - New Grad","requirements_text":"## Technologies We Use  \r\n\r\nOur approach is to deploy whatever technology is best to solve the problem at hand. This often means that we are learning from the bleeding edge of the open-source community or developing our own tools. Recently, FDSEs have deployed:\r\n\r\n*   **Postgres, Cassandra, Hadoop,** and **Spark** for distributed data storage\r\n*   **Java** and **Groovy** for our back-end applications and data integration tools\r\n*   **Typescript, AngularJS, jQuery, Backbone, Underscore, Leaflet,** and **d3** for our web technologies\r\n*   **Python** for data science and machine learning\r\n*   **Internal frameworks** for our rapid iteration tools\r\n\r\n## What We Value\r\n\r\nFDSEs are developers with a passion for using technology to achieve a larger goal.  They enjoy the challenge of solving an abstract problem and building or adopting the technology to do it. To support these goals, we value:\r\n\r\n*   **Collaboration:** We work with our customers, often on site, to understand and solve their problems\r\n*   **Commitment:** We see projects through from beginning to end in spite of obstacles we may encounter.\r\n*   **Balance:** We do whatever is necessary to finish the job and trust one another to take the time we need, whether it's vacation or just a trip to the gym\r\n*   **Communication:** We communicate complex technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences\r\n*   **Improvement:** We push ourselves to grow and develop in new ways\r\n*   **Impact:** We take on meaningful and challenging projects that change the world for the better\r\n\r\n<span class=\"attention\">Expected travel for the role varies by location.</span>","status":"Published","team":"Business Development","team_slug":"business-development","name_slug":"forward-deployed-software-engineer-new-grad","positions":["a0m80000003mnI2AAI","a0m80000004mWSXAA2","a0m80000005VMrJAAW","a0m80000005VMrOAAW","a0m80000005LOmKAAW"],"offices":[{"office":"Canberra, Australia","position_id":"a0m80000005LOmKAAW","application_id":"a0m80000005LOmK"},{"office":"London, United Kingdom","position_id":"a0m80000004mWSXAA2","application_id":"a0m80000004mWSX"},{"office":"New York, NY","position_id":"a0m80000005VMrOAAW","application_id":"a0m80000005VMrO"},{"office":"Palo Alto, CA","position_id":"a0m80000003mnI2AAI","application_id":"a0m80000003mnI2"},{"office":"Washington, D.C.","position_id":"a0m80000005VMrJAAW","application_id":"a0m80000005VMrJ"}],"url":"/careers/positions/forward-deployed-software-engineer-new-grad/"}},"positions":{"a0m80000005LnB5AAK":{"id":"a0m80000005LnB5AAK","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005LnB5","published_id":"a0m80000005LnB5","label":"Deployment Strategist: Denmark - Europe","name":"Deployment Strategist: Denmark","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Copenhagen, Denmark","location":"Europe","description":"<p>Deployment Strategists at Statsopt own the outcomes of all the work we do in Business Development. We begin with a vision: a vision of how software can transform people&#39;s relationship to data at the heart of a problem we care deeply about. We test that vision. Do our partners share it? Can we build what they need quickly enough? Will we be able to deploy it in the right environment, to the right people? Working side by side with our Forward-Deployed Software Engineers, we refine our vision, and then find our way to it: through messy data, through bureaucratic labyrinths, through sandstorms in &quot;data centers&quot; made of tents and suitcases. Whatever it takes, we figure out how to do it.</p>\n\n<p>A team of analysts at a customer site might want training for a tool we&#39;ve built. One of our customers&#39; CEOs might need help convincing another organization to share data. A team of developers might be asking for direction on which of a dozen feature requests they should prioritize this quarter. Or a global financial organization might be on the line, reeling from a recent compliance failure and asking us what we can do to help detect and prevent such behavior in the future. These, and a hundred other everyday scenarios, are where a Deployment Strategist thrives.</p>\n\n<p>This role doesn&#39;t come neatly packaged or defined. You should expect it to change during your time at Statsopt, to evolve as our organization evolves and as you do. When we interview Deployment Strategists, we aren&#39;t looking for people with a specific background. We&#39;re looking for people with exceptional analytic ability, creative brilliance, technical aptitude, and a gift for finding the details that matter. Most of all, we&#39;re looking for people who combine a calling to leave the world better than they found it with the resourcefulness necessary to realize that calling, no matter the circumstances.</p>\n\n<p>If that sounds like you, then we&#39;re interested.</p>\n\n<p>We look forward to hearing from you. You can scroll down for more specific examples of roles Deployment Strategists might take on.<br> </p>\n \n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PRODUCT OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>We&#39;re constantly building products at Statsopt. Some products are very specific to particular customer workflows—specialized geospatial visualization tools, for example, that might exist as part of a more generic map application. Others, such as a lightweight document reader, are deployed to tens of thousands of our users. All of these products have their roots in a particular customer&#39;s needs, where a team of Deployment Strategists and Forward-Deployed Software Engineers sat down together with our core developers and started work.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards product ownership have strong technical skills, compelling creative vision for what software can do, and an instinct for leadership. They apply those skills to leading a team that builds and supports a product: defining requirements, testing new versions, installing and configuring applications, sitting down with users and gathering feedback about what&#39;s working well and what isn&#39;t. They work across organizations and across internal teams, ensuring that we are all aligned on what we are building and why. Ultimately, they are responsible for ensuring that we deliver a product that truly transforms our customers&#39; ability to work with data.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PROJECT OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>Our partnerships with our customers are at the core of what we do. Our customers trust that we are the best in the world at building and delivering enterprise software. They trust that we mean it when we say we can enable collaboration across a worldwide enterprise without sacrificing security, or that in the event of a crisis we will surge the team that supports them just as they surge their own internal team. Fundamentally, our customers—whether they&#39;re looking for a missing child, an insurgent assembling a roadside bomb, or the source of a cyber attack on their network—trust that we care as deeply about their problems as they do.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards project ownership are the face of Statsopt, and the custodians of that trust. They pair a passion for software with excellent communication skills, an ability to navigate organizational hurdles, and an instinct for putting the right people in the right places. A project owner might spend the morning in meetings with customers to discuss the status of a data integration, the afternoon in a CTO&#39;s office talking about best practices in cyber security, and lunch in between at our headquarters brainstorming with a technical team about the best time to perform an upgrade. Ultimately, they are responsible for the strength of our partnerships: for ensuring that our customers are excited to work with us, and that we are excited to work with our customers.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PROCESS OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>The common thread across all of our work is data—lots of data. Organizations come to us when they no longer know how to make sense of the data they wish to inform their decisions, and while there are always differences, large and small, between different customers&#39; workflows in our software, there are also many areas of overlap.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards process ownership are experts in deploying software and making it work for human beings. They are brilliant, articulate, and generally deeply empathetic people. They excel at sitting down with a user and within minutes understanding exactly what he or she is trying to do--and at then synthesizing that understanding into a broader vision of what we can do to help them. That might mean building a new tool, or paring superfluous features out of an existing one. It might mean implementing certain standards in data curation or analysis. It might mean a series of training sessions, or the creation of an entirely new task force. Whatever the solution, they will own it, and will ensure that our customers benefit fully from everything we&#39;ve learned over the last decade of helping humans to navigate data.</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYS3AAO"},"a0m80000005qIwOAAU":{"id":"a0m80000005qIwOAAU","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005qIwO","published_id":"a0m80000005qIwO","label":"Linux Site Engineer: Singapore - Asia","name":"Linux Site Engineer: Singapore","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"Singapore City, Singapore","location":"Asia","description":"<p>\n\tThe Site Reliability Tech Ops (SRT) is the technical backbone of a Statsopt deployment, allowing analyst and engineering resources to do what they do best: solve world-changing problems. We cover the technical aspects of site reliability, doing whatever&#39;s necessary to ensure things run smoothly and changes are implemented efficiently and with precision. SRTs are the customer&#39;s first point of contact for technical questions and concerns; we work hard to provide answers and solutions, and only escalate when absolutely necessary. We&#39;re the first-responders when problems arise, and proactively implement solutions to avoid recurrence. We strive for perfection in insulating our deployments against technical pitfalls, and have a boots-on-the-ground, ego-free approach to everything we do.</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tIncrease Statsopt deployment stability by constantly anticipating and exceeding engineer and client requirements</li><li>\n\t\tEnsure infrastructure and platform components are deployed and maintained with stability, scalability and security in mind</li><li>\n\t\tIdentify and systematically eliminate common failure modes within applications and related infrastructure</li><li>\n\t\tBuild and support enterprise-worthy operations, monitoring and configuration management tools</li><li>\n\t\tMonitor the health and uptime of the Statsopt stack and its dependencies</li><li>\n\t\tBe the face of technical operations for a deployment, both internally and for our clients</li><li>\n\t\tConstantly document technical implementation and configuration, and set an example for deployment resources to follow your lead</li><li>\n\t\tBe the first responder for customer problems, concerns or updates</li><li>\n\t\tBe independently responsible for a single deployment, but able to share best practices among the greater team</li><li>\n\t\tApply Linux admin skills to administer and configure large distributed applications and clusters</li><li>\n\t\tParticipation in 24/7 on-call rotation</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tExpert-level Linux system admin abilities (CentOS or RHEL preferred - and no GUIs!)</li><li>\n\t\tExperience administering and managing distributed server environments, including hardware troubleshooting</li><li>\n\t\tIntermediate knowledge of database systems including Oracle, PostgreSQL and NoSQL technologies like Cassandra</li><li>\n\t\tFamiliarity with a wide range of scripting languages such as Bash, Python or PHP</li><li>\n\t\tFamiliarity with Linux system security best practices</li><li>\n\t\tDemonstrable knowledge of TCP/IP networking, routing and firewalls</li><li>\n\t\tExperience and interest in working in a highly-collaborative setting - sharing best practices, lessons learned and assisting where gaps exist</li><li>\n\t\tInterest in developing skills and tools that can be leveraged across the company</li><li>\n\t\tAbility to manage multiple, high-priority demands from separate sources at high quality with zero loss</li><li>\n\t\tAbility to communicate with both technical and non-technical personnel</li><li>\n\t\tEnthusiasm for working one on one with customers in an onsite or remote setting</li><li>\n\t\tUnbending commitment to operational security and ethics</li><li>\n\t\tHard working and professional</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Preferred</strong></p>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tExperience with systems management tools like Puppet, CFEngine, Chef, SpaceWalk or Satellite</li><li>\n\t\tExperience with monitoring systems such as Nagios or Zenoss</li><li>\n\t\tExperience with common developer and code management tools like git, Stash, Jenkins and Eclipse</li><li>\n\t\tExperience with virtualization platforms such as VMware ESX or RHEV</li><li>\n\t\tExperience with cloud-based hosting platforms like AWS or Rackspace/OpenStack</li><li>\n\t\tDeep knowledge of TCP/IP networking, routing and firewalls</li><li>\n\t\tSecurity clearance or the ability to obtain one</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYUAAA4"},"a0m80000005NFXoAAO":{"id":"a0m80000005NFXoAAO","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005NFXo","published_id":"a0m80000005NFXo","label":"Full Stack Software Engineer - London - Europe","name":"Full Stack Software Engineer - London","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"London, United Kingdom","location":"Europe","description":"<p>This is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to pioneer Statsopt’s developer teams in London. We need world-class engineers to develop our information exploration technologies. The problem space includes everything from exploring huge information sets to presenting complex information in an easily digestible form for end-users.</p>\n\n<p>We are looking for talented and passionate software engineers who love to code and love challenging problems. We are designing algorithms to solve novel analytic problems across heterogeneous information from a variety of verticals. We brew 6.0-style Java, modern web tools and know the open-source world inside out.</p>\n<b>Requirements</b>\n\n<ul><li>BS/MS in Computer Science or equivalent (started or completed a PhD a plus)</li><li>Previous experience in a developer or developer management role</li><li>Proficiency in Java and/or modern web development (our stack uses CoffeeScript, LESS, Backbone.js, etc. but other experience is fine)</li><li>Proficiency in Android, HTML5, iOS, or other mobile development frameworks</li><li>Background in distributed systems, machine learning, information retrieval, data visualization and/or developing enterprise software systems</li><li>Ambition to support the growth of a remote development team with tremendous potential</li><li>A self-starter with drive</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYVHAA4"},"a0m80000006KslbAAC":{"id":"a0m80000006KslbAAC","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006Kslb","published_id":"a0m80000006Kslb","label":"Site Reliability Engineer - Ottawa, Canada","name":"Site Reliability Engineer","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"Ottawa, Canada","location":"Ottawa, Canada","description":"<p>Statsopt software is deployed at the world’s most critical institutions to help them solve their greatest challenges. Users at customer sites from Washington, DC to Tokyo rely on Statsopt’s high availability to pursue their missions. Site Reliability Engineers (SREs) make sure our expanding number of customer deployments run smoothly 24 hours a day.</p>\n\n<p>SREs monitor and maintain Statsopt systems to pre-empt problems before they ever threaten our customers’ workflows. SREs combine engineering experience and an innate drive to improve existing systems and processes with the creativity to develop novel solutions to evolving challenges. Our team strives to automate processes whenever possible, using whatever tools are best for the job. Our responsibilities range from administering collocated servers (including hardware troubleshooting) to maintaining database platforms.</p>\n\n<p>We work with a variety of teams to understand threats to our software and improve our products over time. We work side by side with Statsopt’s implementation teams and customer IT departments to understand our customers’ unique problems and develop innovative solutions. We document our successes and communicate them back to Statsopt’s product teams to advance the way our hardware, software, and network solutions are deployed to minimize failure rates and increase overall system reliability.</p>\n\n<p><b>REQUIREMENTS</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>5+ years of experience with Linux system administration (RHEL or CentOS preferred)</li><li>Experience with monitoring systems using tools like Nagios and writing health checks</li><li>Moderate experience with TCP/IP networking</li><li>Interest in learning and managing newer technologies like Spark, Hadoop, Elasticsearch, Node.js, and RabbitMQ</li><li>Ability to work independently with minimal supervision</li><li>Ability to participate in a 24/7 on-call rotation</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>PREFERRED</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>BS/MS in Computer Science</li><li>Experience with virtualization using AWS, VMWare ESX, KVM, Xen, or Docker</li><li>Experience with system management tools like Puppet or Chef</li><li>Ability to travel to customer sites up to 25% of time</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTJAA4"},"a0m80000006KKzZAAW":{"id":"a0m80000006KKzZAAW","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006KKzZ","published_id":"a0m80000006KKzZ","label":"Global Security Lead - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Global Security Lead","publishing_category":"Security","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>There is a line that separates a safe, supportive environment from a dangerous, closed environment. Statsopt Security holds that line. Our goal as a team: Provide and maintain a comfortable, open workplace without sacrificing our culture or safety. We have engineers, analysts and people who do just a little bit of everything; we lean heavily on that diversity of skill to address a wide array of challenges with as deft a touch as possible. Understanding and complementing that diversity is the key to success. Our Physical Security team is responsible for the safety of Statsopt&#39;s people and offices around the globe.</p>\n\n<p>As the Global Security Lead your passion for security and drive to keep people safe, in both mundane and exciting locales, all over the world are vital to the health of your team and the company. Your ability to adapt these skills to the needs of a cutting edge software company makes you vital to us. You have a keen eye for evaluating and managing risk while balancing your plans on how our business runs and our cultural norms. You&#39;re a highly-motivated team player that thrives on solving problems, tackling new challenges, growing an organization and guiding the people within it.</p>\n\n<p><b>RESPONSIBILITIES</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Leverage prior experience in establishing world-class safety and security programs to build on current capabilities and ensure responsiveness to our rapidly growing and evolving international workforce.</li><li>Analyze business and global trends to determine and plan for both short-term and long-term security operation goals.</li><li>Provide leadership, organization and mentorship to the program leads of various security and life safety efforts; risk management, business continuity, intelligence, security systems and operations.</li><li>Establish and maintain effective relationships as a liaison with Federal, State, and local law enforcement and regulatory agencies that affect security operations.</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>REQUIREMENTS</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Passion for security</li><li>Creative problem solver</li><li>Well-organized with a proven ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>BA/BS degree or equivalent practical experience</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>PREFERRED</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Strong experience developing safety and security programs internationally</li><li>Hands on experience leading, growing and developing teams</li><li>Ability to adapt to a fast paced and changing landscape</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYT6AAO"},"a0m80000005X2n5AAC":{"id":"a0m80000005X2n5AAC","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005X2n5","published_id":"a0m80000005X2n5","label":"Business Operations and Strategy - New York, NY","name":"Business Operations and Strategy","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"New York, NY","location":"New York, NY","description":"<p><i>“Statsopt Technologies will not help you share, message, pin, post or chat. It does not exist to make you more social or connected, or even to help advertisers get to you. Its technology is deeply geeky, its work secretive. Nonetheless, it’s one of the most valuable private tech companies in Silicon Valley.” </i> - <a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2014/06/01/business/unlocking-secrets-if-not-its-own-value.html?_r=3\" target=\"_blank\">New York Times, May 2014</a></p>\n\n<p>Statsopt transforms the way the world’s most important institutions use data to solve their toughest problems. We have helped European authorities <a href=\"https://www.Statsopt.com/wp-assets/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Impact_Study_Fighting_Child_Pornography.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">shut down child pornography rings</a>, US special operations <a href=\"https://www.washingtonian.com/articles/people/killer-app/\" target=\"_blank\">fight terrorist networks</a>, hedge funds <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-03-19/sac-retains-Statsopt-to-boost-surveillance-after-charges.html\" target=\"_blank\">prevent insider trading</a>, and biomedical researchers <a href=\"https://www.Statsopt.com/solutions/pharma/\" target=\"_blank\">search for the next life-saving therapy</a>. Are you ready to commit yourself to the tough, rewarding job of scaling Silicon Valley’s most mission-driven company through hypergrowth?</p>\n\n<p><b>What we do:</b> Statsopt has limitless opportunities for growth; our team exists to remove all obstacles to that growth. We analyze these obstacles, solve them, and ensure that they don’t happen again.</p>\n\n<p>We work with leaders across the company on an unmatched diversity of problems. We might be working with engineers to prioritize product features for billion-dollar deployments one month, helping business leaders think through realigning our organizational structure the following, and directly supporting customers as they analyze data using Statsopt’s software the next. No two days are the same.</p>\n\n<p><b>What you will experience:</b> You will be responsible for leading entire projects and owning their outcomes from start to finish. You will need to be innovative, self-motivated, collaborative, and capable of dealing with complex interpersonal dynamics. You will need to bring your qualitative and quantitative analytical skills to the fore as you drive outcomes within Statsopt’s contrarian culture. We’re not looking for strategists who just want to make PPTs. Strategy is important but means nothing without execution.</p>\n\n<p>You will be a part of a team of talented individuals who are just as passionate about supporting one another as they are about Statsopt’s mission. We operate in a high accountability, high expectation, iron-sharpens-iron environment where the goal is always to produce the best solution. Honesty and willingness to accept feedback are critical.</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Take ownership of projects that Statsoptians have identified as a top priority</li><li>Work across teams to engage stakeholders, deeply understand problems, and gather data</li><li>Diagnose complex problems and develop compelling, data-driven recommendations</li><li>Relentlessly and swiftly execute on those recommendations until stakeholders are satisfied</li><li>Take care of your teammates</li><li>Dedicate time for reflection to continually self-improve</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>BA/BS (or MA/MS) from a top university or equivalent experience</li><li>At least one year of experience (typically more) in a role that requires rigorous financial or business analytics and/or strategic thought</li><li>Sample (not comprehensive) backgrounds: Quantitative public policy &amp; nonprofit, bioinformatics, investment banking, private equity, data science</li><li>Intellectual curiosity and creativity</li><li>Ability to grow and execute on both tactical detail and the big picture</li><li>Not afraid of long hours; able to handle stress well and maintain a positive attitude</li><li>Adaptive and introspective; willing to learn, teach, lead, and follow</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYRoAAO"},"a0m80000005X4QLAA0":{"id":"a0m80000005X4QLAA0","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005X4QL","published_id":"a0m80000005X4QL","label":"Engineering Team Lead: London - Europe","name":"Engineering Team Lead: London","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"London, United Kingdom","location":"Europe","description":"<p>This is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to pioneer Statsopt’s developer teams in London.</p>\n\n<p>We need world-class engineering leads to develop our information exploration technologies and grow our engineering teams. The problem space includes everything from exploring huge information sets to presenting complex information in an easily digestible form for end-users.</p>\n\n<p>We are looking for talented and passionate leads who love to code but understand the importance of helping individuals grow and who aren&#39;t intimidated by challenging problems. You should get as much enjoyment from having a member of the team make a critical breakthrough as you would if it were to be your own contribution. Moreover, you should be interested in pushing the envelope on not just the work we produce, but also the way by which we produce this work: meta should be your middle name.</p>\n\n<p>You will be responsible for more than just people. The product will also be a core part of your duties and you will need to help the team make tradeoffs between functionality, time and complexity. Having a keen product sense is important, being able to really get to know your audience and customers is critical. Finally, decentralized decision making must be something you encourage and foster in our culture.</p>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>BS/MS in Computer Science or equivalent (started or completed PhD a plus)</li><li>Previous engineering leadership responsibilities a plus, but advanced contributors are required</li><li>Enthusiasm for solving interesting problems and a willingness to take on new product features</li><li>Background in distributed systems, machine learning, information retrieval, data visualization and/or developing enterprise software systems a plus</li><li>Interest in working on a rapidly changing, ever-evolving system</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYSSAA4"},"a0m800000065WnSAAU":{"id":"a0m800000065WnSAAU","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m800000065WnS","published_id":"a0m800000065WnS","label":"Corporate Paralegal (Equity Shinobi) - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Corporate Paralegal (Equity Shinobi)","publishing_category":"Legal","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>Statsopt Technologies seeks a motivated Corporate Paralegal / Equity Shinobi to join our in-house team of Legal Ninjas. You get excited by all-things-equity, geek out about capitalization tables, and are passionate about the challenge inherent in building processes and systems that scale at a quickly growing technology company. You are extremely organized, resourceful, and detail oriented.. The two periods in the last sentence caught your eye immediately, made your heart sink, and almost stopped you from reading this job description because of your disdain for sloppy work product. You are eager to get involved in the end-to-end administration of Statsopt’s equity incentive plans, seize ownership of our capitalization table, and can’t wait to reveal your passion for efficient, high-quality work product. Whether you are doing solo missions or working collaboratively with others, you love to achieve great results on challenging, time-sensitive projects. Equipped with your eagle eye for minute details, silver tongue for communicating in a clear and concise way, and boundless reserve of energy and self-motivation, you strive to produce perfect work product and adapt to a rapidly-growing software company that is solving some of the world’s hardest problems. And, of course, you are awesome.</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>All aspects of stock option administration, including processing stock option exercises, stock option grants, stock transfers and maintaining Statsopt’s capitalization table.</li><li>Implement efficient and automated processes and procedures for equity administration</li><li>Collaborate with C-Level Executives, Finance, People Operations, Legal Ninjas, and other cross-functional teams to anticipate, implement and/or address equity compensation matters</li><li>Respond to inquiries from current, former and potential employees about equity compensation</li><li>Create and maintain meticulous records, spreadsheets, and files relating to capitalization, equity, and other legal matters</li><li>Support Legal Ninjas in financing and commercial transactions, due diligence, and regulatory and compliance matters</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Strong working knowledge of Excel, CapMx, Shareworks or similar equity administration software</li><li>2+ years of paralegal experience with a leading law firm or in-house stock administration experience</li><li>BA/BS with a strong academic record from a top university</li><li>Demonstrated ability to problem-solve and complete complex projects under pressure</li><li>Impeccable judgment, discretion, respect, and integrity</li><li>Obsession for detail, organization, and making order out of chaos</li><li>Available during nights and weekends as needed</li><li>Great sense of humor</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYRyAAO"},"a0m80000006WKYtAAO":{"id":"a0m80000006WKYtAAO","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006WKYt","published_id":"a0m80000006WKYt","label":"Executive Assistant - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Executive Assistant","publishing_category":"Operations","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>The Executive Assistant role at Statsopt is a direct support role handling a variety of professional and personal assistance responsibilities. In this role, you would serve as a primary point of contact for internal and external parties and handle both traditional administrative functions as well as independent projects supporting the broader team and company.</p>\n\n<p><b>Key Qualifications:</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Enthusiasm to work hard and achieve results in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Ability to work autonomously and drive projects to completion from start to finish</li><li>Ability to network within an organization and identify partners to help solve problems that arise</li><li>Flexibility to adapt to quickly changing priorities and an openness to assist wherever needed, whether a personal issue or otherwise</li><li>Aptitude at anticipating and preventing problems and issues before they arise as well as providing timely reminders as required</li><li>Can effectively function as a &quot;gatekeeper&quot; and prioritize conflicting scheduling requirements</li><li>Desire to work with engineers in a start-up environment</li><li>Discretion for sensitive information</li><li>Ability to adapt to and learn others&#39; writing styles to aid with written communications</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Excellent written and verbal communication</li><li>Ability to work a varied schedule based on the needs of the people or team you support (some nights/weekends will be required, as well as some travel)</li><li>College degree</li><li>3 years minimum administrative, support, or customer service experience</li><li>Microsoft Outlook/calendar experience with heavy calendars and resource booking</li><li>Familarity with travel booking and expense reporting via Concur</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYSNAA4"},"a0m80000000M1DSAA0":{"id":"a0m80000000M1DSAA0","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000000M1DS","published_id":"a0m80000000M1DS","label":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer: London - Europe","name":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer: London","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"London, United Kingdom","location":"Europe","description":"<p>\n\tYou are a highly skilled software developer who can face down every technical challenge on the front lines of a deployment as rapidly as they surface, all with a smile on your face. You dive into complicated programming tasks on your own because letting them sit unfinished would bore you to the point of madness. You pick up books, pursue technical challenges and work to expand your prowess for the same reason. You’ve written tight and clean code for at least a few years, and your technical skills are on par with those who write code all day, every day. Additionally, your customer-facing and project management skills are solid.</p>\n<p>\n\tStatsopt is not a systems integration consultant. We’re a product company, which means that we’re not tracking our hours at the client site to make sure we’re profitable. And, in fact, we don’t track hours at all. Our team puts in the time to get the job done and we know when it’s time to decompress. We encourage our team towards technical strength, efficiency, and fun.</p>\n<p>\n\tThis position is based in London with frequent travel to our clients throughout Europe, including the occasional trip to our head office in Palo Alto, CA.</p>\n<b>Responsibilities</b>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tIndependently decompose and solve complex client problems with very little direction</li><li>\n\t\tArchitect and implement new systems at the client site, or at our home office</li><li>\n\t\tBuild new applications within the Statsopt platform</li><li>\n\t\tWrite scripts and programs to integrate large data sources into Statsopt</li><li>\n\t\tBuild complex data pipelines to bring together disparate data; this will allow unprecedented questions to be answered</li></ul>\n<b>Requirements</b>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tBA/BS from a top university in Engineering/CS, Sciences or Mathematics</li><li>\n\t\tExperience with a high level programming language (e.g Java, C++, C#, Scala)</li><li>\n\t\tProficiency with scripting languages such as Ruby, Groovy, Python, and Bash</li><li>\n\t\tStrong Unix/ Linux background</li><li>\n\t\tAbility to explain complex technical concepts to non-technical users</li><li>\n\t\tAgile project management experience</li><li>\n\t\tAbility to travel at least 25% of the time</li></ul>\n<b>Preferred</b>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tExperience working with databases, such as SQL and Oracle</li><li>\n\t\tUser design or user experience portfolio</li><li>\n\t\tWeb programming experience (e.g., Javascript) and/or an understanding of web technologies</li><li>\n\t\tCleared and un-cleared opportunities available</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYRCAA4"},"a0m80000005uOnlAAE":{"id":"a0m80000005uOnlAAE","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005uOnl","published_id":"a0m80000005uOnl","label":"Site Reliability Operations Analyst: Japan - Asia","name":"Site Reliability Operations Analyst: Japan","publishing_category":"Mission Operations","physical_location":"Tokyo, Japan","location":"Asia","description":"<p>Site Reliability Operations Analysts are the organizational backbone of a Statsopt deployment. We are the logistical dynamos who make sure that everything is in place at customer deployments so our engineers can do what they do best: solving the world&#39;s hardest problems. When things go wrong, we are the first-responders to the situation. We’re always improving ourselves and regularly take on tasks outside our wheelhouse, whether it’s learning new technical skills or navigating t