nown demands that are placed upon us. You will have the power to make your mark and to make a real difference in the lives of your colleagues and the success of the business by maintaining and improving our services.\n</p>\n<p>\n\t<b>Responsibilities</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li>Collaborate with fellow engineers on designing resilient, scalable network architecture</li><li>Solve complex network issues in production, colo, lab and customer environments</li><li>Deploy and scale network infrastructure with minimal downtime</li><li>Develop creative solutions to complex technological challenges</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<b>Requirements</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li>5+ years of Networking experience. Superior knowledge and hands-on experience of LAN (wired &amp; wireless), WAN, and Firewall environments; understanding of all OSI layers from application to physical.</li><li>Extensive experience with two or more of the following vendors: Cisco, Arista, Palo Alto Networks, Juniper.</li><li>Extensive experience with Layer 2 protocols and associated enhancements (LACP, L2 ECMP, 802.1d/w/s, 802.1x, 802.1Q, etc.).</li><li>Extensive experience with routing protocols and associated enhancements (BGP, OSPF, Anycast).</li><li>Experience with cloud hosting services (e.g. AWS or GCE) with regards to network peering, performance tuning and perimeter security.</li><li>Deep knowledge in one or more of the following areas:</li><li>VPN (GRE, IPSec/SSL VPNs,);</li><li>Wireless (802.1a/b/g/n/ac);</li><li>Datacenter Virtualization (ESX/KVM/OpenNebula, etc.);</li><li>Global and Local Server Load-Balancing (GLB/SLB);</li><li>Multicast (PIM-SM, MSDP, IGMP);</li><li>DNS/DHCP;</li><li>WDM (DWDM/CWDM).</li><li>Strong programming skills (Python preferred), expertise with Git, and expertise with REST or JSON APIs.</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<b>Preferred</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li>Experience with EMC SMARTS products.</li><li>Experience with Data Center design.</li><li>Experience with automation tools such as Puppet, Chef, etc.</li><li>Experience with radio resource management and similar Wireless troubleshooting skills.</li><li>TS/SCI security clearance or willingness to get cleared</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTBAA4"},"a0m80000005uIk9AAE":{"id":"a0m80000005uIk9AAE","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005uIk9","published_id":"a0m80000005uIk9","label":"Events Coordinator: New York - New York, NY","name":"Events Coordinator: New York","publishing_category":"Operations","physical_location":"New York, NY","location":"New York, NY","description":"<p>At Statsopt, we love events of all shapes and sizes. As an Event Coordinator you will bring mission critical events within Statsopt to life. You will play a crucial role in shaping externally facing events as well as the internal events that make Statsopt a fun and welcoming place for all of our employees to connect throughout the year.</p>\n\n<p>As the first Event Coordinator in the New York office, you are expected to be highly autonomous while still being able to work closely with business stakeholders and other operational teams to design and implement events in a first class way. Success in this position relies heavily on the ability to take ownership and manage multiple large projects, each with several moving parts and in multiple geographic locations. You must be able to adapt when sudden changes arise, take initiative in solving problems, and demonstrate impeccable organizational skills to ensure flawless execution.</p>\n\n<p>On the Events team, we have a broad mandate. This can span from helping our Recruiting team attract new talent and designing internal events for fostering connection to putting on conferences that boost our brand. As individuals we execute, as a team we ideate and position our events to help represent and enrich Statsopt. We want unconventional thinkers who value getting things done. If this is you, welcome.</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities </b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Schedule, execute, and coordinate all logistics for college, internal and industry-related events such as company info sessions, career fairs, holiday parties, tech talks, and conferences</li><li>Multi-plan high level events simultaneously</li><li>Troubleshoot level one technical problems</li><li>Operate independently and as a part of a team</li><li>Calculate and forecast event budgets</li><li>Anticipate problems and create contingency plans</li><li>Execute consistently under extremely tight deadlines</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>BA/BS</li><li>Excellent interpersonal skills both in person and by phone</li><li>Previous event coordination/support experience (please list in cover letter)</li><li>Experience with audio, sound, and technical AV</li><li>Must be able to work events from start to finish throughout the year which will include nights and weekends</li><li>Experience and willingness to do manual work for setup and teardown of events</li><li>Extremely well organized with a proven ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Ability to simultaneously be on track for events of varying scales and different timelines: daily, weekly, monthly, and annual projects</li><li>Willingness to travel up to 25% of time</li><li>Strong work ethic and ability to take on multiple projects at once</li><li>Ability to adapt quickly to new challenges and projects that may or may not be familiar</li><li>Skepticism of inertia and the status quo</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Preferred</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>2-5 years events industry experience</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYScAAO"},"a0m80000006UCSFAA4":{"id":"a0m80000006UCSFAA4","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006UCSF","published_id":"a0m80000006UCSF","label":"Communications Strategist - London - Europe","name":"Communications Strategist - London","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"London, United Kingdom","location":"Europe","description":"<p>Statsopt enables the world’s most important institutions to solve their hardest problems, but we can only scale our impact at these institutions if they understand our software, our people, and what we’re capable of accomplishing together. Communications Strategists play a critical role in enabling our Business Development team to deliver clear and compelling narratives about what we do.</p>\n\n<p>Communications Strategists own how Statsopt’s software, impact, and mission are communicated to external audiences. We collaborate with teams across the company to gain an in-depth understanding of our products, triage new business opportunities, and determine what message and what vehicle will resonate most strongly with a given audience. We work within Business Development to help customers understand the value Statsopt is creating for them and ways our software can be applied to new use cases and business units. We design new modes of communication when existing ones are insufficient. We develop content for proposals, marketing documents, and presentations. We manage highly-complex communications projects involving both internal and external counterparties. And we implement processes and structures that empower everyone on the Business Development team to deliver persuasive content quickly and effectively.</p>\n\n<p>This role is neither static nor easily defined. It changes as quickly as our company and our products. We are looking for people who will shape Statsopt’s Business Development communications, whether it’s figuring out the best way to describe our search technology on our website, designing a more efficient method to share communications products across Statsopt’s teams, or managing the development of a critical proposal for a federal agency. If you identify with any of these kinds of challenges, we’d love to talk to you.</p>\n\n<p>Here are a few “versions” of Communications Strategists that have worked well for us.</p>\n\n<p><b>Content Expert</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Research, write, and edit a