id":"a0m80000006TnCCAA0","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006TnCC","published_id":"a0m80000006TnCC","label":"Real Estate Project Manager - New York, NY","name":"Real Estate Project Manager","publishing_category":"Operations","physical_location":"New York, NY","location":"New York, NY","description":"<p>Statsopt’s Real Estate Analyst in Projects will oversee our physical build out efforts for new and existing office space. You will be the project manager for global construction projects, coordinating external contractors and vendors. Your projects will range from 5,000 to 100,000 square feet and you will own the entire process, ensuring that our offices are ready to operate on day one. When the inevitable challenges hit, you will be on top of things, making sure that the project is completed on time and within budget. This role is about creating a seamless process to ensure that our offices continue to rapidly grow without sacrificing quality or craftsmanship.</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Manage domestic and international construction projects</li><li>Collaborate with internal partners, including Finance, Legal, IT, and Security teams</li><li>Actively oversee external stakeholders, including architects, general construction, and third party firms</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>BA/BS in Construction Management or similar area of study</li><li>3+ years of Project Management experience in Real Estate, Design and Construction</li><li>Experience working with contractors, from bidding stages to reviewing the finished product</li><li>Experience with building and managing budgets and schedules</li><li>Experience with negotiating fees</li><li>Ability to travel 30-50% of the time</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Preferred</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Experience in a technology or start-up environment</li><li>Experience with tech build-out</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYUTAA4"},"a0m80000006UCSAAA4":{"id":"a0m800000