nt method to share communications products across Statsopt’s teams, or managing the development of a critical proposal for a federal agency. If you identify with any of these kinds of challenges, we’d love to talk to you.</p>\n\n<p>Here are a few “versions” of Communications Strategists that have worked well for us.</p>\n\n<p><b>Content Expert</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Research, write, and edit a wide range of Business Development communications products</li><li>Define how Statsopt’s software, impact, and mission are communicated to broad audiences and specific customers</li><li>Document new offerings and technologies through proposals, presentations, and marketing materials</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Communications Manager</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Design and execute communication plans for our most important deployments</li><li>Manage complex government proposals or product documentation projects involving multiple teams across Statsopt</li><li>Capture, document, and disseminate customer success metrics</li><li>Draft prose for targeted communications products in collaboration with other teams across Business Development</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Communications Designer</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Design new communications vehicles and products for customer or public consumption</li><li>Develop new templates in HTML, InDesign, and PowerPoint</li><li>Construct graphics and visuals for a range of communications products</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Exceptional communication skills</li><li>BA/BS (or MA/MS/JD/MBA/PhD) from a top university or equivalent experience</li><li>At least two years of experience (typically more) in a role that requires significant writing, communications design, communications strategy, and/or management of complex projects</li><li>Sample (not comprehensive) backgrounds: management consulting, public policy, law, government, technology, digital marketing, finance, data science</li><li>Ability to quickly grok technical concepts and thrive in a highly technical environment</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Location</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Palo Alto, New York, Washington DC, Los Angeles, London, and Canberra</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYRBAA4"},"a0m80000005XWTsAAO":{"id":"a0m80000005XWTsAAO","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005XWTs","published_id":"a0m80000005XWTs","label":"Deployment Strategist: D.C. - Washington, D.C.","name":"Deployment Strategist: D.C.","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Washington, D.C.","location":"Washington, D.C.","description":"<p>Deployment Strategists at Statsopt own the outcomes of all the work we do in Business Development. We begin with a vision: a vision of how software can transform people&#39;s relationship to data at the heart of a problem we care deeply about. We test that vision. Do our partners share it? Can we build what they need quickly enough? Will we be able to deploy it in the right environment, to the right people? Working side by side with our Forward-Deployed Software Engineers, we refine our vision, and then find our way to it: through messy data, through bureaucratic labyrinths, through sandstorms in &quot;data centers&quot; made of tents and suitcases. Whatever it takes, we figure out how to do it.</p>\n\n<p>A team of analysts at a customer site might want training for a tool we&#39;ve built. One of our customers&#39; CEOs might need help convincing another organization to share data. A team of developers might be asking for direction on which of a dozen feature requests they should prioritize this quarter. Or a global financial organization might be on the line, reeling from a recent compliance failure and asking us what we can do to help detect and prevent such behavior in the future. These, and a hundred other everyday scenarios, are where a Deployment Strategist thrives.</p>\n\n<p>This role doesn&#39;t come neatly packaged or defined. You should expect it to change during your time at Statsopt, to evolve as our organization evolves and as you do. When we interview Deployment Strategists, we aren&#39;t looking for people with a specific background. We&#39;re looking for people with exceptional analytic ability, creative brilliance, technical aptitude, and a gift for finding the details that matter. Most of all, we&#39;re looking for people who combine a calling to leave the world better than they found it with the resourcefulness necessary to realize that calling, no matter the circumstances.</p>\n\n<p>If that sounds like you, then we&#39;re interested.</p>\n\n<p>We look forward to hearing from you. You can scroll down for more specific examples of roles Deployment Strategists might take on.<br> </p>\n \n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PRODUCT OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>We&#39;re constantly building products at Statsopt. Some products are very specific to particular customer workflows—specialized geospatial visualization tools, for example, that might exist as part of a more generic map application. Others, such as a lightweight document reader, are deployed to tens of thousands of our users. All of these products have their roots in a particular customer&#39;s needs, where a team of Deployment Strategists and Forward-Deployed Software Engineers sat down together with our core developers and started work.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards product ownership have strong technical skills, compelling creative vision for what software can do, and an instinct for leadership. They apply those skills to leading a team that builds and supports a product: defining requirements, testing new versions, installing and configuring applications, sitting down with users and gathering feedback about what&#39;s working well and what isn&#39;t. They work across organizations and across internal teams, ensuring that we are all aligned on what we are building and why. Ultimately, they are responsible for ensuring that we deliver a product that truly transforms our customers&#39; ability to work with data.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PROJECT OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>Our partnerships with our customers are at the core of what we do. Our customers trust that we are the best in the world at building and delivering enterprise software. They trust that we mean it when we say we can enable collaboration across a worldwide enterprise without sacrificing security, or that in the event of a crisis we will surge the team that supports them just as they surge their own internal team. Fundamentally, our customers—whether they&#39;re looking for a missing child, an insurgent assembling a roadside bomb, or the source of a cyber attack on their network—trust that we care as deeply about their problems as they do.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards project ownership are the face of Statsopt, and the custodians of that trust. They pair a passion for software with excellent communication skills, an ability to navigate organizational hurdles, and an instinct for putting the right people in the right places. A project owner might spend the morning in meetings with customers to discuss the status of a data integration, the afternoon in a CTO&#39;s office talking about best practices in cyber security, and lunch in between at our headquarters brainstorming with a technical team about the best time to perform an upgrade. Ultimately, they are responsible for the strength of our partnerships: for ensuring that our customers are excited to work with us, and that we are excited to work with our customers.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PROCESS OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>The common thread across all of our work is data—lots of data. Organizations come to us when they no longer know how to make sense of the data they wish to inform their decisions, and while there are always differences, large and small, between different customers&#39; workflows in our software, there are also many areas of overlap.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards process ownership are experts in deploying software and making it work for human beings. They are brilliant, articulate, and generally deeply empathetic people. They excel at sitting down with a user and within minutes understanding exactly what he or she is trying to do--and at then synthesizing that understanding into a broader vision of what we can do to help them. That might mean building a new tool, or paring superfluous features out of an existing one. It might mean implementing certain standards in data curation or analysis. It might mean a series of training sessions, or the creation of an entirely new task force. Whatever the solution, they will own it, and will ensure that our customers benefit fully from everything we&#39;ve learned over the last decade of helping humans to navigate data.</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYS3AAO"},"a0m80000006TzZGAA0":{"id":"a0m80000006TzZGAA0","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006TzZG","published_id":"a0m80000006TzZG","label":"Infrastructure Quality Engineer - New York, NY","name":"Infrastructure Quality Engineer","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"New York, NY","location":"New York, NY","description":"<p>Statsopt Infrastructure Quality Engineers (IQEs) work on cross-functional product teams to ensure a successful, high-quality product releases. We are looking for energetic, highly motivated, and detail-oriented people with strong software skills to fill this role.</p>\n\n<p>As an IQE at Statsopt, you will help drive customer outcomes by iterating closely with our engineers across the business to define Statsopt’s world-class product. You will assess the server architecture of each release of our software to ensure that it operates flawlessly. You will take ownership of projects and responsibility for driving outcomes for our products. This can mean anything from designing and automating software tests based on expected uses and functional requirements to finding, filing, verifying, and solving issues and defects and providing extensive input to the software development process.</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Review and critique software specifications</li><li>Design and execute test cases using functional requirements</li><li>Automate existing tests and contribute new functionality to our automation framework</li><li>Find and file defects and verify fixed deficiencies</li><li>Maintain and administer robust enterprise software deployments</li><li>Work with developers to ensure successful, high-quality releases</li><li>Debug software and server issues</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Experience working with complex systems and the desire to understand them in detail (software, biological, mechanical)</li><li>Ability to thrive in a fast-moving environment with ad hoc objectives</li><li>Excellent teamwork, independent decision making, and communication skills</li><li>Analytical thinking, creative problem-solving, and troubleshooting skills with great attention to detail</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Preferred</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>BS in Engineering, Computer Science, or a related field</li><li>Experience coding in a major language such as Java or C</li><li>Firm grasp of testing methodologies, preferably backend and scale testing</li><li>Basic knowledge of version control systems such as git or Subversion</li><li>Linux systems administration experience</li><li>Strong scripting abilities</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTVAA4"},"a0m80000006WQBMAA4":{"id":"a0m80000006WQBMAA4","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006WQBM","published_id":"a0m80000006WQBM","label":"Business Development Operations Analyst - New York, NY","name":"Business Development Operations Analyst","publishing_category":"Mission Operations","physical_location":"New York, NY","location":"New York, NY","description":"<p>Business Development Operations Analysts are experts in implementation and execution. Our specialty is high-level logistics – from event management to vendor relationships, budgeting to hardware procurement, travel support to basic technical troubleshooting – we do it all and we do it well.</p>\n\n<p>We own projects from end-to-end and are willing to do whatever it takes to achieve the objective at hand. We work on extremely tight timelines and thrive under pressure. We are capable of running a project in its entirety, from broader project planning right down to the small details. We work hard, have fun, and, most importantly, we get it done. </p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Support a wide range of Business Development projects with an emphasis on responsiveness and adaptability </li><li>Plan and execute projects related to event management, vendor relationships, logistical planning, logistical execution, project budgeting/forecasting, and more</li><li>Anticipate operational requirements of the business and fulfill them as rapidly as possible</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>BA/BS</li><li>Ability to travel at least 50% of the time</li><li>Hard working, professional, and genuine</li><li>Extreme attention to detail</li><li>Previous experience in several of the following: Event management, vendor relations, project management, budgeting/forecasting, logistical planning/execution</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Preferred</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Willingness to be on-call 24/7</li><li>Willingness to learn new technical skills</li><li>Eager to take on new challenges and responsibilities</li><li>Ability to own several projects simultaneously under extremely tight deadlines</li><li>Ability to balance daily responsibilities with time-dependent high-priority tasks</li><li>Ability to anticipate problems before they happen and create contingency plans</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYReAAO"},"a0m80000003lcGcAAI":{"id":"a0m80000003lcGcAAI","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000003lcGc","published_id":"a0m80000003lcGc","label":"Engineering Team Lead - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Engineering Team Lead","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>\n\tWe need world-class engineering leads to develop our information exploration technologies and grow our engineering teams. The problem space includes everything from exploring huge information sets to presenting complex information in an easily digestible form for end-users.</p>\n<p>\n\tWe are looking for talented and passionate leads who love to code but understand the importance of helping individuals grow and who aren&#39;t intimidated by challenging problems. You should get as much enjoyment from having a member of the team make a critical breakthrough as you would if it were to be your own contribution. Moreover, you should be interested in pushing the envelope on not just the work we produce, but also the <i>way by which</i> we produce this work: <i>meta</i> should be your middle name.</p>\n<p>\n\tYou will be responsible for more than just people. The product will also be a core part of your duties and you will need to help the team make tradeoffs between functionality, time, and complexity. Having a keen product sense is important, being able to really get to know your audience and customers is critical. Finally, decentralized decision making must be something you encourage and foster in our culture.</p>\n<b>Requirements</b>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tBS/MS in Computer Science or equivalent (started or completed PhD a plus)</li><li>\n\t\tPrevious engineering leadership responsibilities a plus, but advanced contributors are required</li><li>\n\t\tEnthusiasm for solving interesting problems and a willingness to take on new product features</li><li>\n\t\tBackground in distributed systems, machine learning, information retrieval, data visualization and/or developing enterprise software systems a plus</li><li>\n\t\tInterest in working on a rapidly changing, ever-evolving system</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYSSAA4"},"a0m80000006JKPxAAO":{"id":"a0m80000006JKPxAAO","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006JKPx","published_id":"a0m80000006JKPx","label":"Linux Site Engineer - Australia","name":"Linux Site Engineer","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"Canberra, Australia","location":"Australia","description":"<p>The Site Reliability Tech Ops (SRT) is the technical backbone of a Statsopt deployment, allowing analyst and engineering resources to do what they do best: solve world-changing problems. We cover the technical aspects of site reliability, doing whatever&#39;s necessary to ensure things run smoothly and changes are implemented efficiently and with precision. SRTs are the customer&#39;s first point of contact for technical questions and concerns; we work hard to provide answers and solutions, and only escalate when absolutely necessary. We&#39;re the first-responders when problems arise, and proactively implement solutions to avoid recurrence. We strive for perfection in insulating our deployments against technical pitfalls, and have a boots-on-the-ground, ego-free approach to everything we do.</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Increase Statsopt deployment stability by constantly anticipating and exceeding engineer and client requirements</li><li>Ensure infrastructure and platform components are deployed and maintained with stability, scalability and security in mind</li><li>Identify and systematically eliminate common failure modes within applications and related infrastructure</li><li>Build and support enterprise-worthy operations, monitoring and configuration management tools</li><li>Monitor the health and uptime of the Statsopt stack and its dependencies</li><li>Be the face of technical operations for a deployment, both internally and for our clients</li><li>Constantly document technical implementation and configuration, and set an example for deployment resources to follow your lead</li><li>Be the first responder for customer problems, concerns or updates</li><li>Be independently responsible for a single deployment, but able to share best practices among the greater team</li><li>Apply Linux admin skills to administer and configure large distributed applications and clusters</li><li>Participation in 24/7 on-call rotation</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Expert-level Linux system admin abilities (CentOS or RHEL preferred - and no GUIs!)</li><li>Experience administering and managing distributed server environments, including hardware troubleshooting</li><li>Intermediate knowledge of database systems including Oracle, PostgreSQL and NoSQL technologies like Cassandra</li><li>Familiarity with a wide range of scripting languages such as Bash, Python or PHP</li><li>Familiarity with Linux system security best practices</li><li>Demonstrable knowledge of TCP/IP networking, routing and firewalls</li><li>Experience and interest in working in a highly-collaborative setting - sharing best practices, lessons learned and assisting where gaps exist</li><li>Interest in developing skills and tools that can be leveraged across the company</li><li>Ability to manage multiple, high-priority demands from separate sources at high quality with zero loss</li><li>Ability to communicate with both technical and non-technical personnel</li><li>Enthusiasm for working one on one with customers in an onsite or remote setting</li><li>Unbending commitment to operational security and ethics</li><li>Hard working and professional</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Preferred</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Experience with systems management tools like Puppet, CFEngine, Chef, SpaceWalk or Satellite</li><li>Experience with monitoring systems such as Nagios or Zenoss</li><li>Experience with common developer and code management tools like git, Stash, Jenkins and Eclipse</li><li>Experience with virtualization platforms such as VMware ESX or RHEV</li><li>Experience with cloud-based hosting platforms like AWS or Rackspace/OpenStack</li><li>Deep knowledge of TCP/IP networking, routing and firewalls</li><li>Security clearance or the ability to obtain one</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYUAAA4"},"a0m80000005wSIuAAM":{"id":"a0m80000005wSIuAAM","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005wSIu","published_id":"a0m80000005wSIu","label":"IT Network Engineer - New York, NY","name":"IT Network Engineer","publishing_category":"Information Technology","physical_location":"New York, NY","location":"New York, NY","description":"<p>The network is the core of any IT environment and allows the business to grow, adapt and contributes to its success. Being a member of the Networks team means you will be deeply involved in our mission to continue the evolution of Statsopt’s network services to prepare us for the known and unknown demands that are placed upon us. You will have the power to make your mark and to make a real difference in the lives of your colleagues and the success of the business by maintaining and improving our services.</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Collaborate with fellow engineers on designing resilient, scalable network architecture</li><li>Solve complex network issues in production, colo, lab and customer environments</li><li>Deploy and scale network infrastructure with minimal downtime</li><li>Develop creative solutions to complex technological challenges</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>5+ years of Networking experience. Superior knowledge and hands-on experience of LAN (wired &amp; wireless), WAN, and Firewall environments; understanding of all OSI layers from application to physical.</li><li>Extensive experience with two or more of the following vendors: Cisco, Arista, Palo Alto Networks, Juniper.</li><li>Extensive experience with Layer 2 protocols and associated enhancements (LACP, L2 ECMP, 802.1d/w/s, 802.1x, 802.1Q, etc.).</li><li>Extensive experience with routing protocols and associated enhancements (BGP, OSPF, Anycast).</li><li>Experience with cloud hosting services (e.g. AWS or GCE) with regards to network peering, performance tuning and perimeter security.</li><li>Deep knowledge in one or more of the following areas:</li><li>VPN (GRE, IPSec/SSL VPNs,);</li><li>Wireless (802.1a/b/g/n/ac);</li><li>Datacenter Virtualization (ESX/KVM/OpenNebula, etc.);</li><li>Global and Local Server Load-Balancing (GLB/SLB);</li><li>Multicast (PIM-SM, MSDP, IGMP);</li><li>DNS/DHCP;</li><li>WDM (DWDM/CWDM).</li><li>Strong programming skills (Python preferred), expertise with Git, and expertise with REST or JSON APIs.</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Preferred</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Experience with EMC SMARTS products.</li><li>Experience with Data Center design.</li><li>Experience with automation tools such as Puppet, Chef, etc.</li><li>Experience with radio resource management and similar Wireless troubleshooting skills.</li><li>TS/SCI security clearance or willingness to get cleared</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTBAA4"},"a0m80000006WQBRAA4":{"id":"a0m80000006WQBRAA4","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006WQBR","published_id":"a0m80000006WQBR","label":"Business Development Operations Analyst - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Business Development Operations Analyst","publishing_category":"Mission Operations","physical_location":"Palo Alto, 