orting</li><li>Collaborate with C-Level Executives, Finance, People Operations, Legal Ninjas, and other cross-functional teams to anticipate, implement and/or address equity compensation matters</li><li>Respond to inquiries from current, former and potential employees about equity compensation</li></ul>\n<p>\n<b>Requirements</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li>BA/BS in Business, Finance, Accounting, or a related discipline</li><li>Strong proficiency in Excel</li><li>Obsession for detail, organization, and ability to multitask</li><li>Entrepreneurial mindset, with proven ability to be resourceful, and experience improving and streamlining processes</li><li>Demonstrated ability to problem-solve and complete complex projects under pressure</li><li>Impeccable judgment, discretion, respect, and integrity</li><li>Ability to work independently and as a team member in an unstructured environment</li><li>Flexible schedule - we still operate in start-up mode and fire drills don&#39;t always fit within traditional business hours </li><li>Great sense of humor</li></ul>\n<p>\n<b>Preferred:</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li>1+ years of experience as a paralegal, equity professional or equivalent within a corporation or law firm</li><li>Knowledge of private company equity-related administration, accounting, tax and legal concepts</li><li>Strong working knowledge of Shareworks or similar equity administration software</li><li>Experience graphically representing data</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYSXAA4"},"a0m80000005wRCzAAM":{"id":"a0m80000005wRCzAAM","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005wRCz","published_id":"a0m80000005wRCz","label":"Recruiting Coordinator - Washington, D.C.","name":"Recruiting Coordinator","publishing_category":"Recruiting","physical_location":"Washington, D.C.","location":"Washington, D.C.","description":"<p>\nAs a Recruiting Coordinator at Statsopt, you will work closely with our Hiring Managers and Recruiters to ensure a positive interview experience for all candidates. We&#39;re looking for someone who is smart, resourceful, and who thrives under intense pressure. This position will rely heavily on your superb ability to manage multiple and competing priorities in a hectic environment. You will be part of a team that is responsible for developing, implementing, and executing on a broad recruiting strategy, with an emphasis on efficiency and overall value generation (i.e. hiring awesome people!).</p>\n<p>\n<b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n<ul><li>Schedule multiple interviews with candidates; coordinate all details of interviews including travel arrangements</li><li>Manage written and verbal communication with candidates and hiring managers throughout the interview process</li><li>Manage Applicant Tracking System (ATS) candidate records; create and run weekly tracking reports</li><li>Take on an array of special projects that advance the mission of our recruiting team</li><li>Requirements</li><li>Impeccable organizational skills and attention to detail</li><li>Superior time management and multi-tasking ability</li><li>Poise, superior professionalism and discretion</li><li>Strong analytical ability</li><li>Strong verbal and written communication skills</li><li>Excellent team player</li><li>Proactive approach to problem solving</li><li>Strong work ethic and willingness to take ownership for wide-ranging responsibilities</li><li>BA/BS required</li><li>At least 1 year of relevant experience, preferably in a technology start-up environment</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTcAAO"},"a0m80000006JAg0AAG":{"id":"a0m80000006JAg0AAG","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006JAg0","published_id":"a0m80000006JAg0","label":"Information Security Engineer (CIRT) - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Information Security Engineer (CIRT)","publishing_category":"Security","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>Our Information Security team is responsible for the 