, comfortable and proactive working in ambiguous situations, and can handle a high volume of visa applications at various stages. This position will focus on non-U.S. immigration, but may cover all aspects of immigration as needed.</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Prepare employment-based immigration petitions with minimal supervision</li><li>Engage with outside immigration counsel to initiate immigration applications</li><li>Provide continuous support to applicants and keep all stakeholders appraised of the progress</li><li>Establish process and workflows related to immigration applications</li><li>Partner closely with our Global Mobility Team to support inbound global immigration petitions and employee relocation requests</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>BA/BS or equivalent practical experience</li><li>2+ years of corporate immigration experience</li><li>Strong interpersonal and teamwork skills</li><li>Strong verbal and written communication skills</li><li>Experience with any of the following visas: UK Tier 2, Singapore EP, Australia 457, UAE work authorization, or other relevant global work authorizations</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Preferred</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Workday experience</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTGAA4"},"a0m800000063KJNAA2":{"id":"a0m800000063KJNAA2","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m800000063KJN","published_id":"a0m800000063KJN","label":"Business Continuity Specialist - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Business Continuity Specialist","publishing_category":"Security","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>There is a line that separates a safe, supportive environment from a dangerous, closed environment. Statsopt Security holds that line. Our goal as a team: provide and maintain a comfortable, open workplace without sacrificing our culture or safety. We have engineers, analysts and people who do a bit of everything; we lean heavily on that diversity of