ysical_location":"New York, NY","location":"New York, NY","description":"<p>Technical Instructors on our Business Development team design, develop, and teach classroom courses that will equip new hires and existing developers with the skills they need to successfully deploy and program against Statsopt&#39;s software platforms. As our second Technical Instructor, you will become a product expert who is adept at installing and maintaining a software stack and developing against our APIs. You will implement entirely new training curricula of your own design. You will teach Mission Specialists, Forward Deployed Engineers, and external partners how to perform their most common technical tasks, including data integrations, application development, ontology development, and more. You will provide them with the technical foundation they need to run their deployments with confidence.</p>\n\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\n\n<ul><li>Create course materials, including syllabi, exercises, lectures, and evaluation criteria</li><li>Teach classes at least twice a week</li><li>Provide desk-side support for individual trainees in need of further instruction</li><li>Collaborate with Education, Forward Deployed Engineering, and Software Engineering teams to determine course and curriculum needs and to keep courses relevant over time</li><li>Collaborate with the Support, Forward Deployed Engineering, and Software Engineering teams to acquire and maintain product expertise</li></ul>\n\n<h3>Requirements</h3>\n\n<ul><li>BS from a top university in Computer Science or equivalent, MS or PhD preferred</li><li>Experience teaching Computer Science in an academic or corporate environment</li><li>Strong object-oriented programming skills</li><li>Experience with scripting languages</li><li>Experience working with databases</li><li>Experience developing in a UNIX/Linux environment</li><li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills</li><li>Ease in communicating technical information to both technical and non-technical audiences</li><li>Ability to travel at least 25%-50% of the time</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTxAAO"},"a0m80000002LdDNAA0":{"id":"a0m80000002LdDNAA0","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000002LdDN","published_id":"a0m80000002LdDN","label":"Wordsmith - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Wordsmith","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Wordsmiths are a central part of Business Development at Statsopt. We collaborate with teams across the company to communicate our philosophy, mission, products, and impact to external audiences. On any given day, we’re writing a proposal to win a new contract, a presentation deck describing our impact at a customer, or a web-based description of a new product that our engineers have made possible.</span></span><br> <br><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Wordsmiths handle language the way our developers handle code, meaning we’re the best at what we do and perform with agility under pressure. We work alongside our engineers and developers to translate highly-technical and complex concepts into clear, concise, and powerful written products. Time is usually of the essence, so we’re always ready to craft documents and support projects on short notice.</span></span><br> <br><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">We are prose experts, but our work extends beyond writing itself to researching potential customers and understanding how they think about their problems. Our role also demands a deep understanding of our constantly evolving product and deployment landscape. Because we work with so many groups, Wordsmiths must be highly collaborative and willing to hold ideas loosely. We are constantly improving our internal processes and communication vehicles to ensure that our work reflects the broader mission.</span></span><br> <br><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Our backgrounds are diverse, but we all have a passion for the written word, drive for perfection, and commitment to execution. This position is available in Palo Alto; New York; Washington, DC; Los Angeles; Canberra; and London.</span></span><br> <br><b><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Responsibilities</span></span></b>\n<ul><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Communicate the core concepts of our business philosophy, mission, impact, and products to multiple audiences, including executives, policymakers, contracting officers, and the public</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Write responses, solo or collaboratively, to proposals and other solicitations from potential customers</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Write concept papers, presentation decks, and marketing documents to support customer outreach</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Identify new customers and opportunities in collaboration with the broader business development team</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Gain deep knowledge of our products and their applications to a variety of use cases</span></span></li></ul>\n <br><b><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Requirements</span></span></b>\n\n<ul><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">BA/BS (or MA/MS/JD/MBA/PhD) from a top university or equivalent experience</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Exceptional writing and editing ability</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Demonstrated communication and interpersonal skills</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Superior attention to detail</span></span></li></ul>\n <br><b><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Preferred</span></span></b>\n\n<ul><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Background in a technical field </span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Ability to travel on short notice</span></span></li></ul>\n\n<p> </p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYV2AAO"},"a0m80000005JZMHAA4":{"id":"a0m80000005JZMHAA4","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005JZMH","published_id":"a0m80000005JZMH","label":"Site Reliability Engineer: Canberra - Australia","name":"Site Reliability Engineer: Canberra","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"Canberra, Australia","location":"Australia","description":"<p>\nStatsopt software is deployed at the world’s most critical institutions to help them solve their greatest challenges. Users at customer sites from Washington, DC to Tokyo rely on Statsopt’s high availability to pursue their missions. Site Reliability Engineers (SREs) make sure our expanding number of customer deployments run smoothly 24 hours a day. \n</p>\n<p>\nSREs monitor and maintain Statsopt systems to pre-empt problems before they ever threaten our customers’ workflows. SREs combine engineering experience and an innate drive to improve existing systems and processes with the creativity to develop novel solutions to evolving challenges. Our team strives to automate processes whenever possible, using whatever tools are best for the job. Our responsibilities range from administering collocated servers (including hardware troubleshooting) to maintaining database platforms.\n</p>\n<p>\nWe work with a variety of teams to understand threats to our software and improve our products over time. We work side by side with Statsopt’s implementation teams and customer IT departments to understand our customers’ unique problems and develop innovative solutions. We document our successes and communicate them back to Statsopt’s product teams to advance the way our hardware, software, and network solutions are deployed to minimize failure rates and increase overall system reliability.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>REQUIREMENTS</b></p>\n<ul><li>5+ years of experience with Linux system administration (RHEL or CentOS preferred)</li><li>Experience with monitoring systems using tools like Nagios and writing health checks</li><li>Moderate experience with TCP/IP networking</li><li>Interest in learning and managing newer technologies like Spark, Hadoop, Elasticsearch, Node.js, and RabbitMQ</li><li>Ability to work independently with minimal supervision</li><li>Ability to participate in a 24/7 on-call rotation</li></ul>\n<p><b>PREFERRED</b></p>\n<ul><li>BS/MS in Computer Science</li><li>Experience with virtualization using AWS, VMWare ESX, KVM, Xen, or Docker</li><li>Experience with system management tools like Puppet or Chef</li><li>Ability to travel to customer sites up to 25% of time</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTJAA4"},"a0m80000005JMCPAA4":{"id":"a0m80000005JMCPAA4","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005JMCP","published_id":"a0m80000005JMCP","label":"Corporate/Securities Legal Ninja - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Corporate/Securities Legal Ninja","publishing_category":"Legal","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;\">Corporate/Securities Legal Ninjas are the legal backbone of our equity and corporate governance team. First and foremost, you’ll be an all-star contributor to the Legal Ninja team and to the company as a whole – working on every issue Statsopt faces, from negotiating partnership agreements with Fortune 50 companies to working on regulatory, intellectual property, employment and international issues.  However, you’ll also be a specialist, spending a considerable amount of your time working on corporate/securities issues, and interacting directly (and frequently!) with our General Counsel, CFO and CEO.  You will focus much of your time on financings, securities filings, board matters (including attendance at board meetings), and general stock/option administration. You will be comfortable independently negotiating complex deals and then crystallizing agreed upon terms in a written contract. You like taking ill-defined objectives and taking ownership to achieve epic outcomes.  You are funny and easy to get along with, and are able to quickly connect with a wide variety of personality types.  You are low ego, able to laugh at yourself, and can find enjoyment even in stressful situations.  You want to work at Statsopt because of our mission, not our valuation.  You are diligent, hardworking, and awesome.</span><br> <br><b>Responsibilities</b>\n<ul><li>Advise on a multitude of often complex, equity and securities issues (including financings, mergers and acquisitions, etc.)</li><li>Corporate governance for Statsopt and our subsidiaries</li><li>Lead contract drafting and negotiating</li><li>Assist in management and day-to-day administration of Statsopt’s equity portfolio</li></ul>\n <br><b>Requirements</b>\n\n<ul><li>2-10+ years as a corporate/securities attorney at a top firm or in-house (a combination is even better!)</li><li>BA/BS with a strong academic record from a top university</li><li>JD from a top law school</li><li>Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Experience with venture-backed financings, M&amp;A, corporate governance, board matters, and stock option administration</li><li>Extremely well organized with a proven ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Strong attention to detail</li><li>Available during nights and weekends as needed</li><li>Great sense of humor</li></ul>\n <br><b>Preferred</b>\n\n<ul><li>Experience in a start-up or high tech environment</li><li>Passion for technology</li></ul>\n ","website_job":"a2a80000000PYRkAAO"},"a0m80000003lhNdAAI":{"id":"a0m80000003lhNdAAI","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000003lhNd","published_id":"a0m80000003lhNd","label":"Site Reliability Engineer - Los Angeles, CA","name":"Site Reliability Engineer","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"Los Angeles, CA","location":"Los Angeles, CA","description":"<p>\nStatsopt software is deployed at the world’s most critical institutions to help them solve their greatest challenges. Users at customer sites from Washington, DC to Tokyo rely on Statsopt’s high availability to pursue their missions. Site Reliability Engineers (SREs) make sure our expanding number of customer deployments run smoothly 24 hours a day. \n</p>\n<p>\nSREs monitor and maintain Statsopt systems to pre-empt problems before they ever threaten our customers’ workflows. SREs combine engineering experience and an innate drive to improve existing systems and processes with the creativity to develop novel solutions to evolving challenges. Our team strives to automate processes whenever possible, using whatever tools are best for the job. Our responsibilities range from administering collocated servers (including hardware troubleshooting) to maintaining database platforms.\n</p>\n<p>\nWe work with a variety of teams to understand threats to our software and improve our products over time. We work side by side with Statsopt’s implementation teams and customer IT departments to understand our customers’ unique problems and develop innovative solutions. We document our successes and communicate them back to Statsopt’s product teams to advance the way our hardware, software, and network solutions are deployed to minimize failure rates and increase overall system reliability.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>REQUIREMENTS</b></p>\n<ul><li>5+ years of experience with Linux system administration (RHEL or CentOS preferred)</li><li>Experience with monitoring systems using tools like Nagios and writing health checks</li><li>Moderate experience with TCP/IP networking</li><li>Interest in learning and managing newer technologies like Spark, Hadoop, Elasticsearch, Node.js, and RabbitMQ</li><li>Ability to work independently with minimal supervision</li><li>Ability to participate in a 24/7 on-call rotation</li></ul>\n<p><b>PREFERRED</b></p>\n<ul><li>BS/MS in Computer Science</li><li>Experience with virtualization using AWS, VMWare ESX, KVM, Xen, or Docker</li><li>Experience with system management tools like Puppet or Chef</li><li>Ability to travel to customer sites up to 25% of time</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTJAA4"},"a0m80000005JZNPAA4":{"id":"a0m80000005JZNPAA4","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005JZNP","published_id":"a0m80000005JZNP","label":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer: Denmark - Europe","name":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer: Denmark","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Copenhagen, Denmark","location":"Europe","description":"<p>\n\t<b>What We Do</b>\n</p>\n<p>\nForward Deployed Software Engineers (FDSEs) are responsible for the technical success of each of our deployments. They are full-stack developers who work side by side with our customers to lead technical implementation of our products. FDSEs understand our customers’ greatest pain points and design end-to-end solutions to address them. FDSEs solicit constant feedback on their work from both customers and colleagues, improving our products over time with rapid iteration cycles.\n</p>\n<p>\nFDSEs deploy cutting-edge technologies to solve our customers’ hardest problems. Projects often start with a nebulous question like “Why are we losing customers?” or “How can we more effectively identify instances of money laundering?” FDSEs are thought leaders and first movers in developing a solution, from high-level system design and prototyping to application development and data integration.\n</p>\n<p>\nFDSEs work with customers around the world, where they gain unique insight into the world’s most important industries and institutions. We help our customers detect insider trading, improve disaster relief, fight healthcare fraud, and more. Each mission presents different challenges, from the regulatory environment to the nature of the data to the user population. FSDEs work to accommodate all aspects of an environment to drive real outcomes for our customers. \n</p>\n<p>\n\t<b>Technologies We Use</b>\n</p>\n<p>\nOur approach is to deploy whatever technology is best to solve the problem at hand. This often means that we are learning from the bleeding edge of the open source community or developing our own tools. Recently, FDSEs have deployed:\n</p>\n<ul><li><b>Postgres, Cassandra, Hadoop,</b> and <b>Spark</b> for distributed data storage</li><li><b>Java</b> and <b>Groovy</b> for our back-end applications and data integration tools</li><li><b>Typescript, AngularJS, jQuery, Backbone, Underscore, Leaflet,</b> and <b>d3</b> for our web technologies</li><li><b>Python</b> for data science and machine learning</li><li><b>Internal frameworks</b> for our rapid iteration tools</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<b>What We Value</b>\n</p>\n<p>\nFDSEs are developers with a passion for using technology to achieve a larger goal.  They enjoy the challenge of solving an abstract problem and building or adopting the technology to do it. To support these goals, we value:\n</p>\n<ul><li><b>Collaboration:</b> We work with our customers, often on site, to understand and solve their problems.</li><li><b>Commitment:</b> We see projects through from beginning to end in spite of obstacles we may encounter. </li><li><b>Balance:</b> We do whatever is necessary to finish the job and trust one another to take the time we need, whether it&#39;s vacation or just a trip to the gym.</li><li><b>Communication:</b> We communicate complex technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences.</li><li><b>Improvement:</b> We push ourselves to grow and develop in new ways.</li><li><b>Impact:</b> We take on meaningful and challenging projects that change the world for the better.</li></ul>\n<p>\nExpected travel for the role varies by location. \n</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYRCAA4"},"a0m80000004k8e6AAA":{"id":"a0m80000004k8e6AAA","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000004k8e6","published_id":"a0m80000004k8e6","label":"Mission Ops - Systems Analyst: Canberra - Australia","name":"Mission Ops - Systems Analyst: Canberra","publishing_category":"Mission Operations","physical_location":"Canberra, Australia","location":"Australia","description":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\n\tStatsopt’s Mission Operations Systems Analysts are the first responders for our Business Development team on tough technical issues. Our duties range across the IT spectrum, from systems administration and hardware-building to conference technology and help desk support. Adaptability is key for us – we need to be able to talk fluently to both people and machines while working in any of several IT specialties. We fix whatever problem the rest of Business Development throws our way, and more importantly we do all we can to prevent problems from occurring to begin with. We’re the technical arm of Statsopt’s logistical team, and we approach every day with the proactive attitude that allows us to consistently exceed expectations.</p>\n<p>\n\t Responsibilities</p>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tProactively support the Business Development team with an emphasis on adaptability</li><li>\n\t\tCreate and maintain demo/training computers</li><li>\n\t\tDesign and deploy images on laptops, desktops, and servers</li><li>\n\t\tProvide troubleshooting service at all levels</li><li>\n\t\tCoordinate and support technical conference and tradeshow logistics</li><li>\n\t\tSimultaneously work on time-dependent projects in an extremely fast-paced environment</li><li>\n\t\tSupport the rest of the Mission Ops team as necessary</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t Requirements</p>\n<ul><li>\n\t\t2+ years experience in IT support or equivalent</li><li>\n\t\tBasic understanding of UNIX/Linux server management</li><li>\n\t\tStrong analytical and problem solving skills</li><li>\n\t\tAbility to adapt to new challenges and responsibilities</li><li>\n\t\tAbility to perform at a high level in high pressure situations</li><li>\n\t\tExtreme attention to detail</li><li>\n\t\tAbility to break down complex problems into actionable tasks</li><li>\n\t\tSkepticism of inertia and the status quo</li><li>\n\t\t10-15% travel with optional potential for up to 75%</li></ul>\n<p>\n\tPreferred</p>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tPrevious or current security clearance</li><li>\n\t\tSolid knowledge of UNIX/Linux server administration and configuration</li><li>\n\t\tProfessional experience with virtualization technology</li><li>\n\t\tIntermediate scripting ability</li></ul>\n<div style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n\t </div>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYS4AAO"},"a0m80000002JAMwAAO":{"id":"a0m80000002JAMwAAO","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000002JAMw","published_id":"a0m80000002JAMw","label":"Engineer, Product Support Team - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Engineer, Product Support Team","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>\nStatsopt’s Product Support Engineers are comprehensive product and API experts. We collaborate with our customers, business teams, and development teams, continually building upon and applying our deep technical knowledge and skills across our product suite at every level. \n</p>\n<p>\nFrom working with users and developers, both internal and external, we are deeply familiar with how users leverage and build on top of Statsopt&#39;s products, and use our accumulated experience and expertise to help drive their direction. We anticipate questions, solve problems, and implement solutions to help turn abstract goals into reality. \n</p>\n<p>\nSupport Engineers also spend their time working on projects that affect many parts of the organization, including automating processes, coding custom tools, contributing bug fixes to various products, advocating for features with the product team, and managing instances that are vital to the success of Statsopt.\n</p>\n<p>\nSupport Engineers solve important problems and provide tangible solutions in uniquely collaborative and creative ways; we are integral to the success of Statsopt.\n</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Responsibilities</strong>\n</p>\n<ul><li>Become a Statsopt Product Expert</li><li>Collaborate with the Forward Deployed Engineering and Product teams in the development and design of creative solutions for the field</li><li>Diagnose and resolve issues encountered in the field</li><li>Provide education and guidance on configuring and working with Statsopt products to prevent problems before they occur</li><li>Contribute to the end-to-end quality of the product by verifying fixes and advocating for improvements</li><li>Coordinate and manage customer contact for critical product issues </li><li>Ensure the success of our product by keeping Statsopt running across the globe</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Requirements</strong>\n</p>\n<ul><li>B.S./M.S. in Computer Science, Engineering, Information Systems, Math, Physics, or equivalent experience</li><li>Awesome problem solving skills and ability to break down complex concepts</li><li>Excellent analytical skills and attention to detail</li><li>Comfortable working in a fast moving environment with dynamic objectives</li><li>Ability to think creatively and define product and customer needs</li><li>Ability to work independently and make decisions under minimal supervision</li><li>Excellent teamwork and written/verbal communication skills</li><li>Experience coding with Java and/or web technologies a plus (e.g. HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Python/Ruby, Django/Flask/Ruby on Rails, etc.)</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYSIAA4"},"a0m80000005sXpFAAU":{"id":"a0m80000005sXpFAAU","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005sXpF","published_id":"a0m80000005sXpF","label":"Accounts Payable Specialist - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Accounts Payable Specialist","publishing_category":"Finance and Accounting","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>Solving the world’s hardest problems is no easy task. Our engineers often find themselves in the midst of combat zones, disaster relief efforts or even worse, boardrooms. AP Specialists ensure that our engineers have every tool they need to crack some of the most challenging and puzzling problems on the planet. We do this by managing numerous relationships with vendors across the country and around the globe that can provide our engineers with everything they need to make the world a safer place. As our company continues to grow, we are constantly thinking about how to improve and automate processes so we can continue providing amazing outcomes in even more places across the world.</p>\n\n<p>Please note this is a contract position.</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Assist the AP team with full-cycle accounts payable responsibilities (including but not limited to: invoice processing, maintaining vendor records, running payment reports according to payment schedules and reconciling vendor statements)</li><li>Process 200-300 invoices per week</li><li>Organize, receive and coordinate the processing of vendor invoices</li><li>Work with the treasury team to create weekly payment batches</li><li>Assist with month-end activities, accruals, reconciliation, preparing 1099s and audit support</li><li>Assist with ad-hoc requests</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Qualifications</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>AA/AS degree or equivalent experience in accounting</li><li>One year or more of related experience</li><li>Understanding of full cycle accounts payable</li><li>Knowledge of fundamental accounting related to accounts payable</li><li>Strong organization skills, attention to detail highly accountable</li><li>Strong interpersonal and professional communication skills</li><li>Experience with Excel, Word, and Outlook</li><li>Ability to prioritize and work in a deadline-sensitive and customer-service oriented environment</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYinAAG"},"a0m80000005urHAAAY":{"id":"a0m80000005urHAAAY","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005urHA","published_id":"a0m80000005urHA","label":"Infrastructure Quality Engineer, New Grad - New York, NY","name":"Infrastructure Quality Engineer, New Grad","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"New York, NY","location":"New York, NY","description":"<p>\nStatsopt Infrastructure Quality Engineers (IQEs) work on cross-functional product teams to ensure a successful, high-quality product releases. We are looking for energetic, highly motivated, and detail-oriented people with strong software skills to fill this role.\n</p>\n<p>\nAs an IQE at Statsopt, you will help drive customer outcomes by iterating closely with our engineers across the business to define Statsopt’s world-class product. You will assess the server architecture of each release of our software to ensure that it operates flawlessly. You will take ownership of projects and responsibility for driving outcomes for our products. This can mean anything from designing and automating software tests based on expected uses and functional requirements to finding, filing, verifying, and solving issues and defects and providing extensive input to the software development process.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n<ul><li>Review and critique software specifications</li><li>Design and execute test cases using functional requirements</li><li>Automate existing tests and contribute new functionality to our automation framework</li><li>Find and file defects and verify fixed deficiencies</li><li>Maintain and administer robust enterprise software deployments</li><li>Work with developers to ensure successful, high-quality releases</li><li>Debug software and server issues</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n<ul><li>Experience working with complex systems and the desire to understand them in detail (software, biological, mechanical)</li><li>Ability to thrive in a fast-moving environment with ad hoc objectives</li><li>Excellent teamwork, independent decision making, and communication skills</li><li>Analytical thinking, creative problem-solving, and troubleshooting skills with great attention to detail</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Preferred</b></p>\n<ul><li>BS in Engineering, Computer Science, or a related field</li><li>Experience coding in a major language such as Java or C</li><li>Firm grasp of testing methodologies, preferably backend and scale testing</li><li>Basic knowledge of version control systems such as git or Subversion</li><li>Linux systems administration experience</li><li>Strong scripting abilities</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTaAAO"},"a0m80000003RDCvAAO":{"id":"a0m80000003RDCvAAO","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000003RDCv","published_id":"a0m80000003RDCv","label":"Deployment Strategist: UAE - Abu Dhabi, UAE","name":"Deployment Strategist: UAE","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates","location":"Abu Dhabi, UAE","description":"<p>Deployment Strategists at Statsopt own the outcomes of all the work we do in Business Development. We begin with a vision: a vision of how software can transform people&#39;s relationship to data at the heart of a problem we care deeply about. We test that vision. Do our partners share it? Can we build what they need quickly enough? Will we be able to deploy it in the right environment, to the right people? Working side by side with our Forward-Deployed Software Engineers, we refine our vision, and then find our way to it: through messy data, through bureaucratic labyrinths, through sandstorms in &quot;data centers&quot; made of tents and suitcases. Whatever it takes, we figure out how to do it.</p>\n\n<p>A team of analysts at a customer site might want training for a tool we&#39;ve built. One of our customers&#39; CEOs might need help convincing another organization to share data. A team of developers might be asking for direction on which of a dozen feature requests they should prioritize this quarter. Or a global financial organization might be on the line, reeling from a recent compliance failure and asking us what we can do to help detect and prevent such behavior in the future. These, and a hundred other everyday scenarios, are where a Deployment Strategist thrives.</p>\n\n<p>This role doesn&#39;t come neatly packaged or defined. You should expect it to change during your time at Statsopt, to evolve as our organization evolves and as you do. When we interview Deployment Strategists, we aren&#39;t looking for people with a specific background. We&#39;re looking for people with exceptional analytic ability, creative brilliance, technical aptitude, and a gift for finding the details that matter. Most of all, we&#39;re looking for people who combine a calling to leave the world better than they found it with the resourcefulness necessary to realize that calling, no matter the circumstances.</p>\n\n<p>If that sounds like you, then we&#39;re interested.</p>\n\n<p>We look forward to hearing from you. You can scroll down for more specific examples of roles Deployment Strategists might take on.<br> </p>\n \n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PRODUCT OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>We&#39;re constantly building products at Statsopt. Some products are very specific to particular customer workflows—specialized geospatial visualization tools, for example, that might exist as part of a more generic map application. Others, such as a lightweight document reader, are deployed to tens of thousands of our users. All of these products have their roots in a particular customer&#39;s needs, where a team of Deployment Strategists and Forward-Deployed Software Engineers sat down together with our core developers and started work.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards product ownership have strong technical skills, compelling creative vision for what software can do, and an instinct for leadership. They apply those skills to leading a team that builds and supports a product: defining requirements, testing new versions, installing and configuring applications, sitting down with users and gathering feedback about what&#39;s working well and what isn&#39;t. They work across organizations and across internal teams, ensuring that we are all aligned on what we are building and why. Ultimately, they are responsible for ensuring that we deliver a product that truly transforms our customers&#39; ability to work with data.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PROJECT OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>Our partnerships with our customers are at the core of what we do. Our customers trust that we are the best in the world at building and delivering enterprise software. They trust that we mean it when we say we can enable collaboration across a worldwide enterprise without sacrificing security, or that in the event of a crisis we will surge the team that supports them just as they surge their own internal team. Fundamentally, our customers—whether they&#39;re looking for a missing child, an insurgent assembling a roadside bomb, or the source of a cyber attack on their network—trust that we care as deeply about their problems as they do.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards project ownership are the face of Statsopt, and the custodians of that trust. They pair a passion for software with excellent communication skills, an ability to navigate organizational hurdles, and an instinct for putting the right people in the right places. A project owner might spend the morning in meetings with customers to discuss the status of a data integration, the afternoon in a CTO&#39;s office talking about best practices in cyber security, and lunch in between at our headquarters brainstorming with a technical team about the best time to perform an upgrade. Ultimately, they are responsible for the strength of our partnerships: for ensuring that our customers are excited to work with us, and that we are excited to work with our customers.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PROCESS OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>The common thread across all of our work is data—lots of data. Organizations come to us when they no longer know how to make sense of the data they wish to inform their decisions, and while there are always differences, large and small, between different customers&#39; workflows in our software, there are also many areas of overlap.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards process ownership are experts in deploying software and making it work for human beings. They are brilliant, articulate, and generally deeply empathetic people. They excel at sitting down with a user and within minutes understanding exactly what he or she is trying to do--and at then synthesizing that understanding into a broader vision of what we can do to help them. That might mean building a new tool, or paring superfluous features out of an existing one. It might mean implementing certain standards in data curation or analysis. It might mean a series of training sessions, or the creation of an entirely new task force. Whatever the solution, they will own it, and will ensure that our customers benefit fully from everything we&#39;ve learned over the last decade of helping humans to navigate data.</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYS3AAO"},"a0m80000005cjoBAAQ":{"id":"a0m80000005cjoBAAQ","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005cjoB","published_id":"a0m80000005cjoB","label":"Visual Designer, Internship - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Visual Designer, Internship","publishing_category":"Design","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p> </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">A WORLD-CHANGING COMPANY</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">At Statsopt, we develop the world&#39;s leading products for data analysis and we deploy them against problems that truly matter — uncovering human trafficking rings, containing the spread of infectious diseases, combating fraud, stopping cyber attacks, protecting privacy and civil liberties, prosecuting complex financial crimes, providing relief to victims of natural disasters, and more.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">Sound exciting? We think so, too.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">THE DESIGN TEAM</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">The Statsopt Design team is responsible for creating the human experience of using our software, as well as the execution of our brand. We design everything from user interfaces, to immersive experiences in our buildings and events, all the way down to awesome illustrated teeshirts we&#39;re famous for. </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">We help to achieve connection and understanding. Our <i>users</i> must create knowledge from data in our software, potential <i>customers</i> and <i>candidates</i> need to understand and relate to the story of our company and the awesome work we do, and it&#39;s our job to help tell these stories. </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">We believe that everyone should have access to excellence in design — utility and beauty — in whatever form it takes. Designers are highly valued in the company for our vision, our ability to learn and adapt, and our creativity and inventiveness. We&#39;re growing rapidly, yet focused on creating a tight-knit group of people that enjoy each other’s company in an atmosphere that fosters trust, integrity, empathy, and growth. </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">THE VISUAL DESIGNER</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">Enterprise software should be beautiful and compelling. We are helping to bring a new level of quality to people who have never had access to well-designed software at work: scientists, relief workers, civil servants, healthcare workers, and homicide detectives, just to name a few. Visual Designers have the space and the freedom to think deeply and holistically about the visual languages we use. We pay critical attention to typographic hierarchies, readability, space, color, tone, and balance.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">A great Visual Designer knows that form informs function and usability — that the surface layer doesn&#39;t exist in a vacuum — and that means the partnership with the <a href=\"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000000iQpM\" target=\"_blank\">Product Designer</a> is a two-way conversation. We believe it is often important to have an owner for each of these facets. Dedicated roles help us ensure that we can meet the high bar of quality we’ve set for ourselves. Visual Designers own the look and feel of our products; together with <a href=\"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000000iQpM\" target=\"_blank\">Product Designers</a>, User Researchers, and Product Engineers, we refine and evolve the quality of all Statsopt software.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">WHAT WE VALUE</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">Excellent communication skills. You have a proven ability to build great relationships, and convey and debate design rationale. You are the person that people can’t wait to collaborate with.<br><br>Empathy, not ego. We strive to understand our users and we fight to empower them.<br><br>A profound love of engineers. Statsopt is an engineering company, and we get to work with some of the best in the world. Engineers realize our vision — and we realize theirs — and together we create software that our users love.<br><br>A highly iterative design process. We move fast, we listen, and we adapt. We rapidly incorporate feedback, and we relentlessly collaborate. You must be adept at giving and receiving critiques.<br><br>A mastery of tools. We move with ease across software and fidelity, depending on the task at hand. Sketch.app, Hand-coding, Photoshop, Illustrator, or Keynote — and good old-fashioned pencil and paper.<br> </p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTWAA4"},"a0m80000003lX9SAAU":{"id":"a0m80000003lX9SAAU","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000003lX9S","published_id":"a0m80000003lX9S","label":"Business Operations and Strategy - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Business Operations and Strategy","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p><i>“Statsopt Technologies will not help you share, message, pin, post or chat. It does not exist to make you more social or connected, or even to help advertisers get to you. Its technology is deeply geeky, its work secretive. Nonetheless, it’s one of the most valuable private tech companies in Silicon Valley.” </i> - <a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2014/06/01/business/unlocking-secrets-if-not-its-own-value.html?_r=3\" target=\"_blank\">New York Times, May 2014</a></p>\n\n<p>Statsopt transforms the way the world’s most important institutions use data to solve their toughest problems. We have helped European authorities <a href=\"https://www.Statsopt.com/wp-assets/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Impact_Study_Fighting_Child_Pornography.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">shut down child pornography rings</a>, US special operations <a href=\"https://www.washingtonian.com/articles/people/killer-app/\" target=\"_blank\">fight terrorist networks</a>, hedge funds <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-03-19/sac-retains-Statsopt-to-boost-surveillance-after-charges.html\" target=\"_blank\">prevent insider trading</a>, and biomedical researchers <a href=\"https://www.Statsopt.com/solutions/pharma/\" target=\"_blank\">search for the next life-saving therapy</a>. Are you ready to commit yourself to the tough, rewarding job of scaling Silicon Valley’s most mission-driven company through hypergrowth?</p>\n\n<p><b>What we do:</b> Statsopt has limitless opportunities for growth; our team exists to remove all obstacles to that growth. We analyze these obstacles, solve them, and ensure that they don’t happen again.</p>\n\n<p>We work with leaders across the company on an unmatched diversity of problems. We might be working with engineers to prioritize product features for billion-dollar deployments one month, helping business leaders think through realigning our organizational structure the following, and directly supporting customers as they analyze data using Statsopt’s software the next. No two days are the same.</p>\n\n<p><b>What you will experience:</b> You will be responsible for leading entire projects and owning their outcomes from start to finish. You will need to be innovative, self-motivated, collaborative, and capable of dealing with complex interpersonal dynamics. You will need to bring your qualitative and quantitative analytical skills to the fore as you drive outcomes within Statsopt’s contrarian culture. We’re not looking for strategists who just want to make PPTs. Strategy is important but means nothing without execution.</p>\n\n<p>You will be a part of a team of talented individuals who are just as passionate about supporting one another as they are about Statsopt’s mission. We operate in a high accountability, high expectation, iron-sharpens-iron environment where the goal is always to produce the best solution. Honesty and willingness to accept feedback are critical.</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Take ownership of projects that Statsoptians have identified as a top priority</li><li>Work across teams to engage stakeholders, deeply understand problems, and gather data</li><li>Diagnose complex problems and develop compelling, data-driven recommendations</li><li>Relentlessly and swiftly execute on those recommendations until stakeholders are satisfied</li><li>Take care of your teammates</li><li>Dedicate time for reflection to continually self-improve</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>BA/BS (or MA/MS) from a top university or equivalent experience</li><li>At least one year of experience (typically more) in a role that requires rigorous financial or business analytics and/or strategic thought</li><li>Sample (not comprehensive) backgrounds: Quantitative public policy &amp; nonprofit, bioinformatics, investment banking, private equity, data science</li><li>Intellectual curiosity and creativity</li><li>Ability to grow and execute on both tactical detail and the big picture</li><li>Not afraid of long hours; able to handle stress well and maintain a positive attitude</li><li>Adaptive and introspective; willing to learn, teach, lead, and follow</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYRoAAO"},"a0m80000002wl3rAAA":{"id":"a0m80000002wl3rAAA","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000002wl3r","published_id":"a0m80000002wl3r","label":"Wordsmith - New York, NY","name":"Wordsmith","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"New York, NY","location":"New York, NY","description":"<p><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Wordsmiths are a central part of Business Development at Statsopt. We collaborate with teams across the company to communicate our philosophy, mission, products, and impact to external audiences. On any given day, we’re writing a proposal to win a new contract, a presentation deck describing our impact at a customer, or a web-based description of a new product that our engineers have made possible.</span></span><br> <br><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Wordsmiths handle language the way our developers handle code, meaning we’re the best at what we do and perform with agility under pressure. We work alongside our engineers and developers to translate highly-technical and complex concepts into clear, concise, and powerful written products. Time is usually of the essence, so we’re always ready to craft documents and support projects on short notice.</span></span><br> <br><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">We are prose experts, but our work extends beyond writing itself to researching potential customers and understanding how they think about their problems. Our role also demands a deep understanding of our constantly evolving product and deployment landscape. Because we work with so many groups, Wordsmiths must be highly collaborative and willing to hold ideas loosely. We are constantly improving our internal processes and communication vehicles to ensure that our work reflects the broader mission.</span></span><br> <br><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Our backgrounds are diverse, but we all have a passion for the written word, drive for perfection, and commitment to execution. This position is available in Palo Alto; New York; Washington, DC; Los Angeles; Canberra; and London.</span></span><br> <br><b><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Responsibilities</span></span></b></p>\n\n<ul><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Communicate the core concepts of our business philosophy, mission, impact, and products to multiple audiences, including executives, policymakers, contracting officers, and the public</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Write responses, solo or collaboratively, to proposals and other solicitations from potential customers</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Write concept papers, presentation decks, and marketing documents to support customer outreach</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Identify new customers and opportunities in collaboration with the broader business development team</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Gain deep knowledge of our products and their applications to a variety of use cases</span></span></li></ul>\n <br><b><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Requirements</span></span></b>\n\n<ul><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">BA/BS (or MA/MS/JD/MBA/PhD) from a top university or equivalent experience</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Exceptional writing and editing ability</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Demonstrated communication and interpersonal skills</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Superior attention to detail</span></span></li></ul>\n <br><b><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Preferred</span></span></b>\n\n<ul><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Background in a technical field </span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Ability to travel on short notice</span></span></li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYV2AAO"},"a0m80000002wl3wAAA":{"id":"a0m80000002wl3wAAA","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000002wl3w","published_id":"a0m80000002wl3w","label":"Wordsmith - Washington, D.C.","name":"Wordsmith","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Washington, D.C.","location":"Washington, D.C.","description":"<span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: