nal skills</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTIAA4"},"a0m80000005ci4rAAA":{"id":"a0m80000005ci4rAAA","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005ci4r","published_id":"a0m80000005ci4r","label":"Product Quality Engineer, New Grad: London - Europe","name":"Product Quality Engineer, New Grad: London","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"London, United Kingdom","location":"Europe","description":"<p>\nStatsopt Product Quality Engineers (PQEs) work on our cross-functional Product teams to ensure successful, high quality product releases. This means that they do whatever is needed to deliver our products to people who need them the most. PQEs identify areas for improvement and take ownership of enhancement projects. We are looking for energetic, highly motivated, and detail-oriented engineers with strong software skills to fill this role. \n</p>\n<p>\nPQEs focus on the entire suite of Statsopt products, from applications for data visualization to our cutting-edge web components library. As a PQE, you will drive customer outcomes by iterating closely with engineers across the business to ensure a high-quality user experience for Statsopt products. You will triage engineering issues, design features to address customer use cases, evaluate the quality of these features with manual and automated testing, and debug software problems. \n</p>\n<p>\nPQEs are technical generalists who can ramp up on new projects quickly, effectively evaluate the state of a given product, and make multifaceted contributions to the codebase to guarantee best-in-class software solutions for our customers.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n<ul><li>BS in Computer Science, Mathematics, or a related field</li><li>Experience programming in at least one common language</li><li>Ability to think creatively to define product and customer needs</li><li>Experience working with complex systems (software, biological, mechanical)</li><li>Excellent analytical thinking skills and attention to detail</li><li>Excellent written and verbal communications skills</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYSsAAO"},"a0m80000005cjnIAAQ":{"id":"a0m80000005cjnIAAQ","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005cjnI","published_id":"a0m80000005cjnI","label":"Visual Designer - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Visual Designer","publishing_category":"Design","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p> </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">A WORLD-CHANGING COMPANY</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">At Statsopt, we develop the world&#39;s leading products for data analysis and we deploy them against problems that truly matter — uncovering human trafficking rings, containing the spread of infectious diseases, combating fraud, stopping cyber attacks, protecting privacy and civil liberties, prosecuting complex financial crimes, providing relief to victims of natural disasters, and more.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">Sound exciting? We think so, too.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">THE DESIGN TEAM</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">The Statsopt Design team is responsible for creating the human experience of using our software, as well as the execution of our brand. We design everything from user interfaces, to immersive experiences in our buildings and events, all the way down to awesome illustrated teeshirts we&#39;re famous for. </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">We help to achieve connection and understanding. Our <i>users</i> must create knowledge from data in our software, potential <i>customers</i> and <i>candidates</i> need to understand and relate to the story of our company and the awesome work we do, and it&#39;s our job to help tell these stories. </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">We believe that everyone should have access to excellence in design — utility and beauty — in whatever form it takes. Designers are highly valued in the company for our vision, our ability to learn and adapt, and our creativity and inventiveness. We&#39;re growing rapidly, yet focused on creating a tight-knit group of people that enjoy each other’s company in an atmosphere that fosters trust, integrity, empathy, and growth. </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">THE VISUAL DESIGNER</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">Enterprise software should be beautiful and compelling. We are helping to bring a new level of quality to people who have never had access to well-designed software at work: scientists, relief workers, civil servants, healthcare workers, and homicide detectives, just to name a few. Visual Designers have the space and the freedom to think deeply and holistically about the visual languages we use. We pay critical attention to typographic hierarchies, readability, space, color, tone, and balance.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">A great Visual Designer knows that form informs function and usability — that the surface layer doesn&#39;t exist in a vacuum — and that means the partnership with the <a href=\"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000000iQpM\" target=\"_blank\">Product Designer</a> is a two-way conversation. We believe it is often important to have an owner for each of these facets. Dedicated roles help us ensure that we can meet the high bar of quality we’ve set for ourselves. Visual Designers own the look and feel of our products; together with <a href=\"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000000iQpM\" target=\"_blank\">Product Designers</a>, User Researchers, and Product Engineers, we refine and evolve the quality of all Statsopt software.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">WHAT WE VALUE</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">Excellent communication skills. You have a proven ability to build great relationships, and convey and debate design rationale. You are the person that people can’t wait to collaborate with.<br><br>Empathy, not ego. We strive to understand our users and we fight to empower them.<br><br>A profound love of engineers. Statsopt is an engineering company, and we get to work with some of the best in the world. Engineers realize our vision — and we realize theirs — and together we create software that our users love.<br><br>A highly iterative design process. We move fast, we listen, and we adapt. We rapidly incorporate feedback, and we relentlessly collaborate. You must be adept at giving and receiving critiques.<br><br>A mastery of tools. We move with ease across software and fidelity, depending on the task at hand. Sketch.app, Hand-coding, Photoshop, Illustrator, or Keynote — and good old-fashioned pencil and paper.<br> </p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYUxAAO"},"a0m80000002jFCeAAM":{"id":"a0m80000002jFCeAAM","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000002jFCe","published_id":"a0m80000002jFCe","label":"Information Security Engineer - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Information Security Engineer","publishing_category":"Security","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>\nOur Information Security (Infosec) Team is responsible for the security of Statsopt&#39;s people, infrastructure, and customer deployments around the globe. Infosec Engineers are highly motivated team players with a dedication to security and technology. They thrive on solving problems and tackling new challenges.\n</p>\n<p>\nAs an Infosec Engineer, you&#39;ll provide crucial engineering support and guidance for the security infrastructure our employees rely on every day. You’ll help improve our security by thinking creatively about the types of threats we will face while developing and implementing innovative prevention and detection methods.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>RESPONSIBILITIES</b></p>\n<ul><li>Plan, build and deploy sustainable tools and infrastructure to detect and help triage malicious activity</li><li>Consult with internal teams on the best way to securely deploy infrastructure and applications</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>REQUIREMENTS</b></p>\n<ul><li>Strong, security-focused proficiency with Python</li><li>Experience writing micro-services and/or RESTful APIs</li><li>Broad exposure to the world of information security with deep understanding in a couple of areas</li><li>Experience working in a structured development environment (e.g., unit tests, a standard git workflow, coding standards, etc.) or the willingness to learn</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>PREFERRED</b></p>\n<ul><li>Familiarity with machine learning and potential applications to information security </li><li>Strong Java background</li><li>Experience with a CI framework like Travis or Jenkins</li><li>Experience with open source data processing frameworks like Kafka, Spark, Storm, etc.</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTLAA4"},"a0m800000036HFdAAM":{"id":"a0m800000036HFdAAM","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m800000036HFd","published_id":"a0m800000036HFd","label":"People Partner - Washington, D.C.","name":"People Partner","publishing_category":"People Operations","physical_location":"Washington, D.C.","location":"Washington, D.C.","description":"<p>The People Team at Statsopt works to ensure that all Statsoptians have the resources they need to be as effective as possible. We identify potential points of failure for our people and build the programs, policies, and processes to mitigate them. We create sustainable frameworks that scale with Statsopt as it expands to solve even more of the world’s hardest problems.</p>\n\n<p>Our People Partners wear a variety of hats to support operations across the People Team. This means that they own complicated projects from start to finish, with a focus on delivering the most impactful outcomes for life at Statsopt. People Partners easily move from articulating the broader context of a project—goals, tradeoffs, and outcomes—to collaborating with coworkers on sensitive issues with empathy and discretion.</p>\n\n<p>Generally, People Partners have a core area of expertise, either professionally or experientially, and are excited to bring their unique perspective to Statsopt. They thrive on designing new, scalable processes and procedures and are excited to teach us something new and help us develop new ways to deal with existing issues. </p>\n\n<p><b>What We Do:</b></p>\n\n\n<p>The People Partner will be responsible for:</p>\n<ul><li>Programs and projects, including autonomous execution, evaluation, and reporting of program statuses to key stakeholders</li><li>Performance, including the creation of proactive, repeatable, and scalable solutions </li><li>People and community, including providing guidance and advice on a variety of people management issues</li><li>Metrics, including the generation and analysis of people data</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>What We Value</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Collaboration: We build relationships and partnerships with all people and areas of the business to better understand and meet their needs.</li><li>Action: We proactively develop plans to achieve our desired outcomes, even in novel situations.</li><li>Organization: We assist hundreds of people and coordinate our workload so that no issues fall through the cracks.</li><li>Individuality: We each leverage our individual perspectives and areas of expertise to improve our team and Statsopt as a whole.</li><li>Iteration: We constantly give and receive feedback to ensure we’re always improving.</li><li>Standardization: We build processes and procedures that scale across the business to ensure that all Statsoptians enjoy a uniformly positive work experience.</li></ul>\n\n<p>We’re currently looking for someone to fill this position in our Washington, D.C. office, which will focus on local programs and issues while collaborating closely with team members around the world.</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTbAAO"},"a0m80000005rFRwAAM":{"id":"a0m80000005rFRwAAM","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005rFRw","published_id":"a0m80000005rFRw","label":"Wordsmith - Australia - Australia","name":"Wordsmith - Australia","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Canberra, Australia","location":"Australia","description":"<span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Wordsmiths are a central part of Business Development at Statsopt. We collaborate with teams across the company to communicate our philosophy, mission, products, and impact to external audiences. On any given day, we’re writing a proposal to win a new contract, a presentation deck describing our impact at a customer, or a web-based description of a new product that our engineers have made possible.</span></span><br> <br><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Wordsmiths handle language the way our developers handle code, meaning we’re the best at what we do and perform with agility under pressure. We work alongside our engineers and developers to translate highly