style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Background in a technical field </span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Ability to travel on short notice</span></span></li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYV2AAO"},"a0m80000002jFvFAAU":{"id":"a0m80000002jFvFAAU","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000002jFvF","published_id":"a0m80000002jFvF","label":"Scholarship for Women in Engineering - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Scholarship for Women in Engineering","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p><b>Eligibility Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Only undergraduate students may apply</li><li>Applicants should be able to demonstrate a strong focus in a science, technology, engineering, or math (STEM) field</li><li>Applicants should have completed at least one full academic year</li><li>Applicants must be currently enrolled at an accredited college or university</li><li>Applicants must intend to be active, full-time students during the 2015-2016 academic year</li><li>Applicants must be women</li><li>Applicants must be eligible to work in the United States</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Application process</b></p>\n\n<p>Please submit a copy of:</p>\n\n<ul><li>1. Current undergraduate transcript</li><li>2. Curriculum Vitae and/or professional resume (as relevant)</li><li>3. A thoughtful response to the following prompt (max. 500 words):</li><li>Describe a technical project you are currently working on, or have worked on in the past. This can be an individual or team project, completed in an academic or extra-curricular setting. We&#39;d like to hear about the problem, how you used technology to apply a practical solution, the impact of the project, and challenges you overcame along the way. Please limit your essay to 500 words or less.</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Workshop and Interview</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Scholarship finalists will interview at Statsopt’s headquarters in Palo Alto, CA (Statsopt will cover the cost of travel) to participate in a full day workshop with Statsopt engineers.</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Scholarship Award</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Several grants, ranging from $1,500 to $10,000, will be awarded for the 2015-2016 academic year.</li><li>The scholarships are awarded to recipients for one academic year only and are not available for extension or renewal.</li><li>Select finalists will complete a Statsopt internship in either Summer of Fall 2016.</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Deadlines:</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Applications are due August 31, 2015</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYisAAG"},"a0m80000002jHYNAA2":{"id":"a0m80000002jHYNAA2","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000002jHYN","published_id":"a0m80000002jHYN","label":"Financial Analyst - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Financial Analyst","publishing_category":"Finance and Accounting","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>The Financial Analytics team at Statsopt is a combination of engineers, entrepreneurs, and finance geeks, brought together by our passion for solving complex problems, building innovative models, and supporting data-driven transparency. The questions we ask evolve as quickly as our company grows, so what works today always needs to work better and smarter tomorrow. Our small team is full of creative self-starters, and we tackle unstructured problems every day with a lot of independence. Our roles are flexible and tailored to our superpowers; we analyze data using whatever program and method will generate the best results. Everything in our workplace is designed to let us rock a project from start to finish with no red tape to hold us back. This team resembles the rest of Statsopt, not anything you’ll find in traditional corporate finance.</p>\n<b>Responsibilities:</b>\n<ul><li>Seeking out unsolved problems and taking initiative to address them</li><li>Constantly iterating on projects to ensure they will scale with Statsopt&#39;s growth</li><li>Building models, dashboards, and systems from scratch</li><li>Collaborating with other Statsoptians, across the company and around the globe </li></ul>\n<b>Requirements:</b>\n    <ul><li>BA/BS or MA/MS in Engineering, Finance, Economics, Math, or another analytical field</li><li>Entrepreneurial mindset, with proven ability to be resourceful, and experience improving and streamlining processes</li><li>Strong experience with complex data modeling in at least one of the following: Excel, VBA, SQL, or MATLAB; familiarity with additional modeling platforms is always a plus</li><li>Demonstrated ability and desire to learn quickly, and make an impact</li><li>Ability to work independently and as a team member in an unstructured environment</li><li>Flexible schedule - we still operate in start-up mode and fire drills don&#39;t always fit within traditional business hours</li></ul>\n    <b>Preferred:</b>\n    <ul><li>Startup experience / work in a low structure high autonomy environment</li><li>Experience graphically representing data</li><li>Programming experience</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYSwAAO"},"a0m80000002jHYDAA2":{"id":"a0m80000002jHYDAA2","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000002jHYD","published_id":"a0m80000002jHYD","label":"Communication Designer - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Communication Designer","publishing_category":"Design","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p> </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">A WORLD-CHANGING COMPANY</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">Statsopt is a place where designers spend their days working on problems that matter. In our short history, we’ve empowered scientists monitoring the environment, prevented the spread of disease, taken down human trafficking networks, helped homeowners avoid foreclosure, prevented fraud in Medicare, and helped governments save billions.<br><br>Sound exciting? We think so.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">THE DESIGN TEAM</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">The Statsopt Design team is responsible for creating the human experience of using our software, as well as the execution of our brand. We design everything from user interfaces, to immersive experiences in our buildings and events, all the way down to awesome illustrated teeshirts we’re famous for.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">We help to achieve connection and understanding. Our <i>users</i> must create knowledge from data in our software, potential <i>customers</i> and <i>candidates</i> need to understand and relate to the story of our company and the awesome work we do, and its our job to help tell these stories.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">We believe that everyone should have access to excellence in design — utility and beauty — in whatever form it takes. Designers are highly valued in the company for our vision, our ability to learn and adapt, and our creativity and inventiveness. We’re growing rapidly, yet focused on creating a tight-knit group of people that enjoy each other’s company in an atmosphere that fosters trust, integrity, empathy, and growth.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">THE COMMUNICATION DESIGNER</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">Communication Designers create the brand touchpoints that connect us to our fellow employees, our customers, the media, and the world. We are a team of Graphic Designers, <a href=\"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005U8Bh\" target=\"_blank\">Motion Designers</a>, and Web Designers. We’re the authors of visual systems for branding, marketing, presentations, and events. We create infographics that help people understand data, diagrams that explain our technology, and illustrations that tell our most important stories.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">As a great Communication Designer, you exhibit stylistic breadth, attention to detail, and know how to balance beauty, clarity, and legibility. You have deep experience from prepress to pixels, and posses a supreme eye for detail in color, typesetting, and layout. You have a strong sense of spacing and rhythm, and you love paragraphs as much as you love symbols and letters.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">WHAT WE VALUE</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">Excellent communication skills. You have a proven ability to build great relationships, and convey and debate design rationale. You are the person that others can’t wait to collaborate with.<br><br>Empathy, not ego. We strive to understand our audience, and develop programs and assets that meet their needs.<br><br>A love of technology. Statsopt is an engineering company, and we get to work with (and have to help explain) complex and powerful technological concepts and many kinds of audiences.<br><br>A highly iterative design process. We move fast, we listen, and we adapt. We rapidly incorporate feedback, and we relentlessly collaborate. You must be adept at giving and receiving critiques.<br><br>A mastery of tools. We move with ease across software and fidelity, depending on the task at hand. Illustrator, Photoshop, InDesign, or Keynote — and good old-fashioned pencil and paper.</p>\n\n<p> </p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYRtAAO"},"a0m80000002MjHuAAK":{"id":"a0m80000002MjHuAAK","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000002MjHu","published_id":"a0m80000002MjHu","label":"Deployment Strategist - Australia","name":"Deployment Strategist","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Canberra, Australia","location":"Australia","description":"<p>Deployment Strategists at Statsopt own the outcomes of all the work we do in Business Development. We begin with a vision: a vision of how software can transform people&#39;s relationship to data at the heart of a problem we care deeply about. We test that vision. Do our partners share it? Can we build what they need quickly enough? Will we be able to deploy it in the right environment, to the right people? Working side by side with our Forward-Deployed Software Engineers, we refine our vision, and then find our way to it: through messy data, through bureaucratic labyrinths, through sandstorms in &quot;data centers&quot; made of tents and suitcases. Whatever it takes, we figure out how to do it.</p>\n\n<p>A team of analysts at a customer site might want training for a tool we&#39;ve built. One of our customers&#39; CEOs might need help convincing another organization to share data. A team of developers might be asking for direction on which of a dozen feature requests they should prioritize this quarter. Or a global financial organization might be on the line, reeling from a recent compliance failure and asking us what we can do to help detect and prevent such behavior in the future. These, and a hundred other everyday scenarios, are where a Deployment Strategist thrives.</p>\n\n<p>This role doesn&#39;t come neatly packaged or defined. You should expect it to change during your time at Statsopt, to evolve as our organization evolves and as you do. When we interview Deployment Strategists, we aren&#39;t looking for people with a specific background. We&#39;re looking for people with exceptional analytic ability, creative brilliance, technical aptitude, and a gift for finding the details that matter. Most of all, we&#39;re looking for people who combine a calling to leave the world better than they found it with the resourcefulness necessary to realize that calling, no matter the circumstances.</p>\n\n<p>If that sounds like you, then we&#39;re interested.</p>\n\n<p>We look forward to hearing from you. You can scroll down for more specific examples of roles Deployment Strategists might take on.<br> </p>\n \n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PRODUCT OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>We&#39;re constantly building products at Statsopt. Some products are very specific to particular customer workflows—specialized geospatial visualization tools, for example, that might exist as part of a more generic map application. Others, such as a lightweight document reader, are deployed to tens of thousands of our users. All of these products have their roots in a particular customer&#39;s needs, where a team of Deployment Strategists and Forward-Deployed Software Engineers sat down together with our core developers and started work.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards product ownership have strong technical skills, compelling creative vision for what software can do, and an instinct for leadership. They apply those skills to leading a team that builds and supports a product: defining requirements, testing new versions, installing and configuring applications, sitting down with users and gathering feedback about what&#39;s working well and what isn&#39;t. They work across organizations and across internal teams, ensuring that we are all aligned on what we are building and why. Ultimately, they are responsible for ensuring that we deliver a product that truly transforms our customers&#39; ability to work with data.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PROJECT OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>Our partnerships with our customers are at the core of what we do. Our customers trust that we are the best in the world at building and delivering enterprise software. They trust that we mean it when we say we can enable collaboration across a worldwide enterprise without sacrificing security, or that in the event of a crisis we will surge the team that supports them just as they surge their own internal team. Fundamentally, our customers—whether they&#39;re looking for a missing child, an insurgent assembling a roadside bomb, or the source of a cyber attack on their network—trust that we care as deeply about their problems as they do.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards project ownership are the face of Statsopt, and the custodians of that trust. They pair a passion for software with excellent communication skills, an ability to navigate organizational hurdles, and an instinct for putting the right people in the right places. A project owner might spend the morning in meetings with customers to discuss the status of a data integration, the afternoon in a CTO&#39;s office talking about best practices in cyber security, and lunch in between at our headquarters brainstorming with a technical team about the best time to perform an upgrade. Ultimately, they are responsible for the strength of our partnerships: for ensuring that our customers are excited to work with us, and that we are excited to work with our customers.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PROCESS OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>The common thread across all of our work is data—lots of data. Organizations come to us when they no longer know how to make sense of the data they wish to inform their decisions, and while there are always differences, large and small, between different customers&#39; workflows in our software, there are also many areas of overlap.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards process ownership are experts in deploying software and making it work for human beings. They are brilliant, articulate, and generally deeply empathetic people. They excel at sitting down with a user and within minutes understanding exactly what he or she is trying to do--and at then synthesizing that understanding into a broader vision of what we can do to help them. That might mean building a new tool, or paring superfluous features out of an existing one. It might mean implementing certain standards in data curation or analysis. It might mean a series of training sessions, or the creation of an entirely new task force. Whatever the solution, they will own it, and will ensure that our customers benefit fully from everything we&#39;ve learned over the last decade of helping humans to navigate data.<br><br><span style=\"\">Our offices are located in Canberra, Melbourne and Sydney. Please specify a location preference in your cover letter.</span></p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYS3AAO"},"a0m80000002te9hAAA":{"id":"a0m80000002te9hAAA","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000002te9h","published_id":"a0m80000002te9h","label":"Site Reliability Engineer - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Site Reliability Engineer","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>\nStatsopt software is deployed at the world’s most critical institutions to help them solve their greatest challenges. Users at customer sites from Washington, DC to Tokyo rely on Statsopt’s high availability to pursue their missions. Site Reliability Engineers (SREs) make sure our expanding number of customer deployments run smoothly 24 hours a day. \n</p>\n<p>\nSREs monitor and maintain Statsopt systems to pre-empt problems before they ever threaten our customers’ workflows. SREs combine engineering experience and an innate drive to improve existing systems and processes with the creativity to develop novel solutions to evolving challenges. Our team strives to automate processes whenever possible, using whatever tools are best for the job. Our responsibilities range from administering collocated servers (including hardware troubleshooting) to maintaining database platforms.\n</p>\n<p>\nWe work with a variety of teams to understand threats to our software and improve our products over time. We work side by side with Statsopt’s implementation teams and customer IT departments to understand our customers’ unique problems and develop innovative solutions. We document our successes and communicate them back to Statsopt’s product teams to advance the way our hardware, software, and network solutions are deployed to minimize failure rates and increase overall system reliability.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>REQUIREMENTS</b></p>\n<ul><li>5+ years of experience with Linux system administration (RHEL or CentOS preferred)</li><li>Experience with monitoring systems using tools like Nagios and writing health checks</li><li>Moderate experience with TCP/IP networking</li><li>Interest in learning and managing newer technologies like Spark, Hadoop, Elasticsearch, Node.js, and RabbitMQ</li><li>Ability to work independently with minimal supervision</li><li>Ability to participate in a 24/7 on-call rotation</li></ul>\n<p><b>PREFERRED</b></p>\n<ul><li>BS/MS in Computer Science</li><li>Experience with virtualization using AWS, VMWare ESX, KVM, Xen, or Docker</li><li>Experience with system management tools like Puppet or Chef</li><li>Ability to travel to customer sites up to 25% of time</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTJAA4"},"a0m80000002te9mAAA":{"id":"a0m80000002te9mAAA","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000002te9m","published_id":"a0m80000002te9m","label":"Site Reliability Engineer - Washington, D.C.","name":"Site Reliability Engineer","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"Washington, D.C.","location":"Washington, D.C.","description":"<p>\nStatsopt software is deployed at the world’s most critical institutions to help them solve their greatest challenges. Users at customer sites from Washington, DC to Tokyo rely on Statsopt’s high availability to pursue their missions. Site Reliability Engineers (SREs) make sure our expanding number of customer deployments run smoothly 24 hours a day. \n</p>\n<p>\nSREs monitor and maintain Statsopt systems to pre-empt problems before they ever threaten our customers’ workflows. SREs combine engineering experience and an innate drive to improve existing systems and processes with the creativity to develop novel solutions to evolving challenges. Our team strives to automate processes whenever possible, using whatever tools are best for the job. Our responsibilities range from administering collocated servers (including hardware troubleshooting) to maintaining database platforms.\n</p>\n<p>\nWe work with a variety of teams to understand threats to our software and improve our products over time. We work side by side with Statsopt’s implementation teams and customer IT departments to understand our customers’ unique problems and develop innovative solutions. We document our successes and communicate them back to Statsopt’s product teams to advance the way our hardware, software, and network solutions are deployed to minimize failure rates and increase overall system reliability.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>REQUIREMENTS</b></p>\n<ul><li>5+ years of experience with Linux system administration (RHEL or CentOS preferred)</li><li>Experience with monitoring systems using tools like Nagios and writing health checks</li><li>Moderate experience with TCP/IP networking</li><li>Interest in learning and managing newer technologies like Spark, Hadoop, Elasticsearch, Node.js, and RabbitMQ</li><li>Ability to work independently with minimal supervision</li><li>Ability to participate in a 24/7 on-call rotation</li></ul>\n<p><b>PREFERRED</b></p>\n<ul><li>BS/MS in Computer Science</li><li>Experience with virtualization using AWS, VMWare ESX, KVM, Xen, or Docker</li><li>Experience with system management tools like Puppet or Chef</li><li>Ability to travel to customer sites up to 25% of time</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTJAA4"},"a0m80000002iHWvAAM":{"id":"a0m80000002iHWvAAM","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000002iHWv","published_id":"a0m80000002iHWv","label":"Recruiting Coordinator - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Recruiting Coordinator","publishing_category":"Recruiting","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>\n\tAs a Recruiting Coordinator at Statsopt, you will work closely with our Hiring Managers and Recruiters to ensure a positive interview experience for all candidates. We’re looking for someone who is smart, resourceful, and who thrives under intense pressure. This position will rely heavily on your superb ability to manage multiple and competing priorities in a hectic environment. You will be part of a team that is responsible for developing, implementing, and executing on a broad recruiting strategy, with an emphasis on efficiency and overall value generation (i.e. hiring awesome people!).</p>\n<h3>\n\tResponsibilities</h3>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tSchedule multiple interviews with candidates; coordinate all details of interviews including travel arrangements</li><li>\n\t\tManage written and verbal communication with candidates and hiring managers throughout the interview process</li><li>\n\t\tManage Applicant Tracking System (ATS) candidate records; create and run weekly tracking reports</li><li>\n\t\tTake on an array of special projects that advance the mission of our recruiting team</li></ul>\n<h3>\n\tRequirements</h3>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tImpeccable organizational skills and attention to detail</li><li>\n\t\tSuperior time management and multi-tasking ability</li><li>\n\t\tPoise, superior professionalism and discretion</li><li>\n\t\tStrong analytical ability</li><li>\n\t\tStrong verbal and written communication skills</li><li>\n\t\tExcellent team player</li><li>\n\t\tProactive approach to problem solving</li><li>\n\t\tStrong work ethic and willingness to take ownership for wide-ranging responsibilities</li><li>\n\t\tBA/BS required</li><li>\n\t\tAt least 1 year of relevant experience, preferably in a technology environment</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTcAAO"},"a0m80000002yG8TAAU":{"id":"a0m80000002yG8TAAU","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000002yG8T","published_id":"a0m80000002yG8T","label":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer: Singapore - Asia","name":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer: Singapore","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Singapore City, Singapore","location":"Asia","description":"<p>\n\t<b>What We Do</b>\n</p>\n<p>\nForward Deployed Software Engineers (FDSEs) are responsible for the technical success of each of our deployments. They are full-stack developers who work side by side with our customers to lead technical implementation of our products. FDSEs understand our customers’ greatest pain points and design end-to-end solutions to address them. FDSEs solicit constant feedback on their work from both customers and colleagues, improving our products over time with rapid iteration cycles.\n</p>\n<p>\nFDSEs deploy cutting-edge technologies to solve our customers’ hardest problems. Projects often start with a nebulous question like “Why are we losing customers?” or “How can we more effectively identify instances of money laundering?” FDSEs are thought leaders and first movers in developing a solution, from high-level system design and prototyping to application development and data integration.\n</p>\n<p>\nFDSEs work with customers around the world, where they gain unique insight into the world’s most important industries and institutions. We help our customers detect insider trading, improve disaster relief, fight healthcare fraud, and more. Each mission presents different challenges, from the regulatory environment to the nature of the data to the user population. FSDEs work to accommodate all aspects of an environment to drive real outcomes for our customers. \n</p>\n<p>\n\t<b>Technologies We Use</b>\n</p>\n<p>\nOur approach is to deploy whatever technology is best to solve the problem at hand. This often means that we are learning from the bleeding edge of the open source community or developing our own tools. Recently, FDSEs have deployed:\n</p>\n<ul><li><b>Postgres, Cassandra, Hadoop,</b> and <b>Spark</b> for distributed data storage</li><li><b>Java</b> and <b>Groovy</b> for our back-end applications and data integration tools</li><li><b>Typescript, AngularJS, jQuery, Backbone, Underscore, Leaflet,</b> and <b>d3</b> for our web technologies</li><li><b>Python</b> for data science and machine learning</li><li><b>Internal frameworks</b> for our rapid iteration tools</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<b>What We Value</b>\n</p>\n<p>\nFDSEs are developers with a passion for using technology to achieve a larger goal.  They enjoy the challenge of solving an abstract problem and building or adopting the technology to do it. To support these goals, we value:\n</p>\n<ul><li><b>Collaboration:</b> We work with our customers, often on site, to understand and solve their problems.</li><li><b>Commitment:</b> We see projects through from beginning to end in spite of obstacles we may encounter. </li><li><b>Balance:</b> We do whatever is necessary to finish the job and trust one another to take the time we need, whether it&#39;s vacation or just a trip to the gym.</li><li><b>Communication:</b> We communicate complex technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences.</li><li><b>Improvement:</b> We push ourselves to grow and develop in new ways.</li><li><b>Impact:</b> We take on meaningful and challenging projects that change the world for the better.</li></ul>\n<p>\nExpected travel for the role varies by location. \n</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYRCAA4"},"a0m80000005WIhEAAW":{"id":"a0m80000005WIhEAAW","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005WIhE","published_id":"a0m80000005WIhE","label":"Full Stack Software Engineer, New Grad - New York, NY","name":"Full Stack Software Engineer, New Grad","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"New York, NY","location":"New York, NY","description":"<p><b>What Full Stack Software Engineers do:</b></p>\n\n<p>Our engineers are involved in all parts of the product lifecycle: brainstorming, design, prototyping, planning, execution, and shipping. We brainstorm to understand and explore the difficult problem spaces we tackle, and work with our talented team to come up with solutions for the hardest problems we discover (product, visual, and technical). We code (there is lots of coding), and finally, ship and own products that directly impact the world. We work with the cutting edge web technologies such as TypeScript, D3, Leaflet and Angular and are avid fans of open source (<a href=\"https://github.com/Statsopt\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/Statsopt</a>)</p>\n\n<p><b>Some highlights of our open source work:</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Linter for TypeScript: <a href=\"https://github.com/Statsopt/tslint\" target=\"_blank\">Click Here</a></li><li>Eclipse plug-in for TypeScript: <a href=\"https://github.com/Statsopt/eclipse-typescript\" target=\"_blank\">Click Here</a></li><li>Converter for CoffeeScript -&gt; TypeScript: <a href=\"https://github.com/Statsopt/coffeescript-to-typescript\" target=\"_blank\">Click Here</a></li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Technologies we use:</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>TypeScript for client and Java for our backend work</li><li>Common open source libraries and frameworks like jQuery, Angular, Leaflet and D3</li><li>Internal frameworks that we’ve crafted to serve our rapid iteration</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>What we value:</b></p>\n\n<ul><li><span>You are a highly skilled, budding software developer who can meet every technical challenge as they arrive and love to deep dive into technology. </span></li><li><span>You&#39;re inquisitive, and when you come across a difficult problem, you don&#39;t rest until you solve it.</span></li><li>You&#39;re cool with working with others. Our jobs aren’t done in a vacuum and everyone contributes to get the job done.</li><li>You’re not afraid to make mistakes because without challenge, you’re not learning.</li><li>Speaking of learning, you have a constant desire to grow and develop.</li><li>You care about great design, not only in the product and visual sense, but also in your code and technical architecture.</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTXAA4"},"a0m80000005daWcAAI":{"id":"a0m80000005daWcAAI","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005daWc","published_id":"a0m80000005daWc","label":"Product Expert: Sydney - Australia","name":"Product Expert: Sydney","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Sydney, Australia","location":"Australia","description":"<p>\nProduct Experts at Statsopt are the technical wizards who empower our customers to solve their most difficult analytical problems. We own every layer of our deployment: working with software, wrangling data, managing relationships, and most importantly solving whatever problem is put in front of us. Our role adapts to meet the needs of the moment.  We collaborate with our engineering team on the future of the platform while relaying concrete product timelines to our customers. We are the Swiss Army knives of Statsopt deployments who manipulate data with code to impact business outcomes for our customers.  We’re motivated by the scope and impact of the problems we solve; our work has a direct effect on the world and the success of Statsopt. We run with projects without needing to be managed, and we love that the success of our deployment rests on our shoulders.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n<ul><li>Conduct analysis and solve problems with customer data onsite</li><li>Deliver quantitative analysis based on modeling from first-principles</li><li>Translate business questions into data questions; ask: what are we doing to provide value?  What are the causes and what does it mean for the business?</li><li>Implement technical solutions at customer sites</li><li>Build a roadmap for the future of the product in conjunction with the engineering team</li><li>Manage relationships with customer stakeholders </li><li>Help build customer workflows and train users through these workflows; gather feature feedback and requirements for features under development</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n<ul><li>BA/BS in Engineering, Computer Science, Sciences, Statistics, or Mathematics (or equivalent work experience)</li><li>Familiarity with quantitative data analysis methods</li><li>Object-oriented programming skills</li><li>Ease in communicating with technical and non-technical personnel</li><li>Travel 50% of the time </li><li>Ability to work in teams while still leading projects solo</li></ul>\n<p>\nCover letter strongly preferred; please include examples of your technical aptitude, interesting projects you have managed or worked on in the past, and your analysis experience\n</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYUEAA4"},"a0m80000002LmUvAAK":{"id":"a0m80000002LmUvAAK","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000002LmUv","published_id":"a0m80000002LmUv","label":"Software Engineer (Internal Applications) - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Software Engineer (Internal Applications)","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>\n\t<strong>A world-changing company</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tAt Statsopt, we develop the world’s leading products for data analysis and we deploy them against problems that truly matter—uncovering human trafficking rings, containing the spread of infectious diseases, combating fraud, stopping cyber attacks, protecting privacy and civil liberties, prosecuting complex financial crimes, providing relief to victims of natural disasters, and more.</p>\n<p>\n\tSound exciting? We think so, too.</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>The Internal Applications team</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tBeing a member of Internal Applications is about solving problems for a scaling company. With our accumulated experience and insight across a myriad of technologies, our team shapes a suite of internal products that have a profound effect on the success of our teams. We anticipate the needs of Statsopt, solve emerging problems, and collaborate with our core teams to turn abstract goals into reality. This means being deeply involved in the creation of custom internal applications as well as bending third party products to our will. We own projects from beginning to end, see our work shift often, and relish in seeing our efforts immediately impact Statsopt.</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Internal Applications Engineer</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tOur apps make Statsopt more efficient and better-connected, and are critical to every team’s success. It’s on the Internal Applications Engineers to decide how best to solve the problems laid out in front of them. This role is for a builder – someone who can learn what our teams need, architect an app, design the interface, make the backend fast, and the code interoperable. They love working with users and owning the solution from the ideas-on-napkins phase all the way to deployment.</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Technologies we use</strong></p>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tRuby on Rails for flexible webapps</li><li>\n\t\tPython, Ruby, Groovy, and Bash for scripting tasks</li><li>\n\t\tJavascript and Coffeescript for client-side web work</li><li>\n\t\tCommon open-source frameworks like jQuery, AngularJS, Backbone.js, D3, Haml, and Sass</li><li>\n\t\tJava for making plugins</li><li>\n\t\tMySQL for storage</li><li>\n\t\tElasticSearch for searching</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<strong>What we value</strong></p>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tYou&#39;re cool with working with others. Our jobs aren’t done in a vacuum and everyone contributes to get the job done.</li><li>\n\t\tYou’re not afraid to make mistakes because without challenge, you’re not learning.</li><li>\n\t\tSpeaking of learning, you have a constant desire to grow and develop.</li><li>\n\t\tYou care about great design, not only in the product and visual sense, but also in your code and technical architecture.</li><li>\n\t\tYou are passionate about product craftsmanship, and can balance that with shipping something relevant.</li><li>\n\t\tYou move fast with a sense of urgency.</li><li>\n\t\tYou want to work on things that make an impact on the world.</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTwAAO"},"a0m80000006WcmpAAC":{"id":"a0m80000006WcmpAAC","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006Wcmp","published_id":"a0m80000006Wcmp","label":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer - Australia","name":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Sydney, Australia","location":"Australia","description":"<p><b>What We Do</b></p>\n\n<p>Forward Deployed Software Engineers (FDSEs) are responsible for the technical success of each of our deployments. They are full-stack developers who work side by side with our customers to lead technical implementation of our products. FDSEs understand our customers’ greatest pain points and design end-to-end solutions to address them. FDSEs solicit constant feedback on their work from both customers and colleagues, improving our products over time with rapid iteration cycles.</p>\n\n<p>FDSEs deploy cutting-edge technologies to solve our customers’ hardest problems. Projects often start with a nebulous question like “Why are we losing customers?” or “How can we more effectively identify instances of money laundering?” FDSEs are thought leaders and first movers in developing a solution, from high-level system design and prototyping to application development and data integration.</p>\n\n<p>FDSEs work with customers around the world, where they gain unique insight into the world’s most important industries and institutions. We help our customers detect insider trading, improve disaster relief, fight healthcare fraud, and more. Each mission presents different challenges, from the regulatory environment to the nature of the data to the user population. FSDEs work to accommodate all aspects of an environment to drive real outcomes for our customers.</p>\n\n<p><b>Technologies We Use</b></p>\n\n<p>Our approach is to deploy whatever technology is best to solve the problem at hand. This often means that we are learning from the bleeding edge of the open source community or developing our own tools. Recently, FDSEs have deployed:</p>\n\n<ul><li><b>Postgres, Cassandra, Hadoop,</b> and <b>Spark</b> for distributed data storage</li><li><b>Java</b> and <b>Groovy</b> for our back-end applications and data integration tools</li><li><b>Typescript, AngularJS, jQuery, Backbone, Underscore, Leaflet,</b> and <b>d3</b> for our web technologies</li><li><b>Python</b> for data science and machine learning</li><li><b>Internal frameworks</b> for our rapid iteration tools</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>What We Value</b></p>\n\n<p>FDSEs are developers with a passion for using technology to achieve a larger goal. They enjoy the challenge of solving an abstract problem and building or adopting the technology to do it. To support these goals, we value:</p>\n\n<ul><li><b>Collaboration:</b> We work with our customers, often on site, to understand and solve their problems.</li><li><b>Commitment:</b> We see projects through from beginning to end in spite of obstacles we may encounter.</li><li><b>Balance:</b> We do whatever is necessary to finish the job and trust one another to take the time we need, whether it&#39;s vacation or just a trip to the gym.</li><li><b>Communication:</b> We communicate complex technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences.</li><li><b>Improvement:</b> We push ourselves to grow and develop in new ways.</li><li><b>Impact:</b> We take on meaningful and challenging projects that change the world for the better.</li></ul>\n\n<p>Expected travel for the role varies by location.<br><br>Our offices are located in Canberra, Melbourne and Sydney. Please specify a location preference in your cover letter. </p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYRCAA4"},"a0m80000006Wdp4AAC":{"id":"a0m80000006Wdp4AAC","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006Wdp4","published_id":"a0m80000006Wdp4","label":"Deployment Strategist - Australia","name":"Deployment Strategist","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Sydney, Australia","location":"Australia","description":"<p>Deployment Strategists at Statsopt own the outcomes of all the work we do in Business Development. We begin with a vision: a vision of how software can transform people&#39;s relationship to data at the heart of a problem we care deeply about. We test that vision. Do our partners share it? Can we build what they need quickly enough? Will we be able to deploy it in the right environment, to the right people? Working side by side with our Forward-Deployed Software Engineers, we refine our vision, and then find our way to it: through messy data, through bureaucratic labyrinths, through sandstorms in &quot;data centers&quot; made of tents and suitcases. Whatever it takes, we figure out how to do it.</p>\n\n<p>A team of analysts at a customer site might want training for a tool we&#39;ve built. One of our customers&#39; CEOs might need help convincing another organization to share data. A team of developers might be asking for direction on which of a dozen feature requests they should prioritize this quarter. Or a global financial organization might be on the line, reeling from a recent compliance failure and asking us what we can do to help detect and prevent such behavior in the future. These, and a hundred other everyday scenarios, are where a Deployment Strategist thrives.</p>\n\n<p>This role doesn&#39;t come neatly packaged or defined. You should expect it to change during your time at Statsopt, to evolve as our organization evolves and as you do. When we interview Deployment Strategists, we aren&#39;t looking for people with a specific background. We&#39;re looking for people with exceptional analytic ability, creative brilliance, technical aptitude, and a gift for finding the details that matter. Most of all, we&#39;re looking for people who combine a calling to leave the world better than they found it with the resourcefulness necessary to realize that calling, no matter the circumstances.</p>\n\n<p>If that sounds like you, then we&#39;re interested.</p>\n\n<p>We look forward to hearing from you. You can scroll down for more specific examples of roles Deployment Strategists might take on.<br> </p>\n \n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PRODUCT OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>We&#39;re constantly building products at Statsopt. Some products are very specific to particular customer workflows—specialized geospatial visualization tools, for example, that might exist as part of a more generic map application. Others, such as a lightweight document reader, are deployed to tens of thousands of our users. All of these products have their roots in a particular customer&#39;s needs, where a team of Deployment Strategists and Forward-Deployed Software Engineers sat down together with our core developers and started work.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards product ownership have strong technical skills, compelling creative vision for what software can do, and an instinct for leadership. They apply those skills to leading a team that builds and supports a product: defining requirements, testing new versions, installing and configuring applications, sitting down with users and gathering feedback about what&#39;s working well and what isn&#39;t. They work across organizations and across internal teams, ensuring that we are all aligned on what we are building and why. Ultimately, they are responsible for ensuring that we deliver a product that truly transforms our customers&#39; ability to work with data.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PROJECT OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>Our partnerships with our customers are at the core of what we do. Our customers trust that we are the best in the world at building and delivering enterprise software. They trust that we mean it when we say we can enable collaboration across a worldwide enterprise without sacrificing security, or that in the event of a crisis we will surge the team that supports them just as they surge their own internal team. Fundamentally, our customers—whether they&#39;re looking for a missing child, an insurgent assembling a roadside bomb, or the source of a cyber attack on their network—trust that we care as deeply about their problems as they do.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards project ownership are the face of Statsopt, and the custodians of that trust. They pair a passion for software with excellent communication skills, an ability to navigate organizational hurdles, and an instinct for putting the right people in the right places. A project owner might spend the morning in meetings with customers to discuss the status of a data integration, the afternoon in a CTO&#39;s office talking about best practices in cyber security, and lunch in between at our headquarters brainstorming with a technical team about the best time to perform an upgrade. Ultimately, they are responsible for the strength of our partnerships: for ensuring that our customers are excited to work with us, and that we are excited to work with our customers.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PROCESS OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>The common thread across all of our work is data—lots of data. Organizations come to us when they no longer know how to make sense of the data they wish to inform their decisions, and while there are always differences, large and small, between different customers&#39; workflows in our software, there are also many areas of overlap.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards process ownership are experts in deploying software and making it work for human beings. They are brilliant, articulate, and generally deeply empathetic people. They excel at sitting down with a user and within minutes understanding exactly what he or she is trying to do--and at then synthesizing that understanding into a broader vision of what we can do to help them. That might mean building a new tool, or paring superfluous features out of an existing one. It might mean implementing certain standards in data curation or analysis. It might mean a series of training sessions, or the creation of an entirely new task force. Whatever the solution, they will own it, and will ensure that our customers benefit fully from everything we&#39;ve learned over the last decade of helping humans to navigate data.<br><br><span>Our offices are located in Canberra, Melbourne and Sydney. Please specify a location preference in your cover letter.</span></p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYS3AAO"},"a0m80000006Wdk4AAC":{"id":"a0m80000006Wdk4AAC","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006Wdk4","published_id":"a0m80000006Wdk4","label":"Product Expert: London - Europe","name":"Product Expert: London","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"London, United Kingdom","location":"Europe","description":"<p>Product Experts at Statsopt are the technical wizards who empower our customers to solve their most difficult analytical problems. We own every layer of our deployment: working with software, wrangling data, managing relationships, and most importantly solving whatever problem is put in front of us. Our role adapts to meet the needs of the moment. We collaborate with our engineering team on the future of the platform while relaying concrete product timelines to our customers. We are the Swiss Army knives of Statsopt deployments who manipulate data with code to impact business outcomes for our customers. We’re motivated by the scope and impact of the problems we solve; our work has a direct effect on the world and the success of Statsopt. We run with projects without needing to be managed, and we love that the success of our deployment rests on our shoulders.</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Conduct analysis and solve problems with customer data onsite</li><li>Deliver quantitative analysis based on modeling from first-principles</li><li>Translate business questions into data questions; ask: what are we doing to provide value? What are the causes and what does it mean for the business?</li><li>Implement technical solutions at customer sites</li><li>Build a roadmap for the future of the product in conjunction with the engineering team</li><li>Manage relationships with customer stakeholders</li><li>Help build customer workflows and train users through these workflows; gather feature feedback and requirements for features under development</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>BA/BS in Engineering, Computer Science, Sciences, Statistics, or Mathematics (or equivalent work experience)</li><li>Familiarity with quantitative data analysis methods</li><li>Object-oriented programming skills</li><li>Ease in communicating with technical and non-technical personnel</li><li>Travel 50% of the time</li><li>Ability to work in teams while still leading projects solo</li></ul>\n\n<p>Cover letter strongly preferred; please include examples of your technical aptitude, interesting projects you have managed or worked on in the past, and your analysis experience</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYUEAA4"},"a0m80000006WdokAAC":{"id":"a0m80000006WdokAAC","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006Wdok","published_id":"a0m80000006Wdok","label":"Recruiter - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Recruiter","publishing_category":"Recruiting","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>As a Recruiter at Statsopt Technologies you will play a key role in helping to shape the organization¹s future by collaborating with colleagues across the company to consistently identify and attract brilliant people to our team. You will be constantly challenged to think creatively about how to drive hiring results. You will be part of a team that is responsible for developing, implementing, and executing a broad recruiting strategy, with a particular emphasis on sourcing high quality active and passive candidates.</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Partner with hiring managers to develop