ers in developing a solution, from high-level system design and prototyping to application development and data integration.</p>\n\n<p>FDSEs work with customers around the world, where they gain unique insight into the world’s most important industries and institutions. We help our customers detect insider trading, improve disaster relief, fight healthcare fraud, and more. Each mission presents different challenges, from the regulatory environment to the nature of the data to the user population. FSDEs work to accommodate all aspects of an environment to drive real outcomes for our customers.</p>\n\n<p><b>Technologies We Use</b></p>\n\n<p>Our approach is to deploy whatever technology is best to solve the problem at hand. This often means that we are learning from the bleeding edge of the open source community or developing our own tools. Recently, FDSEs have deployed:</p>\n\n<ul><li><b>Postgres, Cassandra, Hadoop,</b> and <b>Spark</b> for distributed data storage</li><li><b>Java</b> and <b>Groovy</b> for our back-end applications and data integration tools</li><li><b>Typescript, AngularJS, jQuery, Backbone, Underscore, Leaflet,</b> and <b>d3</b> for our web technologies</li><li><b>Python</b> for data science and machine learning</li><li><b>Internal frameworks</b> for our rapid iteration tools</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>What We Value</b></p>\n\n<p>FDSEs are developers with a passion for using technology to achieve a larger goal. They enjoy the challenge of solving an abstract problem and building or adopting the technology to do it. To support these goals, we value:</p>\n\n<ul><li><b>Collaboration:</b> We work with our customers, often on site, to understand and solve their problems.</li><li><b>Commitment:</b> We see projects through from beginning to end in spite of obstacles we may encounter.</li><li><b>Balance:</b> We do whatever is necessary to finish the job and trust one another to take the time we need, whether it&#39;s vacation or just a trip to the gym.</li><li><b>Communication:</b> We communicate complex technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences.</li><li><b>Improvement:</b> We push ourselves to grow and develop in new ways.</li><li><b>Impact:</b> We take on meaningful and challenging projects that change the world for the better.</li></ul>\n\n<p>Expected travel for the role varies by location.<br><br>Our offices are located in Canberra, Melbourne and Sydney. Please specify a location preference in your cover letter. </p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYRCAA4"},"a0m80000003EQQLAA4":{"id":"a0m80000003EQQLAA4","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000003EQQL","published_id":"a0m80000003EQQL","label":"Engineer, Product Support Team - New York, NY","name":"Engineer, Product Support Team","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"New York, NY","location":"New York, NY","description":"<p>\nStatsopt’s Product Support Engineers are comprehensive product and API experts. We collaborate with our customers, business teams, and development teams, continually building upon and applying our deep technical knowledge and skills across our product suite at every level. \n</p>\n<p>\nFrom working with users and developers, both internal and external, we are deeply familiar with how users leverage and build on top of Statsopt&#39;s products, and use our accumulated experience and expertise to help drive their direction. We anticipate questions, solve problems, and implement solutions to help turn abstract goals into reality. \n</p>\n<p>\nSupport Engineers also spend their time working on projects that affect many parts of the organization, including automating processes, coding custom tools, contributing bug fixes to various products, advocating for features with the product team, and managing instances that are vital to the success of Statsopt.\n</p>\n<p>\nSupport Engineers solve important problems and provide tangible solutions in uniquely collaborative and creative ways; we are integral to the success of Statsopt.\n</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Responsibilities</strong>\n</p>\n<ul><li>Become a Statsopt Product Expert</li><li>Collaborate with the Forward Deployed Engineering and Product teams in the development and design of creative solutions for the field</li><li>Diagnose and resolve issues encountered in the field</li><li>Provide education and guidance on configuring and working with Statsopt products to prevent problems before they occur</li><li>Contribute to the end-to-end quality of the product by verifying fixes and advocating for improvements</li><li>Coordinate and manage customer contact for critical product issues </li><li>Ensure the success of our product by keeping Statsopt running across the globe</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Requirements</strong>\n</p>\n<ul><li>B.S./M.S. in Computer Science, Engineering, Information Systems, Math, Physics, or equivalent experience</li><li>Awesome problem solving skills and ability to break down complex concepts</li><li>Excellent analytical skills and attention to detail</li><li>Comfortable working in a fast moving environment with dynamic objectives</li><li>Ability to think creatively and define product and customer needs</li><li>Ability to work independently and make decisions under minimal supervision</li><li>Excellent teamwork and written/verbal communication skills</li><li>Experience coding with Java and/or web technologies a plus (e.g. HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Python/Ruby, Django/Flask/Ruby on Rails, etc.)</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYSIAA4"},"a0m80000002yYHdAAM":{"id":"a0m80000002yYHdAAM","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000002yYHd","published_id":"a0m80000002yYHd","label":"Site Reliability Engineer - New York, NY","name":"Site Reliability Engineer","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"New York, NY","location":"New York, NY","description":"<p>\nStatsopt software is deployed at the world’s most critical institutions to help them solve their greatest challenges. Users at customer sites from Washington, DC to Tokyo rely on Statsopt’s high availability to pursue their missions. Site Reliability Engineers (SREs) make sure our expanding number of customer deployments run smoothly 24 hours a day. \n</p>\n<p>\nSREs monitor and maintain Statsopt systems to pre-empt problems before they ever threaten our customers’ workflows. SREs combine engineering experience and an innate drive to improve existing systems and processes with the creativity to develop novel solutions to evolving challenges. Our team strives to automate processes whenever possible, using whatever tools are best for the job. Our responsibilities range from administering collocated servers (including hardware troubleshooting) to maintaining database platforms.\n</p>\n<p>\nWe work with a variety of teams to understand threats to our software and improve our products over time. We work side by side with Statsopt’s implementation teams and customer IT departments to understand our customers’ unique problems and develop innovative solutions. We document our successes and communicate them back to Statsopt’s product teams to advance the way our hardware, software, and network solutions are deployed to minimize failure rates and increase overall system reliability.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>REQUIREMENTS</b></p>\n<ul><li>5+ years of experience with Linux system administration (RHEL or CentOS preferred)</li><li>Experience with monitoring systems using tools like Nagios and writing health checks</li><li>Moderate experience with TCP/IP networking</li><li>Interest in learning and managing newer technologies like Spark, Hadoop, Elasticsearch, Node.js, and RabbitMQ</li><li>Ability to work independently with minimal supervision</li><li>Ability to participate in a 24/7 on-call rotation</li></ul>\n<p><b>PREFERRED</b></p>\n<ul><li>BS/MS in Computer Science</li><li>Experience with virtualization using AWS, VMWare ESX, KVM, Xen, or Docker</li><li>Experience with system management tools like Puppet or Chef</li><li>Ability to travel to customer sites up to 25% of time</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTJAA4"},"a0m80000005rYZ9AAM":{"id":"a0m80000005rYZ9AAM","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005rYZ9","published_id":"a0m80000005rYZ9","label":"Finance Strategist - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Finance Strategist","publishing_category":"Finance and Accounting","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>\n\t<strong>Who we are:</strong>\n</p>\n<p>\nWe are data-obsessed and outcomes oriented. We employ this obsession to identify and execute on key internal and external workflows across the business. The questions we address evolve as rapidly as our company grows, so the strategy and solutions we create today need to work better and smarter tomorrow.\n</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Who we are looking for:</strong>\n</p>\n<p>\nYou are incredibly proactive and thrive in a dynamic environment. You’re comfortable taking on an entire workflow, becoming a topic expert, and operationalizing a plan. You’re creative in your approach and synthesis, and seek quality interactions with counterparties to achieve superior outcomes. You’re not satisfied just running Excel models or creating PowerPoint decks, you deeply consume analyses and help define outcomes. \n</p>\n<p> \n\t<strong>Responsibilities</strong>\n</p><ul><li>Proactively identify opportunities for increased data transparency</li><li>Work with financial, business, and field data</li><li>Create models to support data-driven decisions across the business</li><li>Build scalable and automated analyses</li><li>Help lead workflows that are a priority for the company</li><li>Engage Statsoptians across the business and empower them with data</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Requirements</strong>\n</p>\n<ul><li>Analytical and data-obsessed</li><li>Entrepreneurially minded (you can figure anything out)</li><li>Proven ability to take initiative in unstructured, autonomous environments</li><li>Highly adaptive, inquisitive and socially aware </li><li>Humble</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Other</strong>\n</p>\n<ul><li>BA/BS or MA/MS from a top tier University</li><li>Minimum 2 years of relevant work experience, 3-5 years preferred</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYSrAAO"},"a0m80000005tM8RAAU":{"id":"a0m80000005tM8RAAU","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005tM8R","published_id":"a0m80000005tM8R","label":"Infrastructure Quality Engineer, New Grad: London - Europe","name":"Infrastructure Quality Engineer, New Grad: London","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"London, United Kingdom","location":"Europe","description":"<p>\nStatsopt Infrastructure Quality Engineers (IQEs) work on cross-functional product teams to ensure a successful, high-quality product releases. We are looking for energetic, highly motivated, and detail-oriented people with strong software skills to fill this role.\n</p>\n<p>\nAs an IQE at Statsopt, you will help drive customer outcomes by iterating closely with our engineers across the business to define Statsopt’s world-class product. You will assess the server architecture of each release of our software to ensure that it operates flawlessly. You will take ownership of projects and responsibility for driving outcomes for our products. This can mean anything from designing and automating software tests based on expected uses and functional requirements to finding, filing, verifying, and solving issues and defects and providing extensive input to the software development process.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n<ul><li>Review and critique software specifications</li><li>Design and execute test cases using functional requirements</li><li>Automate existing tests and contribute new functionality to our automation framework</li><li>Find and file defects and verify fixed deficiencies</li><li>Maintain and administer robust enterprise software deployments</li><li>Work with developers to ensure successful, high-quality releases</li><li>Debug software and server issues</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n<ul><li>Experience working with complex systems and the desire to understand them in detail (software, biological, mechanical)</li><li>Ability to thrive in a fast-moving environment with ad hoc objectives</li><li>Excellent teamwork, independent decision making, and communication skills</li><li>Analytical thinking, creative problem-solving, and troubleshooting skills with great attention to detail</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Preferred</b></p>\n<ul><li>BS in Engineering, Computer Science, or a related field</li><li>Experience coding in a major language such as Java or C</li><li>Firm grasp of testing methodologies, preferably backend and scale testing</li><li>Basic knowledge of version control systems such as git or Subversion</li><li>Linux systems administration experience</li><li>Strong scripting abilities</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTaAAO"},"a0m80000005s9GpAAI":{"id":"a0m80000005s9GpAAI","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005s9Gp","published_id":"a0m80000005s9Gp","label":"Member of the Technical Staff - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Member of the Technical Staff","publishing_category":"Finance and Accounting","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>Statsopt is hiring mathematicians for a new team to solve some of the hardest problems the company and its customers face. The domains are diverse, but the problems all are ill-defined and require ingenuity in modeling. For example, is an observed pattern of behavior malicious? Where should patients optimally start their treatments? What is the value of a purely discretionary bonus? How should we price insurance for an event that has never occurred? Team members individually and in collaboration with one another decide how best to find answers often by interviewing domain experts, reviewing papers, and implementing novel techniques. The team is committed to delivering outcomes, even if sometimes those outcomes are akin to proofs of impossibility, and sees firsthand how the answers change decisions at Statsopt and its customers.</p>\n\n<p><b>What is Statsopt?</b></p>\n\n<p>Statsopt builds software platforms for integrating, managing, and securing data and creates associated applications for human-driven, machine-assisted analysis. Our products are used throughout the public, private, and non-profit sectors to help organizations implement solutions to critical problems, including: anti-fraud monitoring, crisis response, cyber security, defense, disease response, insurance analytics, law enforcement, pharmaceutical research, and trader oversight.</p>\n\n<p><b>Requirements:</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Ph.D. or equivalent degree in mathematics (dissertation still in progress acceptable).</li><li>Experience adapting techniques in research papers to specific problems.</li><li>Fluency in scientific programming (MATLAB, Python, R, SQL, etc.).</li><li>Willingness to work in Palo Alto, California.</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>How do you apply?</b></p>\nPlease submit an academic CV and cover letter here.","website_job":"a2a80000000PYixAAG"},"a0m80000005sxK3AAI":{"id":"a0m80000005sxK3AAI","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005sxK3","published_id":"a0m80000005sxK3","label":"Physical Security Operations Engineer - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Physical Security Operations Engineer","publishing_category":"Security","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>\nThere is a line that separates a safe, supportive environment from a dangerous, closed environment. Statsopt Security holds that line. Our goal as a team: Provide and maintain a comfortable, open workplace without sacrificing our culture or safety. We have engineers, analysts and people who do just a little bit of everything; we lean heavily on that diversity of skill to address a wide array of challenges with as deft a touch as possible. In a nutshell: When you do things right, people won&#39;t be sure you&#39;ve done anything at all.\n</p>\n<p>\nOur Physical Security team is responsible for the safety of Statsopt&#39;s people and offices around the globe. As a Security Operations Engineer, your technical expertise goes hand-in-hand with your passion for security--and your ability to adapt both to the needs of a software company ties them together. You&#39;re a highly-motivated team player that thrives on solving problems, tackling new challenges and growing with an organization.\n</p>\n<p>\nYou&#39;ll provide crucial operational support and guidance to the safety and security of a global organization while aiding in the development and implementation of innovative new prevention and detection methods. (If you immediately know what that sentence means: Congratulations. You are home.)\n</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Responsibilities</strong>\n</p>\n<ul><li>Act as subject matter expert on security systems</li><li>Implement, support and maintain specialized security systems</li><li>Identify and develop new solutions and technology to solve security challenges</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Requirements</strong>\n</p>\n<ul><li>Passion for security</li><li>Well-organized with a proven ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>BA/BS degree or equivalent practical experience</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Preferred </strong>\n</p>\n<ul><li>Strong experience implementing, configuring and integrating a variety of security solutions</li><li>Hands on experience with security systems including access control, digital surveillance and/or identity management solutions</li><li>Understanding of IP based security environments PMP, PSP or CPP</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTzAAO"},"a0m80000005rh7CAAQ":{"id":"a0m80000005rh7CAAQ","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005rh7C","published_id":"a0m80000005rh7C","label":"Talent Sourcer - New York, NY","name":"Talent Sourcer","publishing_category":"Recruiting","physical_location":"New York, NY","location":"New York, NY","description":"<p>\n\tYou&#39;re a motivated contributor with a track record of delivering results, and you deliver consistently without someone hanging over your shoulder. You&#39;re resourceful, creative, performance-oriented, and a researcher at heart. You have a hunter/gatherer mentality and are always up for a challenge. Your pulse on the competitive job market is at an expert level and you thrive in industry research. Combing the Internet, using Boolean Logic, x-raying, networking, and gathering referrals? Piece of cake! Doing what it takes to locate the best engineers in the world and deliver for your team? Naturally. You are a brilliant communicator, you understand technology, and you enjoy the continuous search for Talent.</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tFind the top talent in the world</li><li>\n\t\tPartner with hiring managers and recruiters to define technical roles</li><li>\n\t\tDevelop, implement, and manage tactical sourcing strategies for technical positions</li><li>\n\t\tAssist in driving local and worldwide candidate pipeline within the recruiting organization</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tBA/BS degree preferred</li><li>\n\t\t1-5 years of technical sourcing/research experience</li><li>\n\t\tMotivation and ambition</li><li>\n\t\tAbility to consistently offer innovative solutions to recruiting challenges within the broader context of the organization&#39;s priorities and approach to problem-solving</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYUZAA4"},"a0m80000006SC1dAAG":{"id":"a0m80000006SC1dAAG","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006SC1d","published_id":"a0m80000006SC1d","label":"Project Manager - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Project Manager","publishing_category":"Security","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>\nOur Information Security team is responsible for the security of Statsopt&#39;s people, data, and infrastructure around the globe. We strive to establish ourselves as thought leaders in the InfoSec community through innovative ideas and ruthless execution. As the business and organization continues to grow, the Project Manager becomes even more critical to the success of the InfoSec team.\n</p>\n<p>\nThis high impact role requires a high level of organization to track active key projects. Through careful planning you&#39;ll help ensure that engineers are successful in meeting the objectives of their projects in a timely manner. Your technical background will enable you to understand technical hurdles that the engineering team is facing. Ultimately, your success results in the mission&#39;s success.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n<ul><li>Partner closely with business and IT leads to develop a deep understanding of Statsopt&#39;s business goals, processes and technology limitations.</li><li>Design and run a machine to ensure that the InfoSec engineering team achieves their quarterly objectives for the organization.</li><li>Drive success of high impact projects by:</li><ul><li>Developing roadmaps with detailed milestones and potential risks. Breaking down the milestones into sprint sized efforts.</li><li>Holding engineers accountable and focused on their commitments stated in their roadmaps.</li><li>Unblocking engineers when necessary.</li><li>Communicating with internal customers on a regular basis to manage expectations.</li></ul><li>Capture signal on project progress and relevant metrics that measure impact and team efficiency. Report interesting trends to leadership and use data to improve the team.</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n<ul><li>Experience developing project roadmaps based on customer requirements.</li><l