pts to both technical and non-technical audiences.</li><li><b>Improvement:</b> We push ourselves to grow and develop in new ways.</li><li><b>Impact:</b> We take on meaningful and challenging projects that change the world for the better.</li></ul>\n\n<p><span style=\"\">Our Internships are hosted in Australia, in our Canberra office for three months, from December to March. We provide travel and housing assistance for interns moving to Canberra for the internship period.</span></p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYT1AAO"},"a0m80000003DCRxAAO":{"id":"a0m80000003DCRxAAO","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000003DCRx","published_id":"a0m80000003DCRx","label":"Site Reliability Ops - Los Angeles, CA","name":"Site Reliability Ops","publishing_category":"Mission Operations","physical_location":"Los Angeles, CA","location":"Los Angeles, CA","description":"<p>\nSite Reliability Operations Analysts (SROs) are the organizational backbone of a Statsopt deployment. We are the logistics experts who make sure that everything is in place so our engineers can do what they do best: solve the world&#39;s hardest problems. When things go wrong, we are the first responders. We strive for high-quality execution in everything we do.\n</p>\n<p>\nWe’re always improving ourselves and regularly take on tasks outside our wheelhouse, whether it’s learning new technical skills or navigating the procedural guidelines of many different clients. We field customer questions even if they&#39;re not within our expertise, and escalate the issue only after we’ve tried to solve it ourselves. We believe that the best idea wins, even if it&#39;s not our own.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n<ul><li>Help develop Statsopt deployments by anticipating employee and customer needs</li><li>Be a primary liaison for clients, including learning and adhering to customer processes and protocols</li><li>Provide first-level support for Statsopt software</li><li>Manage accounts and 