 and communication skills</li><li>Analytical thinking, creative problem-solving, and troubleshooting skills with great attention to detail</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Preferred</b></p>\n<ul><li>BS in Engineering, Computer Science, or a related field</li><li>Experience coding in a major language such as Java or C</li><li>Firm grasp of testing methodologies, preferably backend and scale testing</li><li>Basic knowledge of version control systems such as git or Subversion</li><li>Linux systems administration experience</li><li>Strong scripting abilities</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTaAAO"},"a0m80000005UC26AAG":{"id":"a0m80000005UC26AAG","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005UC26","published_id":"a0m80000005UC26","label":"Site Reliability Technical Analyst: UAE - Abu Dhabi, UAE","name":"Site Reliability Technical Analyst: UAE","publishing_category":"Mission Operations","physical_location":"Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates","location":"Abu Dhabi, UAE","description":"<p>\nThe Site Reliability Technical Analyst (SRT) is the technical backbone of a Statsopt deployment, allowing analyst and engineering resources to do what they do best: solve world-changing problems. We cover the technical aspects of site reliability, doing whatever&#39;s necessary to ensure things run smoothly and changes are implemented with efficiency and precision. SRTs are the customer&#39;s first point of contact for technical questions and concerns; we work hard to provide answers and solutions, and only escalate when absolutely necessary. We&#39;re the first-responders when problems arise, and proactively implement solutions to avoid recurrence. We strive for perfection in insulating our deployments against technical pitfalls, and have a boots-on-the-ground, ego-free approach to everything we do.\n</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Responsibilities</strong>\n</p>\n<ul><li>Increase Statsopt deployment stability by constantly anticipating and exceeding customer requirements</li><