g the technology to do it. To support these goals, we value:</p>\n\n<ul><li><b>Collaboration:</b> We work with our customers, often on site, to understand and solve their problems.</li><li><b>Commitment:</b> We see projects through from beginning to end in spite of obstacles we may encounter.</li><li><b>Balance:</b> We do whatever is necessary to finish the job and trust one another to take the time we need, whether it&#39;s vacation or just a trip to the gym.</li><li><b>Communication:</b> We communicate complex technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences.</li><li><b>Improvement:</b> We push ourselves to grow and develop in new ways.</li><li><b>Impact:</b> We take on meaningful and challenging projects that change the world for the better.</li></ul>\n\n<p>Expected travel for the role varies by location.</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYRCAA4"},"a0m80000006JAOLAA4":{"id":"a0m80000006JAOLAA4","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006JAOL","published_id":"a0m80000006JAOL","label":"Information Security Engineer (Threat Intelligence) - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Information Security Engineer (Threat Intelligence)","publishing_category":"Security","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>\nOur Information Security team is responsible for the security of Statsopt&#39;s people and infrastructure around the globe. As a member of the Information Security team, your technical expertise is second only to your professionalism and passion for security and technology in general. You&#39;re a highly motivated team player that thrives on solving problems and tackling new challenges.\n</p>\n<p>\nYou&#39;re tasked with understanding the past, and predicting the future of information security. You will analyze attacks, exploits, trends, and malware to understand the security landscape, and help Statsopt defend itself against the most dedicated attackers. Your work will provide important context to security events, and will enable network defenders to hunt for badness across our global network, wherever it may hide.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b>\n</p><p>Analyze malware, attacks, trends, and historical security events to understand the attacker landscape</p>\n<p>Analyze large data-sets to find valuable signal hiding in noise</p>\n<p>Assist defenders in hunting badness across our infrastructure</p>\n<p>Develop new and novel capabilities for prevention, detection, and deterrence</p>\n<p>Develop threat intelligence products for internal and external consumption</p>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n<p>Active security clearance or willingness and eligibility to obtain a security clearance</p>\n<p>Broad exposure to security disciplines and deep exposure in one or more (preferably including Digital Forensics or Incident Response)</p>\n<p>Advanced knowledge of the threat landscape and threat intelligence methodologies</p>\n<p>Strong investigative mindset with acute attention to detail</p>\n<p>Experience performing formal threat modeling</p>\n\n<p><b>Preferred</b></p>\n<p>Experience reverse engineering malware to develop signatures and countermeasures</p>\n<p>Experience with Yara or OpenIOC frameworks</p>\n<p>Experience performing offensive assessments, penetration testing, exploit development, or vulnerability analysis</p>\n<p>Experience with Python (Preferred), Perl, Ruby, C/C++, or Java</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTMAA4"},"a0m80000005udIeAAI":{"id":"a0m80000005udIeAAI","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005udIe","published_id":"a0m80000005udIe","label":"Finance Operations Analyst - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Finance Operations Analyst","publishing_category":"Finance and Accounting","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>Finance Operations Analysts are working hard to build and transform the financial infrastructure at Statsopt. We enable the finance team to improve business performance by actively improving operational effectiveness and efficiency. We do this by identifying problems and inefficiencies across the company and addressing them. Whether we’re building new financial models, systems, procedures or analyses, our goal is always to improve upon the old and create systems that will scale with Statsopt&#39;s exponential growth.</p>\n\n<p>We build things from the ground up and have a knack for getting in the weeds and fixing what’s broken. Our skillset is technical in nature and we have a vision for the future. We have a passion for creating and fixing, adoration for analysis, the foresight to see the 30,000 foot view, and the elbow grease to get down and dirty.</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Identify, destroy and re-build old systems that will not scale with Statsopt&#39;s Growth</li><li>Identify, track, and create new metrics to improve business processes through analysis</li><li>Create, implement, and track fiscal requirements across 20+ business sectors</li><li>Iterate on financial &amp; operational models built from scratch and then implement them</li><li>Seek out unsolved problems and taking initiative to address them</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>5-7 years of working experience within a large public accounting firm and/or an enterprise software company or in corporate FP&amp;A</li><li>BA/BS in Accounting, Finance, Economics, Engineering, or a related discipline</li><li>Strong knowledge of US GAAP, accruals, budgeting and systems</li><li>Strong verbal and written communication skills</li><li>Meticulous attention to detail and the ability to complete tasks with minimal oversight</li><li>Ability to multitask</li><li>Strong interpersonal skills</li><li>Strong proficiency with Excel and PowerPoint</li><li>Extremely hard worker, ethical, thoughtful, and most importantly, genuine</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYShAAO"},"a0m80000002LgTSAA0":{"id":"a0m80000002LgTSAA0","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000002LgTS","published_id":"a0m80000002LgTS","label":"Tax and International Accountant - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Tax and International Accountant","publishing_category":"Finance and Accounting","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>Statsopt is looking for an energetic, highly-skilled individual who will thrive in this entrepreneurial environment to manage our tax accounting and international accounting. This successful candidate will manage all tax operations, assist with international accounting and provide guidance on technical tax and foreign accounting issues that are relevant to our ordinary course of business.  This role will work directly with our Finance, PeopleOps and Legal teams to expand Statsopt’s global operations.</p>\n\n<p><b>Qualifications:</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s Degree or equivalent experience in Business Administration, Economics, Finance, Accounting, or related field</li><li>5+ years of working experience within a large public accounting firm and/or a small to mid-size <span>enterprise software company with a strong concentration in tax</span></li><li><span>Extensive experience in application of US GAAP </span></li><li>Foreign subsidiary and consolidations accounting experience</li><li><span>Highly skilled in the interpretation of tax accounting pronouncements as well as applicability to specific </span>technical accounting <span>transactions </span></li><li>Strong communication, analytical, and writing skills, including the ability to summarize key accounting and operational issues to management</li><li>Complex analytic problem solving and project management skills</li><li>Proficiency with Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, and PowerPoint)</li><li>Proficiency with NetSuite and/or other accounting systems</li><li><span>CPA is a plus, but is not required</span></li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities:</b></p>\n\n<ul><li><span>Manage all aspects of tax accounting; including </span>information gathering and analysis for all Federal, State and Local tax issues (e.g.: property tax, sales tax, use tax, franchise tax, oversight of unclaimed property reports/filings, preparing quarterly estimated corporate tax payments, and researching and responding to various state and local inquiries/notices)</li><li><span>Help manage the general ledger for all international subsidiaries and assist with monthly consolidation in accordance with intercompany agreements</span></li><li>Maintain high level of confidentiality and integrity of tax data</li><li>Become the central point of contact for all tax and international accounting issues</li><li><span>Coordinate with our external accountants on tax filings and footnotes for our audited financial statements</span></li><li><span>Provide technical guidance, training, and support to the </span>Finance, PeopleOps and Legal<span> teams</span></li><li><span>Work actively with external auditors to ensure compliance with all IRS and GAAP guidelines</span></li><li><span>Build cross-functional working relationships within the Company </span></li><li><span>Identify and implement continuous improvement initiatives related to tax, including reporting, data gathering, value added analysis and enhancement of existing processes for efficiency and effectiveness</span></li><li><span>Participate/lead various special ad hoc projects</span></li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Critical Success Factors: </b></p>\n\n<ul><li><span>High degree of forward thinking, partnering skills, personal integrity and motivation for results</span></li><li><span>Effective communication &amp; interpersonal skills and the ability to interact effectively and professionally with cross-functional teams</span></li><li>Strong interest in technology, innovation, civil liberties and national security</li><li><span>Entrepreneurial spirit and desire to meet deadlines in a rapidly growing environment</span></li><li><span>Strong analytical and problem solving skills </span></li><li><span>Attention to detail and organization skills </span></li><li><span>Ability to multi-task in a dynamic environment</span></li><li>Eligible to obtain clearance from the US Government</li></ul>\n\n<p><span> </span></p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYUsAAO"},"a0m80000000gguhAAA":{"id":"a0m80000000gguhAAA","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000000gguh","published_id":"a0m80000000gguh","label":"Product Expert: New York - New York, NY","name":"Product Expert: New York","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"New York, NY","location":"New York, NY","description":"<p>\nProduct Experts at Statsopt are the technical wizards who empower our customers to solve their most difficult analytical problems. We own every layer of our deployment: working with software, wrangling data, managing relationships, and most importantly solving whatever problem is put in front of us. Our role adapts to meet the needs of the moment.  We collaborate with our engineering team on the future of the platform while relaying concrete product timelines to our customers. We are the Swiss Army knives of Statsopt deployments who manipulate data with code to impact business outcomes for our customers.  We’re motivated by the scope and impact of the problems we solve; our work has a direct effect on the world and the success of Statsopt. We run with projects without needing to be managed, and we love that the success of our deployment rests on our shoulders.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n<ul><li>Conduct analysis and solve problems with customer data onsite</li><li>Deliver quantitative analysis based on modeling from first-principles</li><li>Translate business questions into data questions; ask: what are we doing to provide value?  What are the causes and what does it mean for the business?</li><li>Implement technical solutions at customer sites</li><li>Build a roadmap for the future of the product in conjunction with the engineering team</li><li>Manage relationships with customer stakeholders </li><li>Help build customer workflows and train users through these workflows; gather feature feedback and requirements for features under development</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n<ul><li>BA/BS in Engineering, Computer Science, Sciences, Statistics, or Mathematics (or equivalent work experience)</li><li>Familiarity with quantitative data analysis methods</li><li>Object-oriented programming skills</li><li>Ease in communicating with technical and non-technical personnel</li><li>Travel 50% of the time </li><li>Ability to work in teams while still leading projects solo</li></ul>\n<p>\nCover letter strongly preferred; please include examples of your technical aptitude, interesting projects you have managed or worked on in the past, and your analysis experience\n</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYUEAA4"},"a0m80000005U0ulAAC":{"id":"a0m80000005U0ulAAC","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005U0ul","published_id":"a0m80000005U0ul","label":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer: Japan - Asia","name":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer: Japan","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Tokyo, Japan","location":"Asia","description":"<p>\n\t<b>What We Do</b>\n</p>\n<p>\nForward Deployed Software Engineers (FDSEs) are responsible for the technical success of each of our deployments. They are full-stack developers who work side by side with our customers to lead technical implementation of our products. FDSEs understand our customers’ greatest pain points and design end-to-end solutions to address them. FDSEs solicit constant feedback on their work from both customers and colleagues, improving our products over time with rapid iteration cycles.\n</p>\n<p>\nFDSEs deploy cutting-edge technologies to solve our customers’ hardest problems. Projects often start with a nebulous question like “Why are we losing customers?” or “How can we more effectively identify instances of money laundering?” FDSEs are thought leaders and first movers in developing a solution, from high-level system design and prototyping to application development and data integration.\n</p>\n<p>\nFDSEs work with customers around the world, where they gain unique insight into the world’s most important industries and institutions. We help our customers detect insider trading, improve disaster relief, fight healthcare fraud, and more. Each mission presents different challenges, from the regulatory environment to the nature of the data to the user population. FSDEs work to accommodate all aspects of an environment to drive real outcomes for our customers. \n</p>\n<p>\n\t<b>Technologies We Use</b>\n</p>\n<p>\nOur approach is to deploy whatever technology is best to solve the problem at hand. This often means that we are learning from the bleeding edge of the open source community or developing our own tools. Recently, FDSEs have deployed:\n</p>\n<ul><li><b>Postgres, Cassandra, Hadoop,</b> and <b>Spark</b> for distributed data storage</li><li><b>Java</b> and <b>Groovy</b> for our back-end applications and data integration tools</li><li><b>Typescript, AngularJS, jQuery, Backbone, Underscore, Leaflet,</b> and <b>d3</b> for our web technologies</li><li><b>Python</b> for data science and machine learning</li><li><b>Internal frameworks</b> for our rapid iteration tools</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<b>What We Value</b>\n</p>\n<p>\nFDSEs are developers with a passion for using technology to achieve a larger goal.  They enjoy the challenge of solving an abstract problem and building or adopting the technology to do it. To support these goals, we value:\n</p>\n<ul><li><b>Collaboration:</b> We work with our customers, often on site, to understand and solve their problems.</li><li><b>Commitment:</b> We see projects through from beginning to end in spite of obstacles we may encounter. </li><li><b>Balance:</b> We do whatever is necessary to finish the job and trust one another to take the time we need, whether it&#39;s vacation or just a trip to the gym.</li><li><b>Communication:</b> We communicate complex technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences.</li><li><b>Improvement:</b> We push ourselves to grow and develop in new ways.</li><li><b>Impact:</b> We take on meaningful and challenging projects that change the world for the better.</li></ul>\n<p>\nExpected travel for the role varies by location. \n</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYRCAA4"},"a0m8000000557A8AAI":{"id":"a0m8000000557A8AAI","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m8000000557A8","published_id":"a0m8000000557A8","label":"Software Engineer: New York - New York, NY","name":"Software Engineer: New York","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"New York, NY","location":"New York, NY","description":"<p>We need world-class engineers to develop our information exploration technologies. Customers use our software to gather massive datasets from disparate sources, perform complex transformations and aggregations on it, and visually communicate the resulting insights.</p>\n\n<p>We are looking for talented and passionate software engineers who love to code and aren’t intimidated by challenging problems. We build modern web tools and know the open-source world inside out. We are designing algorithms to solve novel analytic and computational problems across heterogeneous domains. Our information exploration technology allows analysts to understand complex relationships. If you’re interested in working at a fast-moving, rapidly growing business-- we’re the company for you.</p>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>BS or MS in Computer Science or equivalent (started or completed a PhD a plus)</li><li>Previous job experience a plus, Java experience</li><li>Enthusiasm for solving interesting problems and a willingness to take on new product features</li><li>Background in distributed systems, machine learning, data visualization, user experience, high performance computing and/or developing enterprise software systems</li><li>Interest in working on a rapidly changing, ever-evolving system</li><li>Software engineering positions are available on multiple teams</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYSTAA4"},"a0m80000003mQFSAA2":{"id":"a0m80000003mQFSAA2","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000003mQFS","published_id":"a0m80000003mQFS","label":"Application Security Engineer - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Application Security Engineer","publishing_category":"Security","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>\nOur Information Security (Infosec) Team is responsible for the security of Statsopt&#39;s people, infrastructure, and customer deployments around the globe. Infosec Engineers are highly motivated team players with a dedication to security and technology. They thrive on solving problems and tackling new challenges.\n</p>\n<p>\nAs an Application Security Engineer, you&#39;ll work with engineering teams across Statsopt to establish and improve the security of Statsopt’s entire suite of products at every step of the development lifecycle. You will act as both a builder, creating tools to help our engineers write more secure code, and a breaker, performing penetration tests of internally developed applications.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>RESPONSIBILITIES</b></p>\n<ul><li>Consult with internal teams to assist in design, threat modeling, and reviewing security-critical code</li><li>Conduct periodic penetration tests of internal applications with up to several million lines of code</li><li>Plan, build and deploy infrastructure to help our engineers detect and remediate vulnerabilities automatically</li><li>Work with external vendors to support 3rd party security reviews</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>REQUIREMENTS</b></p>\n<ul><li>Expert-level knowledge in Python, Java, or Ruby</li><li>Strong familiarity with OWASP top 10 web vulnerabilities and the ability to explain them</li><li>Expert with ZAP, Burp or another intercepting proxy</li><li>Knowledge of the role of static and dynamic analysis in a robust security testing suite</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>PREFERRED</b></p>\n<ul><li>Experience in evaluating the choice and implementation of cryptography</li><li>Experience evaluating the security of mobile applications on iOS and Android</li><li>Experience evaluating the security of applications written in Node.js or Go</li><li>Experience integrating WAFs as part of a defensible application stack</li><li>Experience with fuzzing</li><li>Experience with threat modeling, especially STRIDE</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYRKAA4"},"a0m80000005KlH9AAK":{"id":"a0m80000005KlH9AAK","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005KlH9","published_id":"a0m80000005KlH9","label":"Site Reliability Operations Analyst: London - Europe","name":"Site Reliability Operations Analyst: London","publishing_category":"Mission Operations","physical_location":"London, United Kingdom","location":"Europe","description":"<p>\n\tSite Reliability Operations Analysts are the organizational backbone of a Statsopt deployment. We are the logistical dynamos who make sure that everything is in place at customer deployments so our engineers can do what they do best: solving the world&#39;s hardest problems. When things go wrong, we are the first-responders to the situation. We’re always improving ourselves and regularly take on tasks outside our wheelhouse, whether it’s learning new technical skills or navigating the procedural guidelines of many different clients. We field customer questions even if they&#39;re not within our expertise, and escalate the issue only after we’ve tried to solve it ourselves; this mentality applies to every aspect of our job. We strive for flawless execution in everything we do. Being genuine is the most important quality that unites us – our experience is disparate. None of us have egos and we’re all willing to choose the best idea, even when it&#39;s not our own.</p>\n<b>Responsibilities</b>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tHelp develop Statsopt deployments by anticipating and exceeding employee and customer needs</li><li>\n\t\tBe a primary liaison for clients, including learning and adhering to customer processes and protocols</li><li>\n\t\tProvide first-level support for Statsopt software</li><li>\n\t\tManage accounts and assets at our deployment</li><li>\n\t\tSupport multiple deployments simultaneously or a single deployment intensively</li></ul>\n<b>Requirements</b>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tExcellent customer service: relationship development skills and instant professionalism</li><li>\n\t\tProven record of accurate and consistent record keeping</li><li>\n\t\tStrong analytical and problem solving skills</li><li>\n\t\tUnbending commitment to operational security and ethics</li><li>\n\t\tEnthusiasm for working one on one with customers in an onsite setting</li><li>\n\t\tHard working, professional, and most importantly, genuine</li><li>\n\t\tAbility to adapt to new challenges and responsibilities</li><li>\n\t\tAbility to perform at a high level in high pressure situations</li></ul>\n<b>Preferred</b>\n<ul><li>\n\t\t1+ years in customer-focused IT support, or equivalent experience</li><li>\n\t\tKnowledge of UNIX and Windows administration</li><li>\n\t\tFamiliarity with wide range of shell scripting/web technologies such as PHP or Rails</li><li>\n\t\tBasic knowledge of such database systems as Oracle, Cassandra, or PostgreSQL</li><li>\n\t\tHigh degree of skill with MS Excel</li><li>\n\t\tProject management skills or PMP Certification</li><li>\n\t\tAbility to travel up to 75% of the time or being open to relocation</li><li>\n\t\tSecurity clearance or the ability to obtain one</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYUdAAO"},"a0m80000003mUYCAA2":{"id":"a0m80000003mUYCAA2","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000003mUYC","published_id":"a0m80000003mUYC","label":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer: New Zealand - Wellington, New Zealand","name":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer: New Zealand","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Wellington, New Zealand","location":"Wellington, New Zealand","description":"<p style=\"\"><b>What We Do</b></p>\n\n<p style=\"\">Forward Deployed Software Engineers (FDSEs) are responsible for the technical success of each of our deployments. They are full-stack developers who work side by side with our customers to lead technical implementation of our products. FDSEs understand our customers’ greatest pain points and design end-to-end solutions to address them. FDSEs solicit constant feedback on their work from both customers and colleagues, improving our products over time with rapid iteration cycles.</p>\n\n<p style=\"\">FDSEs deploy cutting-edge technologies to solve our customers’ hardest problems. Projects often start with a nebulous question like “Why are we losing customers?” or “How can we more effectively identify instances of money laundering?” FDSEs are thought leaders and first movers in developing a solution, from high-level system design and prototyping to application development and data integration.</p>\n\n<p style=\"\">FDSEs work with customers around the world, where they gain unique insight into the world’s most important industries and institutions. We help our customers detect insider trading, improve disaster relief, fight healthcare fraud, and more. Each mission presents different challenges, from the regulatory environment to the nature of the data to the user population. FSDEs work to accommodate all aspects of an environment to drive real outcomes for our customers.</p>\n\n<p style=\"\"><b>Technologies We Use</b></p>\n\n<p style=\"\">Our approach is to deploy whatever technology is best to solve the problem at hand. This often means that we are learning from the bleeding edge of the open source community or developing our own tools. Recently, FDSEs have deployed:</p>\n\n<ul><li><b>Postgres, Cassandra, Hadoop,</b> and <b>Spark</b> for distributed data storage</li><li><b>Java</b> and <b>Groovy</b> for our back-end applications and data integration tools</li><li><b>Typescript, AngularJS, jQuery, Backbone, Underscore, Leaflet,</b> and <b>d3</b> for our web technologies</li><li><b>Python</b> for data science and machine learning</li><li><b>Internal frameworks</b> for our rapid iteration tools</li></ul>\n\n<p style=\"\"><b>What We Value</b></p>\n\n<p style=\"\">FDSEs are developers with a passion for using technology to achieve a larger goal. They enjoy the challenge of solving an abstract problem and building or adopting the technology to do it. To support these goals, we value:</p>\n\n<ul><li><b>Collaboration:</b> We work with our customers, often on site, to understand and solve their problems.</li><li><b>Commitment:</b> We see projects through from beginning to end in spite of obstacles we may encounter.</li><li><b>Balance:</b> We do whatever is necessary to finish the job and trust one another to take the time we need, whether it&#39;s vacation or just a trip to the gym.</li><li><b>Communication:</b> We communicate complex technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences.</li><li><b>Improvement:</b> We push ourselves to grow and develop in new ways.</li><li><b>Impact:</b> We take on meaningful and challenging projects that change the world for the better.</li></ul>\n\n<p style=\"\">Expected travel for the role varies by location.</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYRCAA4"},"a0m80000003mUYHAA2":{"id":"a0m80000003mUYHAA2","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000003mUYH","published_id":"a0m80000003mUYH","label":"Deployment Strategist: New Zealand - Wellington, New Zealand","name":"Deployment Strategist: New Zealand","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Wellington, New Zealand","location":"Wellington, New Zealand","description":"<p>Deployment Strategists at Statsopt own the outcomes of all the work we do in Business Development. We begin with a vision: a vision of how software can transform people&#39;s relationship to data at the heart of a problem we care deeply about. We test that vision. Do our partners share it? Can we build what they need quickly enough? Will we be able to deploy it in the right environment, to the right people? Working side by side with our Forward-Deployed Software Engineers, we refine our vision, and then find our way to it: through messy data, through bureaucratic labyrinths, through sandstorms in &quot;data centers&quot; made of tents and suitcases. Whatever it takes, we figure out how to do it.</p>\n\n<p>A team of analysts at a customer site might want training for a tool we&#39;ve built. One of our customers&#39; CEOs might need help convincing another organization to share data. A team of developers might be asking for direction on which of a dozen feature requests they should prioritize this quarter. Or a global financial organization might be on the line, reeling from a recent compliance failure and asking us what we can do to help detect and prevent such behavior in the future. These, and a hundred other everyday scenarios, are where a Deployment Strategist thrives.</p>\n\n<p>This role doesn&#39;t come neatly packaged or defined. You should expect it to change during your time at Statsopt, to evolve as our organization evolves and as you do. When we interview Deployment Strategists, we aren&#39;t looking for people with a specific background. We&#39;re looking for people with exceptional analytic ability, creative brilliance, technical aptitude, and a gift for finding the details that matter. Most of all, we&#39;re looking for people who combine a calling to leave the world better than they found it with the resourcefulness necessary to realize that calling, no matter the circumstances.</p>\n\n<p>If that sounds like you, then we&#39;re interested.</p>\n\n<p>We look forward to hearing from you. You can scroll down for more specific examples of roles Deployment Strategists might take on.<br> </p>\n \n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PRODUCT OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>We&#39;re constantly building products at Statsopt. Some products are very specific to particular customer workflows—specialized geospatial visualization tools, for example, that might exist as part of a more generic map application. Others, such as a lightweight document reader, are deployed to tens of thousands of our users. All of these products have their roots in a particular customer&#39;s needs, where a team of Deployment Strategists and Forward-Deployed Software Engineers sat down together with our core developers and started work.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards product ownership have strong technical skills, compelling creative vision for what software can do, and an instinct for leadership. They apply those skills to leading a team that builds and supports a product: defining requirements, testing new versions, installing and configuring applications, sitting down with users and gathering feedback about what&#39;s working well and what isn&#39;t. They work across organizations and across internal teams, ensuring that we are all aligned on what we are building and why. Ultimately, they are responsible for ensuring that we deliver a product that truly transforms our customers&#39; ability to work with data.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PROJECT OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>Our partnerships with our customers are at the core of what we do. Our customers trust that we are the best in the world at building and delivering enterprise software. They trust that we mean it when we say we can enable collaboration across a worldwide enterprise without sacrificing security, or that in the event of a crisis we will surge the team that supports them just as they surge their own internal team. Fundamentally, our customers—whether they&#39;re looking for a missing child, an insurgent assembling a roadside bomb, or the source of a cyber attack on their network—trust that we care as deeply about their problems as they do.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards project ownership are the face of Statsopt, and the custodians of that trust. They pair a passion for software with excellent communication skills, an ability to navigate organizational hurdles, and an instinct for putting the right people in the right places. A project owner might spend the morning in meetings with customers to discuss the status of a data integration, the afternoon in a CTO&#39;s office talking about best practices in cyber security, and lunch in between at our headquarters brainstorming with a technical team about the best time to perform an upgrade. Ultimately, they are responsible for the strength of our partnerships: for ensuring that our customers are excited to work with us, and that we are excited to work with our customers.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PROCESS OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>The common thread across all of our work is data—lots of data. Organizations come to us when they no longer know how to make sense of the data they wish to inform their decisions, and while there are always differences, large and small, between different customers&#39; workflows in our software, there are also many areas of overlap.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards process ownership are experts in deploying software and making it work for human beings. They are brilliant, articulate, and generally deeply empathetic people. They excel at sitting down with a user and within minutes understanding exactly what he or she is trying to do--and at then synthesizing that understanding into a broader vision of what we can do to help them. That might mean building a new tool, or paring superfluous features out of an existing one. It might mean implementing certain standards in data curation or analysis. It might mean a series of training sessions, or the creation of an entirely new task force. Whatever the solution, they will own it, and will ensure that our customers benefit fully from everything we&#39;ve learned over the last decade of helping humans to navigate data.</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYS3AAO"},"a0m80000004kyQhAAI":{"id":"a0m80000004kyQhAAI","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000004kyQh","published_id":"a0m80000004kyQh","label":"Software Engineer - Washington, D.C.","name":"Software Engineer","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"Washington, D.C.","location":"Washington, D.C.","description":"<p class=\"p1\">We need world-class engineers to develop our information exploration technologies. The problem space includes everything from exploring huge information sets to presenting complex information in an easily digestible form for end-users.</p>\n\n<p>We are looking for talented and passionate software engineers who love to code and aren’t intimidated by challenging problems. We brew modern web tools and know the open-source world inside out. We are designing algorithms to solve novel search problems across heterogeneous information. Our information exploration technology allows analysts to understand complex relationships. </p>\n\n<h3 style=\"font-size: 13px;\">Requirements</h3>\n\n<ul><li>BS/MS in Computer Science or equivalent (PhD or dropped out of PhD 