g with colleagues across the company to consistently identify and attract brilliant people to our team. You will be constantly challenged to think creatively about how to drive hiring results. You will be part of a team that is responsible for developing, implementing, and executing a broad recruiting strategy, with a particular emphasis on sourcing high quality active and passive candidates.</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Partner with hiring managers to develop, implement, and manage tactical sourcing strategies for technical positions</li><li>Build job descriptions and develop posting strategies for maximum exposure</li><li>Cold calls and outreach to prospective candidates to generate interest in Statsopt and positions</li><li>Screen and qualify prospective candidates</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>BA/BS from a top university is required, a technical degree is a plus</li><li>At least 3 years of recruiting experience, preferably in a technology environment</li><li>Ability to consistently offer innovative solutions to recruiting challenges within the broader context of the organization&#39;s priorities and approach to problem-solving</li><li>Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYTIAA4"},"a0m80000004mWSXAA2":{"id":"a0m80000004mWSXAA2","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000004mWSX","published_id":"a0m80000004mWSX","label":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer: New Grad - London - Europe","name":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer: New Grad - London","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"London, United Kingdom","location":"Europe","description":"<p>\n\t<b>What We Do</b>\n</p>\n<p>\nForward Deployed Software Engineers (FDSEs) are responsible for the technical success of each of our deployments. They are full-stack developers who work side by side with our customers to lead technical implementation of our products. FDSEs understand our customers’ greatest pain points and design end-to-end solutions to address them. FDSEs solicit constant feedback on their work from both customers and colleagues, improving our products over time with rapid iteration cycles.\n</p>\n<p>\nFDSEs deploy cutting-edge technologies to solve our customers’ hardest problems. Projects often start with a nebulous question like “Why are we losing customers?” or “How can we more effectively identify instances of money laundering?” FDSEs are thought leaders and first movers in developing a solution, from high-level system design and prototyping to application development and data integration.\n</p>\n<p>\nFDSEs work with customers around the world, where they gain unique insight into the world’s most important industries and institutions. We help our customers detect insider trading, improve disaster relief, fight healthcare fraud, and more. Each mission presents different challenges, from the regulatory environment to the nature of the data to the user population. FSDEs work to accommodate all aspects of an environment to drive real outcomes for our customers. \n</p>\n<p>\n\t<b>Technologies We Use</b>\n</p>\n<p>\nOur approach is to deploy whatever technology is best to solve the problem at hand. This often means that we are learning from the bleeding edge of the open source community or developing our own tools. Recently, FDSEs have deployed:\n</p>\n<ul><li><b>Postgres, Cassandra, Hadoop,</b> and <b>Spark</b> for distributed data storage</li><li><b>Java</b> and <b>Groovy</b> for our back-end applications and data integration tools</li><li><b>Typescript, AngularJS, jQuery, Backbone, Underscore, Leaflet,</b> and <b>d3</b> for our web technologies</li><li><b>Python</b> for data science and machine learning</li><li><b>Internal frameworks</b> for our rapid iteration tools</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<b>What We Value</b>\n</p>\n<p>\nFDSEs are developers with a passion for using technology to achieve a larger goal.  They enjoy the challenge of solving an abstract problem and building or adopting the technology to do it. To support these goals, we value:\n</p>\n<ul><li><b>Collaboration:</b> We work with our customers, often on site, to understand and solve their problems.</li><li><b>Commitment:</b> We see projects through from beginning to end in spite of obstacles we may encounter. </li><li><b>Balance:</b> We do whatever is necessary to finish the job and trust one another to take the time we need, whether it&#39;s vacation or just a trip to the gym.</li><li><b>Communication:</b> We communicate complex technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences.</li><li><b>Improvement:</b> We push ourselves to grow and develop in new ways.</li><li><b>Impact:</b> We take on meaningful and challenging projects that change the world for the better.</li></ul>\n<p>\nExpected travel for the role varies by location. \n</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PZq8AAG"},"a0m80000005UAxlAAG":{"id":"a0m80000005UAxlAAG","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005UAxl","published_id":"a0m80000005UAxl","label":"Deployment Strategist: Norway - Europe","name":"Deployment Strategist: Norway","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Oslo, Norway","location":"Europe","description":"<p>Deployment Strategists at Statsopt own the outcomes of all the work we do in Business Development. We begin with a vision: a vision of how software can transform people&#39;s relationship to data at the heart of a problem we care deeply about. We test that vision. Do our partners share it? Can we build what they need quickly enough? Will we be able to deploy it in the right environment, to the right people? Working side by side with our Forward-Deployed Software Engineers, we refine our vision, and then find our way to it: through messy data, through bureaucratic labyrinths, through sandstorms in &quot;data centers&quot; made of tents and suitcases. Whatever it takes, we figure out how to do it.</p>\n\n<p>A team of analysts at a customer site might want training for a tool we&#39;ve built. One of our customers&#39; CEOs might need help convincing another organization to share data. A team of developers might be asking for direction on which of a dozen feature requests they should prioritize this quarter. Or a global financial organization might be on the line, reeling from a recent compliance failure and asking us what we can do to help detect and prevent such behavior in the future. These, and a hundred other everyday scenarios, are where a Deployment Strategist thrives.</p>\n\n<p>This role doesn&#39;t come neatly packaged or defined. You should expect it to change during your time at Statsopt, to evolve as our organization evolves and as you do. When we interview Deployment Strategists, we aren&#39;t looking for people with a specific background. We&#39;re looking for people with exceptional analytic ability, creative brilliance, technical aptitude, and a gift for finding the details that matter. Most of all, we&#39;re looking for people who combine a calling to leave the world better than they found it with the resourcefulness necessary to realize that calling, no matter the circumstances.</p>\n\n<p>If that sounds like you, then we&#39;re interested.</p>\n\n<p>We look forward to hearing from you. You can scroll down for more specific examples of roles Deployment Strategists might take on.<br> </p>\n \n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PRODUCT OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>We&#39;re constantly building products at Statsopt. Some products are very specific to particular customer workflows—specialized geospatial visualization tools, for example, that might exist as part of a more generic map application. Others, such as a lightweight document reader, are deployed to tens of thousands of our users. All of these products have their roots in a particular customer&#39;s needs, where a team of Deployment Strategists and Forward-Deployed Software Engineers sat down together with our core developers and started work.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards product ownership have strong technical skills, compelling creative vision for what software can do, and an instinct for leadership. They apply those skills to leading a team that builds and supports a product: defining requirements, testing new versions, installing and configuring applications, sitting down with users and gathering feedback about what&#39;s working well and what isn&#39;t. They work across organizations and across internal teams, ensuring that we are all aligned on what we are building and why. Ultimately, they are responsible for ensuring that we deliver a product that truly transforms our customers&#39; ability to work with data.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PROJECT OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>Our partnerships with our customers are at the core of what we do. Our customers trust that we are the best in the world at building and delivering enterprise software. They trust that we mean it when we say we can enable collaboration across a worldwide enterprise without sacrificing security, or that in the event of a crisis we will surge the team that supports them just as they surge their own internal team. Fundamentally, our customers—whether they&#39;re looking for a missing child, an insurgent assembling a roadside bomb, or the source of a cyber attack on their network—trust that we care as deeply about their problems as they do.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards project ownership are the face of Statsopt, and the custodians of that trust. They pair