re that our customers benefit fully from everything we&#39;ve learned over the last decade of helping humans to navigate data.</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYS3AAO"},"a0m80000000LkdwAAC":{"id":"a0m80000000LkdwAAC","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000000Lkdw","published_id":"a0m80000000Lkdw","label":"Software Engineer - Palo Alto - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Software Engineer - Palo Alto","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>\n<b>WHAT WE DO</b>\n</p>\n<p>\nOur engineers are involved in all parts of the product lifecycle: idea generation, design, prototyping, planning, execution, and shipping. Our work starts with brainstorming to discover, explore, and understand our customer’s greatest challenges in the visual and technical spaces. Then we code. A lot. Finally, we ship and continuously iterate on products that have a direct impact on the world’s hardest problems.\n</p>\n<p>\n<b>OUR WORK</b>\n</p>\n<p>\nStatsopt makes products for human-driven analysis of real-world data. These products must handle messy data at enormous scales, all while maintaining an intuitive user experience and a wide range of analytic capabilities. Our software engineers push the boundaries of what’s possible. We have:\n</p>\n<ul><li>Built a web-based mapping interface that handles millions of data points dynamically displayed at once. </li><li>Constructed an analysis platform on top of a columnar database and custom infrastructure that allows complex numerical analysis at the petabyte scale.</li><li>Created AtlasDB, which provides high-scale, reliable data storage for Statsopt products. This NoSQL distributed data store adds a transactional layer that gives the whole system ACID properties.</li><li>Developed a WYSIWYG web app for quickly creating interactive, data-driven web sites. </li><li>And much, much more: mobile, infrastructure, search, client facing, etc.</li></ul>\n<p>\n<b>TECHNOLOGIES WE USE</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li>Java for back-end work</li><li>Javascript, CoffeeScript, and TypeScript for client and server web work</li><li>Open source technologies such as Cassandra, Spark, ElasticSearch, etc</li><li>The latest web technologies</li><li>Internal frameworks for our rapid iteration tools</li></ul>\n<p>\n<b>WHAT WE LOOK FOR</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li>You’re a strong coder. Regardless of which language you use or how you learned it, we’re looking for people who can write clean, effective code.</li><li>You enjoy collaboration with others. Our work isn’t carried out in a vacuum, and everyone contributes to get the job done.</li><li>You understand that making mistakes means you’re learning.</li><li>You have a constant desire to grow and develop.</li><li>You are passionate about product craftsmanship, and care about great design not only in products and their visual presentation, but in your code and technical architecture as well.</li><li>You are comfortable in a high-paced environment, and can respond to urgent requests. </li><li>You want to work on things that make an impact on the world.</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYSTAA4"},"a0m80000000iQpMAAU":{"id":"a0m80000000iQpMAAU","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000000iQpM","published_id":"a0m80000000iQpM","label":"Product Designer - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Product Designer","publishing_category":"Design","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p> </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">A WORLD-CHANGING COMPANY</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">At Statsopt, we develop the world&#39;s leading products for data analysis and we deploy them against problems that truly matter — uncovering human trafficking rings, containing the spread of infectious diseases, combating fraud, stopping cyber attacks, protecting privacy and civil liberties, prosecuting complex financial crimes, providing relief to victims of natural disasters, and more.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">Sound exciting? We think so, too.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">THE DESIGN TEAM</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">The Statsopt Design team is responsible for creating the human experience of using our software, as well as the execution of our brand. We design everything from user interfaces, to immersive experiences in our buildings and events, all the way down to awesome illustrated teeshirts we&#39;re famous for. </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">We help to achieve connection and understanding. Our <i>users</i> must create knowledge from data in our software, potential <i>customers</i> and <i>candidates</i> need to understand and relate to the story of our company and the awesome work we do, and it&#39;s our job to help tell these stories. </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">We believe that everyone should have access to excellence in design — utility and beauty — in whatever form it takes. Designers are highly valued in the company for our vision, our ability to learn and adapt, and our creativity and inventiveness. We&#39;re growing rapidly, yet focused on creating a tight-knit group of people that enjoy each other’s company in an atmosphere that fosters trust, integrity, empathy, and growth. </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">THE PRODUCT DESIGNER</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">We are generalists that span many design disciplines: user research, information architecture, prototyping, ideation, interaction design, and sometimes visual design. Our artifacts come in many different forms and fidelities. We draw a lot, and we write a lot. We prototype with paper and Sharpies, Javascript, After Effects, and Keynote. We visit our users, listen, investigate, learn, and ideate. We rigorously share and promote our ideas, and constantly incorporate feedback and critique.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">Sometimes we’re out in front, exploring brand-new problem spaces, figuring out <i>what</i> to build. And sometimes we’re deep in the details of micro-interactions, figuring out <i>how</i> to build it. We lead feature teams in design exercises ranging from day-long design studios to week-long design sprints.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">A great Product Designer knows that form informs function and usability — that the surface layer doesn&#39;t exist in a vacuum — and that means the partnership with the <a href=\"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005cjnIAAQ\" target=\"_blank\">Visual Designer</a> is a two-way conversation. We believe it is often important to have an owner for each of these facets. Dedicated roles help us ensure that we can meet the high bar of quality we’ve set for ourselves. Product Designers own the user experience of our products along with <a href=\"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005cjnIAAQ\" target=\"_blank\">Visual Designers</a>, User Researchers, and Product Engineers. Together, we refine and evolve the quality of all Statsopt software. </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><i>Please note: this is not an industrial design role.</i></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">WHAT WE VALUE</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">Excellent communication skills. You have a proven ability to build great relationships, and convey and debate design rationale. You are the person that people can’t wait to collaborate with.<br><br>Empathy, not ego. We strive to understand our users and we fight to empower them.<br><br>A profound love of engineers. Statsopt is an engineering company, and we get to work with some of the best in the world. Engineers realize our vision — and we realize theirs — and together we create software that our users love.<br><br>A highly iterative design process. We move fast, we listen, and we adapt. We rapidly incorporate feedback, and we relentlessly collaborate. You must be adept at giving and receiving critiques.<br><br>A mastery of tools. We move with ease across software and fidelity, depending on the task at hand. Sketch.app, hand-coding, Photoshop, Illustrator, or Keynote — and good old-fashioned pencil and paper.<br> </p>\n\n<p> </p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYU4AAO"},"a0m80000000Lne9AAC":{"id":"a0m80000000Lne9AAC","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000000Lne9","published_id":"a0m80000000Lne9","label":"Product Quality Engineer, New Grad - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Product Quality Engineer, New Grad","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>\nStatsopt Product Quality Engineers (PQEs) work on our cross-functional Product teams to ensure successful, high quality product releases. This means that they do whatever is needed to deliver our products to people who need them the most. PQEs identify areas for improvement and take ownership of enhancement projects. We are looking for energetic, highly motivated, and detail-oriented engineers with strong software skills to fill this role. \n</p>\n<p>\nPQEs focus on the entire suite of Statsopt products, from applications for data visualization to our cutting-edge web components library. As a PQE, you will drive customer outcomes by iterating closely with engineers across the business to ensure a high-quality user experience for Statsopt products. You will triage engineering issues, design features to address customer use cases, evaluate the quality of these features with manual and automated testing, and debug software problems. \n</p>\n<p>\nPQEs are technical generalists who can ramp up on new projects quickly, effectively evaluate the state of a given product, and make multifaceted contributions to the codebase to guarantee best-in-class software solutions for our customers.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n<ul><li>BS in Computer Science, Mathematics, or a related field</li><li>Experience programming in at least one common language</li><li>Ability to think creatively to define product and customer needs</li><li>Experience working with complex systems (software, biological, mechanical)</li><li>Excellent analytical thinking skills and attention to detail</li><li>Excellent written and verbal communications skills</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYSsAAO"},"a0m80000000LneBAAS":{"id":"a0m80000000LneBAAS","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000000LneB","published_id":"a0m80000000LneB","label":"Salesforce Applications Developer - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Salesforce Applications Developer","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p><b>A WORLD-CHANGING COMPANY</b></p>\n<p>\nAt Statsopt, we develop the world’s leading products for data analysis and we deploy them against problems that\ntruly matter—uncovering human trafficking rings, containing the spread of infectious diseases, combating fraud,\nstopping cyber attacks, protecting privacy and civil liberties, prosecuting complex financial crimes, providing relief to\nvictims of natural disasters, and more.\n</p>\n<p>\nSound exciting? We think so, too.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>THE INTERNAL APPLICATIONS TEAM</b></p>\n<p>\nBeing a member of Internal Applications is about solving problems for a scaling company. With our accumulated\nexperience and insight across a myriad of technologies, our team shapes a suite of internal products that have a\nprofound effect on the success of our teams. We anticipate the needs of Statsopt, solve emerging problems, and\ncollaborate with our core teams to turn abstract goals into reality. This means being deeply involved in the creation\nof custom internal applications as well as bending third party products to our will. We own projects from beginning\nto end, see our work shift often, and relish in seeing our efforts immediately impact Statsopt.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>SALESFORCE DEVELOPER</b></p>\n<p>\nOur apps make Statsopt more efficient and better-connected, and are critical to every team’s success. The Salesforce\nDeveloper architects, builds, tests, and deploys applications using the Force.com platform. They love working with\nusers and owning the solution from the ideas-on-napkins phase all the way to deployment.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>TECHNOLOGIES WE USE</b></p>\n<p>\nApex to power the core of our custom applications<br>Visualforce to present concise and engaging interfaces<br>Web Services to interact and collaborate with other systems<br>Metadata APIs to automate and simplify workflows\n</p>\n<p>\nWe also use…\nPython, Ruby, Groovy, and Bash for scripting tasks<br>Javascript and Coffeescript for client-side web work<br>Common open-source frameworks like jQuery, AngularJS, Backbone.js, D3, Haml, and Sass<br>Java for making plugins<br>MySQL and Postgres for storage<br>ElasticSearch for searching\n</p>\n\n<p><b>WHAT WE VALUE</b></p>\n<p>\nYou&#39;re cool with working with others. Our jobs aren’t done in a vacuum and everyone contributes to get the job done.<br>You’re not afraid to make mistakes because without challenge, you’re not learning.<br>Speaking of learning, you have a constant desire to grow and develop.<br>You care about great design, not only in the product and visual sense, but also in your code and technical\narchitecture.<br>You are passionate about product craftsmanship, and can balance that with shipping something relevant.<br>You move fast with a sense of urgency.<br>You want to work on things that make an impact on the world.<br></p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYUYAA4"},"a0m80000005Vge2AAC":{"id":"a0m80000005Vge2AAC","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005Vge2","published_id":"a0m80000005Vge2","label":"Deployment Strategist: Finland - Europe","name":"Deployment Strategist: Finland","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Helsinki, Finland","location":"Europe","description":"<p>Deployment Strategists at Statsopt own the outcomes of all the work we do in Business Development. We begin with a vision: a vision of how software can transform people&#39;s relationship to data at the heart of a problem we care deeply about. We test that vision. Do our partners share it? Can we build what they need quickly enough? Will we be able to deploy it in the right environment, to the right people? Working side by side with our Forward-Deployed Software Engineers, we refine our vision, and then find our way to it: through messy data, through bureaucratic labyrinths, through sandstorms in &quot;data centers&quot; made of tents and suitcases. Whatever it takes, we figure out how to do it.</p>\n\n<p>A team of analysts at a customer site might want training for a tool we&#39;ve built. One of our customers&#39; CEOs might need help convincing another organization to share data. A team of developers might be asking for direction on which of a dozen feature requests they should prioritize this quarter. Or a global financial organization might be on the line, reeling from a recent compliance failure and asking us what we can do to help detect and prevent such behavior in the future. These, and a hundred other everyday scenarios, are where a Deployment Strategist thrives.</p>\n\n<p>This role doesn&#39;t come neatly packaged or defined. You should expect it to change during your time at Statsopt, to evolve as our organization evolves and as you do. When we interview Deployment Strategists, we aren&#39;t looking for people with a specific background. We&#39;re looking for people with exceptional analytic ability, creative brilliance, technical aptitude, and a gift for finding the details that matter. Most of all, we&#39;re looking for people who combine a calling to leave the world better than they found it with the resourcefulness necessary to realize that calling, no matter the circumstances.</p>\n\n<p>If that sounds like you, then we&#39;re interested.</p>\n\n<p>We look forward to hearing from you. You can scroll down for more specific examples of roles Deployment Strategists might take on.<br> </p>\n \n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PRODUCT OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>We&#39;re constantly building products at Statsopt. Some products are very specific to particular customer workflows—specialized geospatial visualization tools, for example, that might exist as part of a more generic map application. Others, such as a lightweight document reader, are deployed to tens of thousands of our users. All of these products have their roots in a particular customer&#39;s needs, where a team of Deployment Strategists and Forward-Deployed Software Engineers sat down together with our core developers and started work.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards product ownership have strong technical skills, compelling creative vision for what software can do, and an instinct for leadership. They apply those skills to leading a team that builds and supports a product: defining requirements, testing new versions, installing and configuring applications, sitting down with users and gathering feedback about what&#39;s working well and what isn&#39;t. They work across organizations and across internal teams, ensuring that we are all aligned on what we are building and why. Ultimately, they are responsible for ensuring that we deliver a product that truly transforms our customers&#39; ability to work with data.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PROJECT OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>Our partnerships with our customers are at the core of what we do. Our customers trust that we are the best in the world at building and delivering enterprise software. They trust that we mean it when we say we can enable collaboration across a worldwide enterprise without sacrificing security, or that in the event of a crisis we will surge the team that supports them just as they surge their own internal team. Fundamentally, our customers—whether they&#39;re looking for a missing child, an insurgent assembling a roadside bomb, or the source of a cyber attack on their network—trust that we care as deeply about their problems as they do.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards project ownership are the face of Statsopt, and the custodians of that trust. They pair a passion for software with excellent communication skills, an ability to navigate organizational hurdles, and an instinct for putting the right people in the right places. A project owner might spend the morning in meetings with customers to discuss the status of a data integration, the afternoon in a CTO&#39;s office talking about best practices in cyber security, and lunch in between at our headquarters brainstorming with a technical team about the best time to perform an upgrade. Ultimately, they are responsible for the strength of our partnerships: for ensuring that our customers are excited to work with us, and that we are excited to work with our customers.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">PROCESS OWNER</span></p>\n\n<p>The common thread across all of our work is data—lots of data. Organizations come to us when they no longer know how to make sense of the data they wish to inform their decisions, and while there are always differences, large and small, between different customers&#39; workflows in our software, there are also many areas of overlap.</p>\n\n<p>Deployment Strategists who gravitate towards process ownership are experts in deploying software and making it work for human beings. They are brilliant, articulate, and generally deeply empathetic people. They excel at sitting down with a user and within minutes understanding exactly what he or she is trying to do--and at then synthesizing that understanding into a broader vision of what we can do to help them. That might mean building a new tool, or paring superfluous features out of an existing one. It might mean implementing certain standards in data curation or analysis. It might mean a series of training sessions, or the creation of an entirely new task force. Whatever the solution, they will own it, and will ensure that our customers benefit fully from everything we&#39;ve learned over the last decade of helping humans to navigate data.</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYS3AAO"},"a0m80000005VelWAAS":{"id":"a0m80000005VelWAAS","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005VelW","published_id":"a0m80000005VelW","label":"Full Stack Software Engineer - New York, NY","name":"Full Stack Software Engineer","publishing_category":"Engineering","physical_location":"New York, NY","location":"New York, NY","description":"<p>\n\t<strong>What Full Stack Software Engineers do:</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tOur engineers are involved in all parts of the product lifecycle: brainstorming, design, prototyping, planning, execution, and shipping. We brainstorm to understand and explore the difficult problem spaces we tackle, and work with our talented team to come up with solutions for the hardest problems we discover (product, visual, and technical). We code (there is lots of coding), and finally, ship and own products that directly impact the world. We work with the cutting edge web technologies such as TypeScript, D3, Leaflet and Angular and are avid fans of open source (<a href=\"https://github.com/Statsopt\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/Statsopt</a>)</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Some highlights of our open source work:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tLinter for TypeScript: <a href=\"https://github.com/Statsopt/tslint\" target=\"_blank\">Click Here</a></li><li>\n\t\tEclipse plug-in for TypeScript: <a href=\"https://github.com/Statsopt/eclipse-typescript\" target=\"_blank\">Click Here</a></li><li>\n\t\tConverter for CoffeeScript -&gt; TypeScript: <a href=\"https://github.com/Statsopt/coffeescript-to-typescript\" target=\"_blank\">Click Here</a></li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Technologies we use:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tTypeScript for client and Java for our backend work</li><li>\n\t\tCommon open source libraries and frameworks like jQuery, Angular, Leaflet and D3</li><li>\n\t\tInternal frameworks that we’ve crafted to serve our rapid iteration</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<strong>What we value:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>\n\t\tYou&#39;re cool with working with others. Our jobs aren’t done in a vacuum and everyone contributes to get the job done.</li><li>\n\t\tYou’re not afraid to make mistakes because without challenge, you’re not learning.</li><li>\n\t\tSpeaking of learning, you have a constant desire to grow and develop.</li><li>\n\t\tYou care about great design, not only in the product and visual sense, but also in your code and technical architecture.</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYVHAA4"},"a0m80000005KmMhAAK":{"id":"a0m80000005KmMhAAK","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005KmMh","published_id":"a0m80000005KmMh","label":"Product Designer - New York, NY","name":"Product Designer","publishing_category":"Design","physical_location":"New York, NY","location":"New York, NY","description":"<p> </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">A WORLD-CHANGING COMPANY</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">At Statsopt, we develop the world&#39;s leading products for data analysis and we deploy them against problems that truly matter — uncovering human trafficking rings, containing the spread of infectious diseases, combating fraud, stopping cyber attacks, protecting privacy and civil liberties, prosecuting complex financial crimes, providing relief to victims of natural disasters, and more.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">Sound exciting? We think so, too.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">THE DESIGN TEAM</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">The Statsopt Design team is responsible for creating the human experience of using our software, as well as the execution of our brand. We design everything from user interfaces, to immersive experiences in our buildings and events, all the way down to awesome illustrated teeshirts we&#39;re famous for. </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">We help to achieve connection and understanding. Our <i>users</i> must create knowledge from data in our software, potential <i>customers</i> and <i>candidates</i> need to understand and relate to the story of our company and the awesome work we do, and it&#39;s our job to help tell these stories. </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">We believe that everyone should have access to excellence in design — utility and beauty — in whatever form it takes. Designers are highly valued in the company for our vision, our ability to learn and adapt, and our creativity and inventiveness. We&#39;re growing rapidly, yet focused on creating a tight-knit group of people that enjoy each other’s company in an atmosphere that fosters trust, integrity, empathy, and growth. </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">THE PRODUCT DESIGNER</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">We are generalists that span many design disciplines: user research, information architecture, prototyping, ideation, interaction design, and sometimes visual design. Our artifacts come in many different forms and fidelities. We draw a lot, and we write a lot. We prototype with paper and Sharpies, Javascript, After Effects, and Keynote. We visit our users, listen, investigate, learn, and ideate. We rigorously share and promote our ideas, and constantly incorporate feedback and critique.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">Sometimes we’re out in front, exploring brand-new problem spaces, figuring out <i>what</i> to build. And sometimes we’re deep in the details of micro-interactions, figuring out <i>how</i> to build it. We lead feature teams in design exercises ranging from day-long design studios to week-long design sprints.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">A great Product Designer knows that form informs function and usability — that the surface layer doesn&#39;t exist in a vacuum — and that means the partnership with the <a href=\"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005cjnIAAQ\" target=\"_blank\">Visual Designer</a> is a two-way conversation. We believe it is often important to have an owner for each of these facets. Dedicated roles help us ensure that we can meet the high bar of quality we’ve set for ourselves. Product Designers own the user experience of our products along with <a href=\"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005cjnIAAQ\" target=\"_blank\">Visual Designers</a>, User Researchers, and Product Engineers. Together, we refine and evolve the quality of all Statsopt software. </p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><i>Please note: this is not an industrial design role.</i></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(16, 17, 19); display: block; font-family: blender,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 28px; text-align: center;\">WHAT WE VALUE</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(119, 122, 122); font-size: 15px;\">Excellent communication skills. You have a proven ability to build great relationships, and convey and debate design rationale. You are the person that people can’t wait to collaborate with.<br><br>Empathy, not ego. We strive to understand our users and we fight to empower them.<br><br>A profound love of engineers. Statsopt is an engineering company, and we get to work with some of the best in the world. Engineers realize our vision — and we realize theirs — and together we create software that our users love.<br><br>A highly iterative design process. We move fast, we listen, and we adapt. We rapidly incorporate feedback, and we relentlessly collaborate. You must be adept at giving and receiving critiques.<br><br>A mastery of tools. We move with ease across software and fidelity, depending on the task at hand. Sketch.app, hand-coding, Photoshop, Illustrator, or Keynote — and good old-fashioned pencil and paper.<br> </p>\n\n<p> </p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYU4AAO"},"a0m80000006WULSAA4":{"id":"a0m80000006WULSAA4","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006WULS","published_id":"a0m80000006WULS","label":"Campus Specialist - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Campus Specialist","publishing_category":"Recruiting","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>The Campus Specialist is responsible for designing, developing and executing high-touch recruiting strategies for Statsopt¹s target schools, in partnership with College Recruiters. This person will act as the “face” of Statsopt, interfacing directly with students and school stakeholders.</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities:</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Manage all on-campus events for the schools he/she owns, approximately 5 total schools</li><li>Identify which events/opportunities best align with recruiting strategies</li><li>Register for all events</li><li>Manage all event-related logistics including, but not limited to vendor selection, vendor rate negotiation, venue selection, food ordering, and AV setup</li><li>Vet and recommended travel partners for campus attendees (ie hotels, airlines and transportation options)</li><li>Design and distribute advertising and promotional materials on campus</li><li>Travel to events during the peak travel season (September ­through March)</li><li>Host pre-event syncs for each event</li><li>Manage communications to campus attendees and act as POC for them</li><li>Own all aspects of on-campus interview process</li><li>Direct Intern Program Specialist¹s ordering of swag and collateral for events</li><li>Source and triage candidates from Career Fairs, Tech Talks and other core events</li><li>Partner with Recruiters on sourcing for specialized events</li><li>Network with key professors, student organizations and other faculty contacts</li><li>Create and maintain clear documentation around outcomes from recruiting events</li><li>Meet with Campus Ambassadors during travel season to provide support and guidance</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements:</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Passion for College Recruiting</li><li>Strong organization and communication skills</li><li>Outgoing and professional personality</li><li>Ability to travel, approximately 50%</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Preferred Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>College Recruiting experience</li><li>Experience building relationships at nationally ranked universities</li><li>Coordination experience</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PZfBAAW"},"a0m80000006LUWwAAO":{"id":"a0m80000006LUWwAAO","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006LUWw","published_id":"a0m80000006LUWw","label":"Administrative Assistant - Europe","name":"Administrative Assistant","publishing_category":"Operations","physical_location":"London, United Kingdom","location":"Europe","description":"<p>Statsopt Administrative Professionals are the behind-the-scenes, multitasking powerhouses that ensure the people, teams, and projects we support run smoothly. Our day-to-day is a fast-paced landscape of new challenges, creative problem solving, and goal setting. Every “To Do” we complete brings us one step closer to our mission. Our positive spirit and can-do attitude transforms chaos into order, paving the way for Statsopt’s success. Our willingness to experiment with new processes helps us boldly step forward one Post-it at a time.</p>\n\n<p><b>Key Qualifications:</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Enthusiasm to work hard and achieve results in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Ability to work both autonomously and in constant collaboration with teammates, colleagues, and external contacts</li><li>Determination to find the answers to open-ended questions</li><li>Desire to delve into details to understand how they fit into the big picture</li><li>Capacity to learn quickly and apply knowledge on the fly</li><li>Flexibility to adapt to quickly changing priorities and an openness to assist wherever needed</li><li>Aptitude at anticipating and preventing problems, issues, and roadblocks before they materialize while strategizing for when things go wrong</li><li>Motivation to help our teams succeed</li><li>Desire to partner with the people and teams we support, gather context, and tailor solutions</li><li>Desire to work with engineers in a start-up environment</li><li>Discretion for sensitive information</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements:</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Excellent written and verbal communication</li><li>Ability to work a varied schedule based on the needs of the people or team you support (Note: some nights and weekends required)</li><li>Some college or equivalent relevant work experience</li><li>1 year minimum administrative, support, or customer service experience (more experience required for some roles)</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Preferred:</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Microsoft Outlook/calendar experience with heavy calendars and resource booking</li><li>Familiarity with travel booking and expense reporting via Concur</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Roles:</b></p>\n\n<p>We are hiring for a range of administrative roles. Through the interview process we will help you connect with the role(s) that best suit your experience, abilities, and goals. Potential roles include: Front Desk Administrator, Generalist Admin, Team Admin, and Executive Admin.</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYRPAA4"},"a0m80000005wmtlAAA":{"id":"a0m80000005wmtlAAA","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005wmtl","published_id":"a0m80000005wmtl","label":"Mission Ops: Systems Analyst - Washington, D.C.","name":"Mission Ops: Systems Analyst","publishing_category":"Mission Operations","physical_location":"Washington, D.C.","location":"Washington, D.C.","description":"<p>Statsopt’s Mission Operations Systems Analysts are the first responders for our Business Development team on tough technical issues. Our duties range across the IT spectrum, from systems administration and hardware-building to trade shows and help desk support. Adaptability is key for us – we need to be able to talk fluently to both people and machines while working in any of several IT specialties; we’re the interdisciplinary team that gets called on to solve the hardest problems with solutions that attack the root cause. We fix whatever issues the rest of Business Development throws our way, and more importantly we do all we can to prevent problems from occurring to begin with. Our varied expertise is called upon daily in consultations across teams across the organization. We’re the technical arm of Statsopt’s logistical team, known for our excellence in execution, and we approach every day with the proactive attitude that allows us to consistently exceed expectations.</p>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Proactively support the Business Development team with an emphasis on adaptability</li><li>Create and maintain demo/training computers and their support infrastructure</li><li>Provide troubleshooting service at all levels</li><li>Simultaneously work on time-dependent projects in an extremely fast-paced environment</li><li>Support the rest of the Mission Ops &amp; Site Reliability teams as necessary</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>2+ years experience in IT support or equivalent</li><li>Basic understanding of UNIX/Linux server management</li><li>Strong analytical and problem solving skills</li><li>Eagerness to take ownership</li><li>Ability to perform at a high level in high pressure situations</li><li>Extreme attention to detail</li><li>Ability to clearly articulate problems and proposed solutions to varied audiences</li><li>Skepticism of inertia and the status quo</li><li>10-15% travel with optional potential for up to 75%</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>Optional</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Previous or current security clearance</li><li>Solid knowledge of UNIX/Linux server administration and configuration</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYS4AAO"},"a0m80000006LUWmAAO":{"id":"a0m80000006LUWmAAO","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006LUWm","published_id":"a0m80000006LUWm","label":"Administrative Assistant - Washington, D.C.","name":"Administrative Assistant","publishing_category":"Operations","physical_location":"Washington, D.C.","location":"Washington, D.C.","description":"<p>Statsopt Administrative Professionals are the behind-the-scenes, multitasking powerhouses that ensure the people, teams, and projects we support run smoothly. Our day-to-day is a fast-paced landscape of new challenges, creative problem solving, and goal setting. Every “To Do” we complete brings us one step closer to our mission. Our positive spirit and can-do attitude transforms chaos into order, paving the way for Statsopt’s success. Our willingness to experiment with new processes helps us boldly step forward one Post-it at a time.</p>\n\n<p><b>Key Qualifications:</b></p>\n\n<ul><li>Enthusiasm to work hard and achieve results in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Ability to work both autonomously and in constant collaboration with teammates, colleagues, and external contacts</li><li>Determination to find the answers to open-ended questions</li><li>Desire to delve into details to understand how they fit into the big picture</li><li>Capacity to learn quickly and apply knowledge on the fly</li><li>Flexibility to adapt to quickly changing priorities and an openness to assist wherever needed</li><li>Aptitude at anticipating and preventing problems, issues, and roadblocks before they materialize while strategizing for when things go wrong</li><li>Motivation to help our teams succeed</li><li>Desire to partner with the people and teams we support, gather context, and tailor solutions</li><