 point of contact for technical questions and concerns; we work hard to provide answers and solutions, and only escalate when absolutely necessary. We&#39;re the first-responders when problems arise, and proactively implement solutions to avoid recurrence. We strive for perfection in insulating our deployments against technical pitfalls, and have a boots-on-the-ground, ego-free approach to everything we do.</p>\n<b>Responsibilities</b>\n<ul><li>Increase Statsopt deployment stability by constantly anticipating and exceeding customer requirements</li><li>Monitor the health and uptime of the Statsopt stack</li><li>Be the first responder for customer problems, concerns or updates</li><li>Apply Linux admin skills to administer and configure large clusters</li><li>Participation in 24/7 on-call rotation</li></ul>\n<b>Requirements</b>\n<ul><li>1-3+ years experience with Linux system admin (CentOS or RHEL)</li><li>Familiarity with wide range of shell scripting/web technologies such as PHP or Rails</li><li>Basic knowledge of such database systems as Oracle, Cassandra, or PostgreSQL</li><li>Experience administering and managing collocated servers, including hardware troubleshooting</li><li>Excellent customer service: relationship development skills and instant professionalism</li><li>Ability to communicate with both technical and non-technical personnel</li><li>Enthusiasm for working one on one with customers in an onsite setting</li><li>Unbending commitment to operational security and ethics</li><li>Hard working, professional, and most importantly, genuine</li></ul>\n<b>Preferred</b>\n<ul><li>Experience with systems management tools like Puppet, CFEngine, Chef, SpaceWalk or Satellite</li><li>Experience with monitoring systems such as Nagios or Zenoss</li><li>Ability to travel up to 75% of the time or being open to relocation</li><li>Security clearance or the ability to obtain one</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYUAAA4"},"a0m80000005VMrJAAW":{"id":"a0m80000005VMrJAAW","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005VMrJ","published_id":"a0m80000005VMrJ","label":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer: New Grad - Washington, D.C.","name":"Forward Deployed Software Engineer: New Grad","publishing_category":"Business Development","physical_location":"Washington, D.C.","location":"Washington, D.C.","description":"<p><b>What We Do</b></p>\n\n<p>Forward Deployed Software Engineers (FDSEs) are responsible for the technical success of each of our deployments. They are full-stack developers who work side by side with our customers to lead technical implementation of our products. FDSEs understand our customers’ greatest pain points and design end-to-end solutions to address them. FDSEs solicit constant feedback on their work from both customers and colleagues, improving our products over time with rapid iteration cycles.</p>\n\n<p>FDSEs deploy cutting-edge technologies to solve our customers’ hardest problems. Projects often start with a nebulous question like “Why are we losing customers?” or “How can we more effectively identify instances of money laundering?” FDSEs are thought leaders and first movers in developing a solution, from high-level system design and prototyping to application development and data integration.</p>\n\n<p>FDSEs work with customers around the world, where they gain unique insight into the world’s most important industries and institutions. We help our customers detect insider trading, improve disaster relief, fight healthcare fraud, and more. Each mission presents different challenges, from the regulatory environment to the nature of the data to the user population. FSDEs work to accommodate all aspects of an environment to drive real outcomes for our customers.</p>\n\n<p><b>Technologies We Use</b></p>\n\n<p>Our approach is to deploy whatever technology is best to solve the problem at hand. This often means that we are learning from the bleeding edge of the open source community or developing our own tools. Recently, FDSEs have deployed:</p>\n\n<ul><li><b>Postgres, Cassandra, Hadoop,</b> and <b>Spark</b> for distributed data storage</li><li><b>Java</b> and <b>Groovy</b> for our back-end applications and data integration tools</li><li><b>Typescript, AngularJS, jQuery, Backbone, Underscore, Leaflet,</b> and <b>d3</b> for our web technologies</li><li><b>Python</b> for data science and machine learning</li><li><b>Internal frameworks</b> for our rapid iteration tools</li></ul>\n\n<p><b>What We Value</b></p>\n\n<p>FDSEs are developers with a passion for using technology to achieve a larger goal. They enjoy the challenge of solving an abstract problem and building or adopting the technology to do it. To support these goals, we value:</p>\n\n<ul><li><b>Collaboration:</b> We work with our customers, often on site, to understand and solve their problems.</li><li><b>Commitment:</b> We see projects through from beginning to end in spite of obstacles we may encounter.</li><li><b>Balance:</b> We do whatever is necessary to finish the job and trust one another to take the time we need, whether it&#39;s vacation or just a trip to the gym.</li><li><b>Communication:</b> We communicate complex technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences.</li><li><b>Improvement:</b> We push ourselves to grow and develop in new ways.</li><li><b>Impact:</b> We take on meaningful and challenging projects that change the world for the better.</li></ul>\n\n<p>Expected travel for the role varies by location.</p>","website_job":"a2a80000000PZq8AAG"},"a0m80000006LUWSAA4":{"id":"a0m80000006LUWSAA4","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006LUWS","published_id":"a0m80000006LUWS","label":"Administrative Assistant - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Administrative Assistant","publishing_category":"Operations","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>\nStatsopt Administrative Professionals are the behind-the-scenes, m