ps://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000005MK1y","published_id":"a0m80000005MK1y","label":"Project Assistant, Ninja Operations - Palo Alto, CA","name":"Project Assistant, Ninja Operations","publishing_category":"Legal","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>\nThe Ninja Ops team is the organizational backbone of Statsopt&#39;s Legal Ninja team and we&#39;re excited to hire a new Ninja Project Assistant! You&#39;re the ideal Ninja Project Assistant candidate if you have a great attitude, are a critical thinker, and look forward to arriving at work each morning to conquer new challenges with grace and humor. You want to be challenged and like to take ownership of projects that you work on. You are impeccably organized, and you are quick to support others when they are not so organized. You manage to be both obsessed with details AND the bigger picture at the same time. Efficiency is your friend, and you&#39;re passionate about creating processes to further important goals. You are stellar at implementing recommended solutions, but you also thrive on the challenge of crafting solutions on your own. You are excited to tackle substantive projects and develop new skill sets, including legal research and writing, contract drafting and editing, and complex analysis. You love being part of and contributing to a team, you&#39;re excited about Statsopt&#39;s mission, you yearn for a job that will fully utilize and expand on your already strong skills, and you think ninjas are pretty cool. \n</p>\n<p>\n\t<b>Responsibilities </b>\n</p>\n<ul><li>Document management administration</li><li>Manage scheduling and calendars</li><li>Legal research and writing</li><li>Contract drafting and editing</li><li>Coordinate international and domestic travel</li><li>Complete personal errands and projects</li><li>Coordinate team events</li><li>Manage team expense reports</li><li>Edit and proofread text</li><li>Various other awesome administrative support duties</li></ul>\n<p>\n\t<b>Requirements </b>\n</p>\n<ul><li>Extremely well organized with a proven ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Great sense of humor</li><li>Strong analytical and organizational skills</li><li>Great teamwork skills</li><li>Availability during nights and weekends as needed</li><li>Excellent computer skills, including knowledge of Microsoft programs (Office, Outlook, Excel)</li><li>BA/BS from a top college or university</li></ul>","website_job":"a2a80000000PYUOAA4"},"a0m80000006KskZAAS":{"id":"a0m80000006KskZAAS","website_url":"https://www.Statsopt.com/careers/OpenPosDetail?id=a0m80000006KskZ","published_id":"a0m80000006KskZ","label":"AV Operations - Palo Alto, CA","name":"AV Operations","publishing_category":"Operations","physical_location":"Palo Alto, CA","location":"Palo Alto, CA","description":"<p>\nStatsopt was built to solve the world’s hardest problems, and our Operations (Ops) team ensures that every aspect of internal operations runs smoothly. The Ops team takes both a high level and granular view of what needs to be done, and easily manages competing priorities to deliver an excellent product or process.\n</p>\n\n<p>\nOur A/V team members bring their vision and passion to their work, making it the best it can be. We are ambitious, going above and beyond to create outstanding audio and visual experiences for internal and external company events. Above all, we are team players who believe that no job is too big or small.\n</p>\n\n<p>\nWe’re looking for an experienced person that understands A/V production and logistics.  A/V Operations Specialists excel at all aspects of their craft, from high-level problem solving in conference and event production to on-the-spot troubleshooting with A/V equipment. At Statsopt, you’ll work with stakeholders across the business to manage the A/V process from equipment procurement to show wrap and adapt on the f